346#define DOCUMENT_RELEASE_LOG_ERROR(channel, fmt, ...) RELEASE_LOG_ERROR(channel, "%p - [pageID=%" PRIu64 ", frameID=%" PRIu64 ", main=%d] Document::" fmt, this, pageID().value_or(PageIdentifier { }).toUInt64(), frameID().value_or(FrameIdentifier { }).toUInt64(), this == &topDocument(), ##__VA_ARGS__)

359struct FrameFlatteningLayoutDisallower {
360 FrameFlatteningLayoutDisallower(FrameView& frameView)
361 : m_frameView(frameView)
362 , m_disallowLayout(frameView.effectiveFrameFlattening() != FrameFlattening::Disabled)
363 {
364 if (m_disallowLayout)
365 m_frameView.startDisallowingLayout();
366 }
367
368 ~FrameFlatteningLayoutDisallower()
369 {
370 if (m_disallowLayout)
371 m_frameView.endDisallowingLayout();
372 }
373
374private:
375 FrameView& m_frameView;
376 bool m_disallowLayout { false };
377};

391// DOM Level 2 says (letters added):
392//
393// a) Name start characters must have one of the categories Ll, Lu, Lo, Lt, Nl.
394// b) Name characters other than Name-start characters must have one of the categories Mc, Me, Mn, Lm, or Nd.
395// c) Characters in the compatibility area (i.e. with character code greater than #xF900 and less than #xFFFE) are not allowed in XML names.
396// d) Characters which have a font or compatibility decomposition (i.e. those with a "compatibility formatting tag" in field 5 of the database -- marked by field 5 beginning with a "<") are not allowed.
397// e) The following characters are treated as name-start characters rather than name characters, because the property file classifies them as Alphabetic: [#x02BB-#x02C1], #x0559, #x06E5, #x06E6.
398// f) Characters #x20DD-#x20E0 are excluded (in accordance with Unicode, section 5.14).
399// g) Character #x00B7 is classified as an extender, because the property list so identifies it.
400// h) Character #x0387 is added as a name character, because #x00B7 is its canonical equivalent.
401// i) Characters ':' and '_' are allowed as name-start characters.
402// j) Characters '-' and '.' are allowed as name characters.
403//
404// It also contains complete tables. If we decide it's better, we could include those instead of the following code.
405
406static inline bool isValidNameStart(UChar32 c)
407{
408 // rule (e) above
409 if ((c >= 0x02BB && c <= 0x02C1) || c == 0x559 || c == 0x6E5 || c == 0x6E6)
410 return true;
411
412 // rule (i) above
413 if (c == ':' || c == '_')
414 return true;
415
416 // rules (a) and (f) above
417 if (!(U_GET_GC_MASK(c) & (U_GC_LL_MASK | U_GC_LU_MASK | U_GC_LO_MASK | U_GC_LT_MASK | U_GC_NL_MASK)))
418 return false;
419
420 // rule (c) above
421 if (c >= 0xF900 && c < 0xFFFE)
422 return false;
423
424 // rule (d) above
425 int type = u_getIntPropertyValue(c, UCHAR_DECOMPOSITION_TYPE);
426 if (type == U_DT_FONT || type == U_DT_COMPAT)
427 return false;
428
429 return true;
430}
431
432static inline bool isValidNamePart(UChar32 c)
433{
434 // rules (a), (e), and (i) above
435 if (isValidNameStart(c))
436 return true;
437
438 // rules (g) and (h) above
439 if (c == 0x00B7 || c == 0x0387)
440 return true;
441
442 // rule (j) above
443 if (c == '-' || c == '.')
444 return true;
445
446 // rules (b) and (f) above
447 if (!(U_GET_GC_MASK(c) & (U_GC_M_MASK | U_GC_LM_MASK | U_GC_ND_MASK)))
448 return false;
449
450 // rule (c) above
451 if (c >= 0xF900 && c < 0xFFFE)
452 return false;
453
454 // rule (d) above
455 int type = u_getIntPropertyValue(c, UCHAR_DECOMPOSITION_TYPE);
456 if (type == U_DT_FONT || type == U_DT_COMPAT)
457 return false;
458
459 return true;
460}
461
462static Widget* widgetForElement(Element* focusedElement)
463{
464 if (!focusedElement)
465 return nullptr;
466 auto* renderer = focusedElement->renderer();
467 if (!is<RenderWidget>(renderer))
468 return nullptr;
469 return downcast<RenderWidget>(*renderer).widget();
470}
471
472static bool acceptsEditingFocus(const Element& element)
473{
474 ASSERT(element.hasEditableStyle());
475
476 auto* root = element.rootEditableElement();
477 Frame* frame = element.document().frame();
478 if (!frame || !root)
479 return false;
480
481 return frame->editor().shouldBeginEditing(makeRangeSelectingNodeContents(*root));
482}
483
484static bool canAccessAncestor(const SecurityOrigin& activeSecurityOrigin, Frame* targetFrame)
485{
486 // targetFrame can be 0 when we're trying to navigate a top-level frame
487 // that has a 0 opener.
488 if (!targetFrame)
489 return false;
490
491 const bool isLocalActiveOrigin = activeSecurityOrigin.isLocal();
492 for (Frame* ancestorFrame = targetFrame; ancestorFrame; ancestorFrame = ancestorFrame->tree().parent()) {
493 Document* ancestorDocument = ancestorFrame->document();
494 // FIXME: Should be an ASSERT? Frames should alway have documents.
495 if (!ancestorDocument)
496 return true;
497
498 const SecurityOrigin& ancestorSecurityOrigin = ancestorDocument->securityOrigin();
499 if (activeSecurityOrigin.isSameOriginDomain(ancestorSecurityOrigin))
500 return true;
501
502 // Allow file URL descendant navigation even when allowFileAccessFromFileURLs is false.
503 // FIXME: It's a bit strange to special-case local origins here. Should we be doing
504 // something more general instead?
505 if (isLocalActiveOrigin && ancestorSecurityOrigin.isLocal())
506 return true;
507 }
508
509 return false;
510}
511
512static void printNavigationErrorMessage(Frame& frame, const URL& activeURL, const char* reason)
513{
514 String message = "Unsafe JavaScript attempt to initiate navigation for frame with URL '" + frame.document()->url().string() + "' from frame with URL '" + activeURL.string() + "'. " + reason + "\n";
515
516 // FIXME: should we print to the console of the document performing the navigation instead?
517 frame.document()->domWindow()->printErrorMessage(message);
518}

520uint64_t Document::s_globalTreeVersion = 0;
521
522static const void* sharedLoggerOwner()
523{
524 static uint64_t owner = cryptographicallyRandomNumber();
525 return reinterpret_cast<const void*>(owner);
526}
527
528static Logger*& staticSharedLogger()
529{
530 static Logger* logger;
531 return logger;
532}
533
534const Logger& Document::sharedLogger()
535{
536 if (!staticSharedLogger()) {
537 staticSharedLogger() = &Logger::create(sharedLoggerOwner()).leakRef();
538 configureSharedLogger();
539 }
540
541 return *staticSharedLogger();
542}
543
544void Document::configureSharedLogger()
545{
546 auto logger = staticSharedLogger();
547 if (!logger)
548 return;
549
550 bool alwaysOnLoggingAllowed = !allDocumentsMap().isEmpty() && WTF::allOf(allDocumentsMap().values(), [](auto* document) {
551 auto* page = document->page();
552 return !page || page->sessionID().isAlwaysOnLoggingAllowed();
553 });
554 logger->setEnabled(sharedLoggerOwner(), alwaysOnLoggingAllowed);
555}
556
557void Document::addToDocumentsMap()
558{
559 auto addResult = allDocumentsMap().add(m_identifier, this);
560 ASSERT_UNUSED(addResult, addResult.isNewEntry);
561
562 configureSharedLogger();
563}
564
565void Document::removeFromDocumentsMap()
566{
567 ASSERT(allDocumentsMap().contains(m_identifier));
568 allDocumentsMap().remove(m_identifier);
569 configureSharedLogger();
570}
571
572auto Document::allDocumentsMap() -> DocumentsMap&
573{
574 static NeverDestroyed<DocumentsMap> documents;
575 return documents;
576}
577
578auto Document::allDocuments() -> DocumentsMap::ValuesIteratorRange
579{
580 return allDocumentsMap().values();
581}

583static inline int currentOrientation(Frame* frame)
584{
585#if ENABLE(ORIENTATION_EVENTS)
586 if (frame)
587 return frame->orientation();
588#else
589 UNUSED_PARAM(frame);
590#endif
591 return 0;
592}
593
594static Ref<CachedResourceLoader> createCachedResourceLoader(Frame* frame)
595{
596 if (frame) {
597 if (auto loader = frame->loader().activeDocumentLoader())
598 return loader->cachedResourceLoader();
599 }
600 return CachedResourceLoader::create(nullptr);
601}

603Document::Document(Frame* frame, const Settings& settings, const URL& url, DocumentClassFlags documentClasses, unsigned constructionFlags)
604 : ContainerNode(*this, CreateDocument)
605 , TreeScope(*this)
606 , FrameDestructionObserver(frame)
607 , m_settings(settings)
608 , m_quirks(makeUniqueRef<Quirks>(*this))
609 , m_cachedResourceLoader(createCachedResourceLoader(frame))
610 , m_domTreeVersion(++s_globalTreeVersion)
611 , m_styleScope(makeUnique<Style::Scope>(*this))
612 , m_extensionStyleSheets(makeUnique<ExtensionStyleSheets>(*this))
613 , m_visitedLinkState(makeUnique<VisitedLinkState>(*this))
614 , m_markers(makeUnique<DocumentMarkerController>(*this))
615 , m_styleRecalcTimer([this] { updateStyleIfNeeded(); })
616#if !LOG_DISABLED
617 , m_documentCreationTime(MonotonicTime::now())
618#endif
619 , m_scriptRunner(makeUnique<ScriptRunner>(*this))
620 , m_moduleLoader(makeUnique<ScriptModuleLoader>(*this, ScriptModuleLoader::OwnerType::Document))
621#if ENABLE(XSLT)
622 , m_applyPendingXSLTransformsTimer(*this, &Document::applyPendingXSLTransformsTimerFired)
623#endif
624 , m_xmlVersion("1.0"_s)
625 , m_constantPropertyMap(makeUnique<ConstantPropertyMap>(*this))
626 , m_documentClasses(documentClasses)
627#if ENABLE(FULLSCREEN_API)
628 , m_fullscreenManager { makeUniqueRef<FullscreenManager>(*this) }
629#endif
630#if ENABLE(INTERSECTION_OBSERVER)
631 , m_intersectionObserversInitialUpdateTimer(*this, &Document::intersectionObserversInitialUpdateTimerFired)
632#endif
633 , m_loadEventDelayTimer(*this, &Document::loadEventDelayTimerFired)
634#if PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY) && ENABLE(DEVICE_ORIENTATION)
635 , m_deviceMotionClient(makeUnique<DeviceMotionClientIOS>(page() ? page()->deviceOrientationUpdateProvider() : nullptr))
636 , m_deviceMotionController(makeUnique<DeviceMotionController>(*m_deviceMotionClient))
637 , m_deviceOrientationClient(makeUnique<DeviceOrientationClientIOS>(page() ? page()->deviceOrientationUpdateProvider() : nullptr))
638 , m_deviceOrientationController(makeUnique<DeviceOrientationController>(*m_deviceOrientationClient))
639#endif
640 , m_pendingTasksTimer(*this, &Document::pendingTasksTimerFired)
641 , m_visualUpdatesSuppressionTimer(*this, &Document::visualUpdatesSuppressionTimerFired)
642 , m_sharedObjectPoolClearTimer(*this, &Document::clearSharedObjectPool)
643 , m_fontSelector(CSSFontSelector::create(*this))
644 , m_fontLoader(makeUniqueRef<DocumentFontLoader>(*this))
645 , m_didAssociateFormControlsTimer(*this, &Document::didAssociateFormControlsTimerFired)
646 , m_cookieCacheExpiryTimer(*this, &Document::invalidateDOMCookieCache)
647 , m_socketProvider(page() ? &page()->socketProvider() : nullptr)
648 , m_isSynthesized(constructionFlags & Synthesized)
649 , m_isNonRenderedPlaceholder(constructionFlags & NonRenderedPlaceholder)
650 , m_orientationNotifier(currentOrientation(frame))
651 , m_identifier(DocumentIdentifier::generate())
652 , m_undoManager(UndoManager::create(*this))
653 , m_editor(makeUniqueRef<Editor>(*this))
654 , m_selection(makeUniqueRef<FrameSelection>(this))
655{
656 addToDocumentsMap();
657
658 // We depend on the url getting immediately set in subframes, but we
659 // also depend on the url NOT getting immediately set in opened windows.
660 // See fast/dom/early-frame-url.html
661 // and fast/dom/location-new-window-no-crash.html, respectively.
662 // FIXME: Can/should we unify this behavior?
663 if ((frame && frame->ownerElement()) || !url.isEmpty())
664 setURL(url);
665
666 m_cachedResourceLoader->setDocument(this);
667
668 resetLinkColor();
669 resetVisitedLinkColor();
670 resetActiveLinkColor();
671
672 initSecurityContext();
673 initDNSPrefetch();
674
675 m_fontSelector->registerForInvalidationCallbacks(*this);
676
677 for (auto& nodeListAndCollectionCount : m_nodeListAndCollectionCounts)
678 nodeListAndCollectionCount = 0;
679
680 InspectorInstrumentation::addEventListenersToNode(*this);
681}
682
683Ref<Document> Document::create(Document& contextDocument)
684{
685 auto document = adoptRef(*new Document(nullptr, contextDocument.m_settings, URL()));
686 document->setContextDocument(contextDocument);
687 document->setSecurityOriginPolicy(contextDocument.securityOriginPolicy());
688 return document;
689}
690
691Ref<Document> Document::createNonRenderedPlaceholder(Frame& frame, const URL& url)
692{
693 return adoptRef(*new Document(&frame, frame.settings(), url, DefaultDocumentClass, NonRenderedPlaceholder));
694}
695
696Document::~Document()
697{
698 ASSERT(activeDOMObjectsAreStopped());
699
700 if (m_logger)
701 m_logger->removeObserver(*this);
702
703#if ENABLE(INTERSECTION_OBSERVER)
704 if (m_intersectionObserverData) {
705 for (const auto& observer : m_intersectionObserverData->observers) {
706 if (observer)
707 observer->rootDestroyed();
708 }
709 m_intersectionObserverData->observers.clear();
710 // Document cannot be a target.
711 ASSERT(m_intersectionObserverData->registrations.isEmpty());
712 }
713#endif
714
715 removeFromDocumentsMap();
716
717 // We need to remove from the contexts map very early in the destructor so that calling postTask() on this Document from another thread is safe.
718 removeFromContextsMap();
719
720 ASSERT(!renderView());
721 ASSERT(m_backForwardCacheState != InBackForwardCache);
722 ASSERT(m_ranges.isEmpty());
723 ASSERT(!m_parentTreeScope);
724 ASSERT(!m_disabledFieldsetElementsCount);
725 ASSERT(m_inDocumentShadowRoots.isEmpty());
726
727#if ENABLE(DEVICE_ORIENTATION) && PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
728 m_deviceMotionClient->deviceMotionControllerDestroyed();
729 m_deviceOrientationClient->deviceOrientationControllerDestroyed();
730#endif
731
732 if (m_templateDocument)
733 m_templateDocument->setTemplateDocumentHost(nullptr); // balanced in templateDocument().
734
735 // FIXME: Should we reset m_domWindow when we detach from the Frame?
736 if (m_domWindow)
737 m_domWindow->resetUnlessSuspendedForDocumentSuspension();
738
739 m_scriptRunner = nullptr;
740 m_moduleLoader = nullptr;
741
742 removeAllEventListeners();
743
744 // Currently we believe that Document can never outlive the parser.
745 // Although the Document may be replaced synchronously, DocumentParsers
746 // generally keep at least one reference to an Element which would in turn
747 // has a reference to the Document. If you hit this ASSERT, then that
748 // assumption is wrong. DocumentParser::detach() should ensure that even
749 // if the DocumentParser outlives the Document it won't cause badness.
750 ASSERT(!m_parser || m_parser->refCount() == 1);
751 detachParser();
752
753 if (this == &topDocument())
754 clearAXObjectCache();
755
756 m_decoder = nullptr;
757
758 if (m_styleSheetList)
759 m_styleSheetList->detach();
760
761 extensionStyleSheets().detachFromDocument();
762
763 styleScope().clearResolver(); // We need to destroy CSSFontSelector before destroying m_cachedResourceLoader.
764 m_fontLoader->stopLoadingAndClearFonts();
765
766 // It's possible for multiple Documents to end up referencing the same CachedResourceLoader (e.g., SVGImages
767 // load the initial empty document and the SVGDocument with the same DocumentLoader).
768 if (m_cachedResourceLoader->document() == this)
769 m_cachedResourceLoader->setDocument(nullptr);
770
771 // We must call clearRareData() here since a Document class inherits TreeScope
772 // as well as Node. See a comment on TreeScope.h for the reason.
773 if (hasRareData())
774 clearRareData();
775
776 RELEASE_ASSERT_WITH_SECURITY_IMPLICATION(m_listsInvalidatedAtDocument.isEmpty());
777 RELEASE_ASSERT_WITH_SECURITY_IMPLICATION(m_collectionsInvalidatedAtDocument.isEmpty());
778
779 for (unsigned count : m_nodeListAndCollectionCounts)
780 ASSERT_UNUSED(count, !count);
781}
782
783void Document::removedLastRef()
784{
785 ScriptDisallowedScope::InMainThread scriptDisallowedScope;
786 ASSERT(!m_deletionHasBegun);
787 if (m_referencingNodeCount) {
788 // Node::removedLastRef doesn't set refCount() to zero because it's not observable.
789 // But we need to remember that our refCount reached zero in subsequent calls to decrementReferencingNodeCount().
790 m_refCountAndParentBit = 0;
791
792 // If removing a child removes the last node reference, we don't want the scope to be destroyed
793 // until after removeDetachedChildren returns, so we protect ourselves.
794 incrementReferencingNodeCount();
795
796 RELEASE_ASSERT(!hasLivingRenderTree());
797 // We must make sure not to be retaining any of our children through
798 // these extra pointers or we will create a reference cycle.
799 m_focusedElement = nullptr;
800 m_hoveredElement = nullptr;
801 m_activeElement = nullptr;
802 m_titleElement = nullptr;
803 m_documentElement = nullptr;
804 m_focusNavigationStartingNode = nullptr;
805 m_userActionElements.clear();
806#if ENABLE(FULLSCREEN_API)
807 m_fullscreenManager->clear();
808#endif
809 m_associatedFormControls.clear();
810 m_pendingRenderTreeTextUpdate = { };
811
812 m_fontLoader->stopLoadingAndClearFonts();
813
814 detachParser();
815
816 RELEASE_ASSERT(m_selection->isNone());
817
818 // removeDetachedChildren() doesn't always unregister IDs,
819 // so tear down scope information up front to avoid having
820 // stale references in the map.
821
822 destroyTreeScopeData();
823 removeDetachedChildren();
824 m_formController = nullptr;
825
826 m_markers->detach();
827
828 m_cssCanvasElements.clear();
829
830 commonTeardown();
831
832#ifndef NDEBUG
833 // We need to do this right now since selfOnlyDeref() can delete this.
834 m_inRemovedLastRefFunction = false;
835#endif
836 decrementReferencingNodeCount();
837 } else {
838 commonTeardown();
839#ifndef NDEBUG
840 m_inRemovedLastRefFunction = false;
841 m_deletionHasBegun = true;
842#endif
843 delete this;
844 }
845}
846
847void Document::commonTeardown()
848{
849 stopActiveDOMObjects();
850
851#if ENABLE(FULLSCREEN_API)
852 m_fullscreenManager->emptyEventQueue();
853#endif
854
855 if (svgExtensions())
856 accessSVGExtensions().pauseAnimations();
857
858 clearScriptedAnimationController();
859
860 m_documentFragmentForInnerOuterHTML = nullptr;
861
862 if (m_highlightRegister)
863 m_highlightRegister->clear();
864#if ENABLE(APP_HIGHLIGHTS)
865 if (m_appHighlightRegister)
866 m_appHighlightRegister->clear();
867#endif
868 m_pendingScrollEventTargetList = nullptr;
869
870 if (m_timelinesController)
871 m_timelinesController->detachFromDocument();
872
873 m_timeline = nullptr;
874}

876Element* Document::elementForAccessKey(const String& key)
877{
878 if (key.isEmpty())
879 return nullptr;
880 if (!m_accessKeyCache)
881 buildAccessKeyCache();
882 return m_accessKeyCache->get(key).get();
883}
884
885void Document::buildAccessKeyCache()
886{
887 m_accessKeyCache = makeUnique<HashMap<String, WeakPtr<Element>, ASCIICaseInsensitiveHash>>([this] {
888 HashMap<String, WeakPtr<Element>, ASCIICaseInsensitiveHash> map;
889 for (auto& node : composedTreeDescendants(*this)) {
890 if (!is<Element>(node))
891 continue;
892 auto& element = downcast<Element>(node);
893 auto& key = element.attributeWithoutSynchronization(accesskeyAttr);
894 if (key.isEmpty())
895 continue;
896 map.add(key, makeWeakPtr(element));
897 }
898 return map;
899 }());
900}
901
902void Document::invalidateAccessKeyCacheSlowCase()
903{
904 m_accessKeyCache = nullptr;
905}

910 return Exception { SyntaxError };
911 if (!m_selectorQueryCache)
912 m_selectorQueryCache = makeUnique<SelectorQueryCache>();
913 return m_selectorQueryCache->add(selectorString, *this);
914}

922{

924 // the policy defined elsewhere.

926 return;

938void Document::setCompatibilityMode(DocumentCompatibilityMode mode)
939{
940 if (m_compatibilityModeLocked || mode == m_compatibilityMode)
941 return;
942 bool wasInQuirksMode = inQuirksMode();
943 m_compatibilityMode = mode;
944
945 clearSelectorQueryCache();
946
947 if (inQuirksMode() != wasInQuirksMode) {
948 // All user stylesheets have to reparse using the different mode.
949 extensionStyleSheets().clearPageUserSheet();
950 extensionStyleSheets().invalidateInjectedStyleSheetCache();
951 }
952}

954String Document::compatMode() const
955{
956 return inQuirksMode() ? "BackCompat" : "CSS1Compat";
957}

959const Color& Document::themeColor()
960{
961 if (!m_cachedThemeColor.isValid()) {
962 if (!m_activeThemeColorMetaElement)
963 m_activeThemeColorMetaElement = determineActiveThemeColorMetaElement();
964 if (m_activeThemeColorMetaElement)
965 m_cachedThemeColor = m_activeThemeColorMetaElement->contentColor();
966
967 if (!m_cachedThemeColor.isValid())
968 m_cachedThemeColor = m_applicationManifestThemeColor;
969 }
970 return m_cachedThemeColor;
971}

1009void Document::childrenChanged(const ChildChange& change)
1010{
1011 ContainerNode::childrenChanged(change);
1012
1013 // FIXME: Chrome::didReceiveDocType() used to be called only when the doctype changed. We need to check the
1014 // impact of calling this systematically. If the overhead is negligible, we need to rename didReceiveDocType,
1015 // otherwise, we need to detect the doc type changes before updating the viewport.
1016 if (Page* page = this->page())
1017 page->chrome().didReceiveDocType(*frame());
1018
1019 Element* newDocumentElement = childrenOfType<Element>(*this).first();
1020 if (newDocumentElement == m_documentElement)
1021 return;
1022 m_documentElement = newDocumentElement;
1023 // The root style used for media query matching depends on the document element.
1024 styleScope().clearResolver();
1025}

1027static ALWAYS_INLINE Ref<HTMLElement> createUpgradeCandidateElement(Document& document, const QualifiedName& name)
1028{
1029 if (Document::validateCustomElementName(name.localName()) != CustomElementNameValidationStatus::Valid)
1030 return HTMLUnknownElement::create(name, document);
1031
1032 auto element = HTMLElement::create(name, document);
1033 element->setIsCustomElementUpgradeCandidate();
1034 return element;
1035}
1036
1037static ALWAYS_INLINE Ref<HTMLElement> createUpgradeCandidateElement(Document& document, const AtomString& localName)
1038{
1039 return createUpgradeCandidateElement(document, QualifiedName { nullAtom(), localName, xhtmlNamespaceURI });
1040}

1042static inline bool isValidHTMLElementName(const AtomString& localName)
1043{
1044 return Document::isValidName(localName);
1045}
1046
1047static inline bool isValidHTMLElementName(const QualifiedName& name)
1048{
1049 return Document::isValidName(name.localName());
1050}
1051
1052template<typename NameType>
1053static ExceptionOr<Ref<Element>> createHTMLElementWithNameValidation(Document& document, const NameType& name)
1054{
1055 auto element = HTMLElementFactory::createKnownElement(name, document);
1056 if (LIKELY(element))
1057 return Ref<Element> { element.releaseNonNull() };
1058
1059 if (auto* window = document.domWindow()) {
1060 auto* registry = window->customElementRegistry();
1061 if (UNLIKELY(registry)) {
1062 if (auto* elementInterface = registry->findInterface(name))
1063 return elementInterface->constructElementWithFallback(document, name);
1064 }
1065 }
1066
1067 if (UNLIKELY(!isValidHTMLElementName(name)))
1068 return Exception { InvalidCharacterError };
1069
1070 return Ref<Element> { createUpgradeCandidateElement(document, name) };
1071}
1072
1073ExceptionOr<Ref<Element>> Document::createElementForBindings(const AtomString& name)
1074{
1075 if (isHTMLDocument())
1076 return createHTMLElementWithNameValidation(*this, name.convertToASCIILowercase());
1077
1078 if (isXHTMLDocument())
1079 return createHTMLElementWithNameValidation(*this, name);
1080
1081 if (!isValidName(name))
1082 return Exception { InvalidCharacterError };
1083
1084 return createElement(QualifiedName(nullAtom(), name, nullAtom()), false);
1085}

1134
1135ExceptionOr<Ref<Node>> Document::importNode(Node& nodeToImport, bool deep)
1136{
1137 switch (nodeToImport.nodeType()) {
1138 case DOCUMENT_FRAGMENT_NODE:
1139 if (nodeToImport.isShadowRoot())
1140 break;
1141 FALLTHROUGH;
1142 case ELEMENT_NODE:
1143 case TEXT_NODE:
1144 case CDATA_SECTION_NODE:
1145 case PROCESSING_INSTRUCTION_NODE:
1146 case COMMENT_NODE:
1147 return nodeToImport.cloneNodeInternal(document(), deep ? CloningOperation::Everything : CloningOperation::OnlySelf);
1148
1149 case ATTRIBUTE_NODE: {
1150 auto& attribute = downcast<Attr>(nodeToImport);
1151 return Ref<Node> { Attr::create(*this, attribute.qualifiedName(), attribute.value()) };
1152 }
1153 case DOCUMENT_NODE: // Can't import a document into another document.
1154 case DOCUMENT_TYPE_NODE: // FIXME: Support cloning a DocumentType node per DOM4.
1155 break;
1156 }
1157
1158 return Exception { NotSupportedError };
1159}
1160
1161
1162ExceptionOr<Ref<Node>> Document::adoptNode(Node& source)
1163{
1164 EventQueueScope scope;
1165
1166 switch (source.nodeType()) {
1167 case DOCUMENT_NODE:
1168 return Exception { NotSupportedError };
1169 case ATTRIBUTE_NODE: {
1170 auto& attr = downcast<Attr>(source);
1171 if (auto* element = attr.ownerElement()) {
1172 auto result = element->removeAttributeNode(attr);
1173 if (result.hasException())
1174 return result.releaseException();
1175 }
1176 break;
1177 }
1178 default:
1179 if (source.isShadowRoot()) {
1180 // ShadowRoot cannot disconnect itself from the host node.
1181 return Exception { HierarchyRequestError };
1182 }
1183 if (is<HTMLFrameOwnerElement>(source)) {
1184 auto& frameOwnerElement = downcast<HTMLFrameOwnerElement>(source);
1185 if (frame() && frame()->tree().isDescendantOf(frameOwnerElement.contentFrame()))
1186 return Exception { HierarchyRequestError };
1187 }
1188 auto result = source.remove();
1189 if (result.hasException())
1190 return result.releaseException();
1191 RELEASE_ASSERT(!source.isConnected());
1192 RELEASE_ASSERT(!source.parentNode());
1193 }
1194
1195 source.setTreeScopeRecursively(*this);
1196
1197 return Ref<Node> { source };
1198}
1199
1200bool Document::hasValidNamespaceForElements(const QualifiedName& qName)
1201{
1202 // These checks are from DOM Core Level 2, createElementNS
1203 // http://www.w3.org/TR/DOM-Level-2-Core/core.html#ID-DocCrElNS
1204 if (!qName.prefix().isEmpty() && qName.namespaceURI().isNull()) // createElementNS(null, "html:div")
1205 return false;
1206 if (qName.prefix() == xmlAtom() && qName.namespaceURI() != XMLNames::xmlNamespaceURI) // createElementNS("http://www.example.com", "xml:lang")
1207 return false;
1208
1209 // Required by DOM Level 3 Core and unspecified by DOM Level 2 Core:
1210 // http://www.w3.org/TR/2004/REC-DOM-Level-3-Core-20040407/core.html#ID-DocCrElNS
1211 // createElementNS("http://www.w3.org/2000/xmlns/", "foo:bar"), createElementNS(null, "xmlns:bar"), createElementNS(null, "xmlns")
1212 if (qName.prefix() == xmlnsAtom() || (qName.prefix().isEmpty() && qName.localName() == xmlnsAtom()))
1213 return qName.namespaceURI() == XMLNSNames::xmlnsNamespaceURI;
1214 return qName.namespaceURI() != XMLNSNames::xmlnsNamespaceURI;
1215}
1216
1217bool Document::hasValidNamespaceForAttributes(const QualifiedName& qName)
1218{
1219 return hasValidNamespaceForElements(qName);
1220}
1221
1222static Ref<HTMLElement> createFallbackHTMLElement(Document& document, const QualifiedName& name)
1223{
1224 if (auto* window = document.domWindow()) {
1225 auto* registry = window->customElementRegistry();
1226 if (UNLIKELY(registry)) {
1227 if (auto* elementInterface = registry->findInterface(name)) {
1228 auto element = HTMLElement::create(name, document);
1229 element->setIsCustomElementUpgradeCandidate();
1230 element->enqueueToUpgrade(*elementInterface);
1231 return element;
1232 }
1233 }
1234 }
1235 // FIXME: Should we also check the equality of prefix between the custom element and name?
1236 return createUpgradeCandidateElement(document, name);
1237}
1238
1239// FIXME: This should really be in a possible ElementFactory class.
1240Ref<Element> Document::createElement(const QualifiedName& name, bool createdByParser)
1241{
1242 RefPtr<Element> element;
1243
1244 // FIXME: Use registered namespaces and look up in a hash to find the right factory.
1245 if (name.namespaceURI() == xhtmlNamespaceURI) {
1246 element = HTMLElementFactory::createKnownElement(name, *this, nullptr, createdByParser);
1247 if (UNLIKELY(!element))
1248 element = createFallbackHTMLElement(*this, name);
1249 } else if (name.namespaceURI() == SVGNames::svgNamespaceURI)
1250 element = SVGElementFactory::createElement(name, *this, createdByParser);
1251#if ENABLE(MATHML)
1252 else if (name.namespaceURI() == MathMLNames::mathmlNamespaceURI)
1253 element = MathMLElementFactory::createElement(name, *this, createdByParser);
1254#endif
1255
1256 if (element)
1257 m_sawElementsInKnownNamespaces = true;
1258 else
1259 element = Element::create(name, document());
1260
1261 // <image> uses imgTag so we need a special rule.
1262 ASSERT((name.matches(imageTag) && element->tagQName().matches(imgTag) && element->tagQName().prefix() == name.prefix()) || name == element->tagQName());
1263
1264 return element.releaseNonNull();
1265}
1266
1267// https://html.spec.whatwg.org/#valid-custom-element-name
1268
1269struct UnicodeCodePointRange {
1270 UChar32 minimum;
1271 UChar32 maximum;
1272};
1273
1274#if ASSERT_ENABLED
1275
1276static inline bool operator<(const UnicodeCodePointRange& a, const UnicodeCodePointRange& b)
1277{
1278 ASSERT(a.minimum <= a.maximum);
1279 ASSERT(b.minimum <= b.maximum);
1280 return a.maximum < b.minimum;
1281}
1282
1283#endif // ASSERT_ENABLED
1284
1285static inline bool operator<(const UnicodeCodePointRange& a, UChar32 b)
1286{
1287 ASSERT(a.minimum <= a.maximum);
1288 return a.maximum < b;
1289}
1290
1291static inline bool operator<(UChar32 a, const UnicodeCodePointRange& b)
1292{
1293 ASSERT(b.minimum <= b.maximum);
1294 return a < b.minimum;
1295}
1296
1297static inline bool isPotentialCustomElementNameCharacter(UChar32 character)
1298{
1299 static const UnicodeCodePointRange ranges[] = {
1300 { '-', '.' },
1301 { '0', '9' },
1302 { '_', '_' },
1303 { 'a', 'z' },
1304 { 0xB7, 0xB7 },
1305 { 0xC0, 0xD6 },
1306 { 0xD8, 0xF6 },
1307 { 0xF8, 0x37D },
1308 { 0x37F, 0x1FFF },
1309 { 0x200C, 0x200D },
1310 { 0x203F, 0x2040 },
1311 { 0x2070, 0x218F },
1312 { 0x2C00, 0x2FEF },
1313 { 0x3001, 0xD7FF },
1314 { 0xF900, 0xFDCF },
1315 { 0xFDF0, 0xFFFD },
1316 { 0x10000, 0xEFFFF },
1317 };
1318
1319 ASSERT(std::is_sorted(std::begin(ranges), std::end(ranges)));
1320 return std::binary_search(std::begin(ranges), std::end(ranges), character);
1321}
1322
1323CustomElementNameValidationStatus Document::validateCustomElementName(const AtomString& localName)
1324{
1325 if (!isASCIILower(localName[0]))
1326 return CustomElementNameValidationStatus::FirstCharacterIsNotLowercaseASCIILetter;
1327
1328 bool containsHyphen = false;
1329 for (auto character : StringView(localName).codePoints()) {
1330 if (isASCIIUpper(character))
1331 return CustomElementNameValidationStatus::ContainsUppercaseASCIILetter;
1332 if (!isPotentialCustomElementNameCharacter(character))
1333 return CustomElementNameValidationStatus::ContainsDisallowedCharacter;
1334 if (character == '-')
1335 containsHyphen = true;
1336 }
1337
1338 if (!containsHyphen)
1339 return CustomElementNameValidationStatus::ContainsNoHyphen;
1340
1341#if ENABLE(MATHML)
1342 const auto& annotationXmlLocalName = MathMLNames::annotation_xmlTag->localName();
1343#else
1344 static MainThreadNeverDestroyed<const AtomString> annotationXmlLocalName("annotation-xml", AtomString::ConstructFromLiteral);
1345#endif
1346 static MainThreadNeverDestroyed<const AtomString> colorProfileLocalName("color-profile", AtomString::ConstructFromLiteral);
1347
1348 if (localName == SVGNames::font_faceTag->localName()
1349 || localName == SVGNames::font_face_formatTag->localName()
1350 || localName == SVGNames::font_face_nameTag->localName()
1351 || localName == SVGNames::font_face_srcTag->localName()
1352 || localName == SVGNames::font_face_uriTag->localName()
1353 || localName == SVGNames::missing_glyphTag->localName()
1354 || localName == annotationXmlLocalName
1355 || localName == colorProfileLocalName)
1356 return CustomElementNameValidationStatus::ConflictsWithStandardElementName;
1357
1358 return CustomElementNameValidationStatus::Valid;
1359}
1360
1361ExceptionOr<Ref<Element>> Document::createElementNS(const AtomString& namespaceURI, const String& qualifiedName)
1362{
1363 auto parseResult = parseQualifiedName(namespaceURI, qualifiedName);
1364 if (parseResult.hasException())
1365 return parseResult.releaseException();
1366 QualifiedName parsedName { parseResult.releaseReturnValue() };
1367 if (!hasValidNamespaceForElements(parsedName))
1368 return Exception { NamespaceError };
1369
1370 if (parsedName.namespaceURI() == xhtmlNamespaceURI)
1371 return createHTMLElementWithNameValidation(*this, parsedName);
1372
1373 return createElement(parsedName, false);
1374}
1375
1376void Document::setReadyState(ReadyState readyState)
1377{
1378 if (readyState == m_readyState)
1379 return;
1380
1381 switch (readyState) {
1382 case Loading:
1383 if (!m_eventTiming.domLoading)
1384 m_eventTiming.domLoading = MonotonicTime::now();
1385 break;
1386 case Complete:
1387 if (!m_eventTiming.domComplete)
1388 m_eventTiming.domComplete = MonotonicTime::now();
1389 FALLTHROUGH;
1390 case Interactive:
1391 if (!m_eventTiming.domInteractive)
1392 m_eventTiming.domInteractive = MonotonicTime::now();
1393 break;
1394 }
1395
1396 m_readyState = readyState;
1397 dispatchEvent(Event::create(eventNames().readystatechangeEvent, Event::CanBubble::No, Event::IsCancelable::No));
1398
1399 if (settings().suppressesIncrementalRendering())
1400 setVisualUpdatesAllowed(readyState);
1401}
1402
1403void Document::setVisualUpdatesAllowed(ReadyState readyState)
1404{
1405 ASSERT(settings().suppressesIncrementalRendering());
1406 switch (readyState) {
1407 case Loading:
1408 ASSERT(!m_visualUpdatesSuppressionTimer.isActive());
1409 ASSERT(m_visualUpdatesAllowed);
1410 setVisualUpdatesAllowed(false);
1411 break;
1412 case Interactive:
1413 ASSERT(m_visualUpdatesSuppressionTimer.isActive() || m_visualUpdatesAllowed);
1414 break;
1415 case Complete:
1416 if (m_visualUpdatesSuppressionTimer.isActive()) {
1417 ASSERT(!m_visualUpdatesAllowed);
1418
1419 if (view() && !view()->visualUpdatesAllowedByClient())
1420 return;
1421
1422 setVisualUpdatesAllowed(true);
1423 } else
1424 ASSERT(m_visualUpdatesAllowed);
1425 break;
1426 }
1427}
1428
1429void Document::setVisualUpdatesAllowed(bool visualUpdatesAllowed)
1430{
1431 if (m_visualUpdatesAllowed == visualUpdatesAllowed)
1432 return;
1433
1434 m_visualUpdatesAllowed = visualUpdatesAllowed;
1435
1436 if (visualUpdatesAllowed)
1437 m_visualUpdatesSuppressionTimer.stop();
1438 else
1439 m_visualUpdatesSuppressionTimer.startOneShot(1_s * settings().incrementalRenderingSuppressionTimeoutInSeconds());
1440
1441 if (!visualUpdatesAllowed)
1442 return;
1443
1444 RefPtr<FrameView> frameView = view();
1445 bool needsLayout = frameView && renderView() && (frameView->layoutContext().isLayoutPending() || renderView()->needsLayout());
1446 if (needsLayout)
1447 updateLayout();
1448
1449 if (Page* page = this->page()) {
1450 if (frame()->isMainFrame()) {
1451 frameView->addPaintPendingMilestones(DidFirstPaintAfterSuppressedIncrementalRendering);
1452 if (page->requestedLayoutMilestones() & DidFirstLayoutAfterSuppressedIncrementalRendering)
1453 frame()->loader().didReachLayoutMilestone(DidFirstLayoutAfterSuppressedIncrementalRendering);
1454 }
1455 }
1456
1457 if (frameView)
1458 frameView->updateCompositingLayersAfterLayout();
1459
1460 if (RenderView* renderView = this->renderView())
1461 renderView->repaintViewAndCompositedLayers();
1462
1463 if (Frame* frame = this->frame())
1464 frame->loader().completePageTransitionIfNeeded();
1465}
1466
1467void Document::visualUpdatesSuppressionTimerFired()
1468{
1469 ASSERT(!m_visualUpdatesAllowed);
1470
1471 // If the client is extending the visual update suppression period explicitly, the
1472 // watchdog should not re-enable visual updates itself, but should wait for the client.
1473 if (view() && !view()->visualUpdatesAllowedByClient())
1474 return;
1475
1476 setVisualUpdatesAllowed(true);
1477}
1478
1479void Document::setVisualUpdatesAllowedByClient(bool visualUpdatesAllowedByClient)
1480{
1481 // We should only re-enable visual updates if ReadyState is Completed or the watchdog timer has fired,
1482 // both of which we can determine by looking at the timer.
1483
1484 if (visualUpdatesAllowedByClient && !m_visualUpdatesSuppressionTimer.isActive() && !visualUpdatesAllowed())
1485 setVisualUpdatesAllowed(true);
1486}

1541void Document::setContent(const String& content)
1542{

1545 // not implemented for the XML parser as it's normally synonymous with
1546 // document.write(). append() will end up yielding, but close() will
1547 // pump the tokenizer syncrhonously and finish the parse.

1550}

1552String Document::suggestedMIMEType() const
1553{
1554 if (isXHTMLDocument())
1555 return "application/xhtml+xml"_s;
1556 if (isSVGDocument())
1557 return "image/svg+xml"_s;
1558 if (xmlStandalone())
1559 return "text/xml"_s;
1560 if (isHTMLDocument())
1561 return "text/html"_s;
1562 if (DocumentLoader* loader = this->loader())
1563 return loader->responseMIMEType();
1564 return String();
1565}

1572String Document::contentType() const
1573{

1575 return m_overriddenMIMEType;
1576
1577 if (DocumentLoader* documentLoader = loader())
1578 return documentLoader->currentContentType();
1579
1580 String mimeType = suggestedMIMEType();
1581 if (!mimeType.isNull())
1582 return mimeType;
1583
1584 return "application/xml"_s;
1585}
1586
1587RefPtr<Range> Document::caretRangeFromPoint(int x, int y)
1588{
1589 auto boundary = caretPositionFromPoint(LayoutPoint(x, y));
1590 if (!boundary)
1591 return nullptr;
1592 return createLiveRange({ *boundary, *boundary });
1593}
1594
1595std::optional<BoundaryPoint> Document::caretPositionFromPoint(const LayoutPoint& clientPoint)
1596{
1597 if (!hasLivingRenderTree())
1598 return std::nullopt;
1599
1600 LayoutPoint localPoint;
1601 auto node = nodeFromPoint(clientPoint, &localPoint);
1602 if (!node)
1603 return std::nullopt;
1604
1605 auto* renderer = node->renderer();
1606 if (!renderer)
1607 return std::nullopt;
1608 auto rangeCompliantPosition = renderer->positionForPoint(localPoint).parentAnchoredEquivalent();
1609 if (rangeCompliantPosition.isNull())
1610 return std::nullopt;
1611
1612 unsigned offset = rangeCompliantPosition.offsetInContainerNode();
1613 node = retargetToScope(*rangeCompliantPosition.containerNode());
1614 if (node != rangeCompliantPosition.containerNode())
1615 offset = 0;
1616
1617 return { { *node, offset } };
1618}
1619
1620bool Document::isBodyPotentiallyScrollable(HTMLBodyElement& body)
1621{
1622 // See https://www.w3.org/TR/cssom-view-1/#potentially-scrollable.
1623 // An element is potentially scrollable if all of the following conditions are true:
1624 // - The element has an associated CSS layout box.
1625 // - The element is not the HTML body element, or it is and the root element's used value of the
1626 // overflow-x or overflow-y properties is not visible.
1627 // - The element's used value of the overflow-x or overflow-y properties is not visible.
1628 //
1629 // FIXME: We should use RenderObject::hasOverflowClip() instead of Element::computedStyle() but
1630 // the used values are currently not correctly updated. See https://webkit.org/b/182292.
1631 return body.renderer()
1632 && documentElement()->computedStyle()
1633 && !documentElement()->computedStyle()->isOverflowVisible()
1634 && body.computedStyle()
1635 && !body.computedStyle()->isOverflowVisible();
1636}
1637
1638Element* Document::scrollingElementForAPI()
1639{
1640 if (inQuirksMode() && settings().CSSOMViewScrollingAPIEnabled())
1641 updateLayoutIgnorePendingStylesheets();
1642 return scrollingElement();
1643}
1644
1645Element* Document::scrollingElement()
1646{
1647 if (settings().CSSOMViewScrollingAPIEnabled()) {
1648 // See https://drafts.csswg.org/cssom-view/#dom-document-scrollingelement.
1649 // The scrollingElement attribute, on getting, must run these steps:
1650 // 1. If the Document is in quirks mode, follow these substeps:
1651 if (inQuirksMode()) {
1652 auto* firstBody = body();
1653 // 1. If the HTML body element exists, and it is not potentially scrollable, return the
1654 // HTML body element and abort these steps.
1655 if (firstBody && !isBodyPotentiallyScrollable(*firstBody))
1656 return firstBody;
1657
1658 // 2. Return null and abort these steps.
1659 return nullptr;
1660 }
1661
1662 // 2. If there is a root element, return the root element and abort these steps.
1663 // 3. Return null.
1664 return documentElement();
1665 }
1666
1667 return body();
1668}
1669
1670static String canonicalizedTitle(Document& document, const String& title)
1671{
1672 // Collapse runs of HTML spaces into single space characters.
1673 // Strip leading and trailing spaces.
1674 // Replace backslashes with currency symbols.
1675
1676 StringBuilder builder;
1677
1678 auto* decoder = document.decoder();
1679 auto backslashAsCurrencySymbol = decoder ? decoder->encoding().backslashAsCurrencySymbol() : '\\';
1680
1681 bool previousCharacterWasHTMLSpace = false;
1682 for (auto character : StringView { title }.codeUnits()) {
1683 if (isHTMLSpace(character))
1684 previousCharacterWasHTMLSpace = true;
1685 else {
1686 if (character == '\\')
1687 character = backslashAsCurrencySymbol;
1688 if (previousCharacterWasHTMLSpace && !builder.isEmpty())
1689 builder.append(' ');
1690 builder.append(character);
1691 previousCharacterWasHTMLSpace = false;
1692 }
1693 }
1694
1695 return builder == title ? title : builder.toString();
1696}
1697
1698void Document::updateTitle(const StringWithDirection& title)
1699{
1700 if (m_rawTitle == title)
1701 return;
1702
1703 m_rawTitle = title;
1704
1705 m_title.string = canonicalizedTitle(*this, title.string);
1706 m_title.direction = title.direction;
1707
1708 if (!m_updateTitleTaskScheduled) {
1709 eventLoop().queueTask(TaskSource::DOMManipulation, [protectedThis = makeRef(*this), this]() mutable {
1710 m_updateTitleTaskScheduled = false;
1711 if (auto documentLoader = makeRefPtr(loader()))
1712 documentLoader->setTitle(m_title);
1713 });
1714 m_updateTitleTaskScheduled = true;
1715 }
1716}
1717
1718void Document::updateTitleFromTitleElement()
1719{
1720 if (!m_titleElement) {
1721 updateTitle({ });
1722 return;
1723 }
1724
1725 if (is<HTMLTitleElement>(*m_titleElement))
1726 updateTitle(downcast<HTMLTitleElement>(*m_titleElement).textWithDirection());
1727 else if (is<SVGTitleElement>(*m_titleElement)) {
1728 // FIXME: Does the SVG title element have a text direction?
1729 updateTitle({ downcast<SVGTitleElement>(*m_titleElement).textContent(), TextDirection::LTR });
1730 }
1731}
1732
1733void Document::setTitle(const String& title)
1734{
1735 auto* element = documentElement();
1736 if (is<SVGSVGElement>(element)) {
1737 if (!m_titleElement) {
1738 m_titleElement = SVGTitleElement::create(SVGNames::titleTag, *this);
1739 element->insertBefore(*m_titleElement, element->firstChild());
1740 }
1741 // insertBefore above may have ran scripts which removed m_titleElement.
1742 if (m_titleElement)
1743 m_titleElement->setTextContent(title);
1744 } else if (is<HTMLElement>(element)) {
1745 if (!m_titleElement) {
1746 auto* headElement = head();
1747 if (!headElement)
1748 return;
1749 m_titleElement = HTMLTitleElement::create(HTMLNames::titleTag, *this);
1750 headElement->appendChild(*m_titleElement);
1751 }
1752 // appendChild above may have ran scripts which removed m_titleElement.
1753 if (m_titleElement)
1754 m_titleElement->setTextContent(title);
1755 }
1756}
1757
1758template<typename> struct TitleTraits;
1759
1760template<> struct TitleTraits<HTMLTitleElement> {
1761 static bool isInEligibleLocation(HTMLTitleElement& element) { return element.isConnected() && !element.isInShadowTree(); }
1762 static HTMLTitleElement* findTitleElement(Document& document) { return descendantsOfType<HTMLTitleElement>(document).first(); }
1763};
1764
1765template<> struct TitleTraits<SVGTitleElement> {
1766 static bool isInEligibleLocation(SVGTitleElement& element) { return element.parentNode() == element.document().documentElement(); }
1767 static SVGTitleElement* findTitleElement(Document& document) { return childrenOfType<SVGTitleElement>(*document.documentElement()).first(); }
1768};
1769
1770template<typename TitleElement> Element* selectNewTitleElement(Document& document, Element* oldTitleElement, Element& changingTitleElement)
1771{
1772 using Traits = TitleTraits<TitleElement>;
1773
1774 if (!is<TitleElement>(changingTitleElement)) {
1775 ASSERT(oldTitleElement == Traits::findTitleElement(document));
1776 return oldTitleElement;
1777 }
1778
1779 if (oldTitleElement)
1780 return Traits::findTitleElement(document);
1781
1782 // Optimized common case: We have no title element yet.
1783 // We can figure out which title element should be used without searching.
1784 bool isEligible = Traits::isInEligibleLocation(downcast<TitleElement>(changingTitleElement));
1785 auto* newTitleElement = isEligible ? &changingTitleElement : nullptr;
1786 ASSERT(newTitleElement == Traits::findTitleElement(document));
1787 return newTitleElement;
1788}
1789
1790void Document::updateTitleElement(Element& changingTitleElement)
1791{
1792 // Most documents use HTML title rules.
1793 // Documents with SVG document elements use SVG title rules.
1794 auto selectTitleElement = is<SVGSVGElement>(documentElement())
1795 ? selectNewTitleElement<SVGTitleElement> : selectNewTitleElement<HTMLTitleElement>;
1796 auto newTitleElement = selectTitleElement(*this, m_titleElement.get(), changingTitleElement);
1797 if (m_titleElement == newTitleElement)
1798 return;
1799 m_titleElement = newTitleElement;
1800 updateTitleFromTitleElement();
1801}
1802
1803void Document::titleElementAdded(Element& titleElement)
1804{
1805 if (m_titleElement == &titleElement)
1806 return;
1807
1808 updateTitleElement(titleElement);
1809}
1810
1811void Document::titleElementRemoved(Element& titleElement)
1812{
1813 if (m_titleElement != &titleElement)
1814 return;
1815
1816 updateTitleElement(titleElement);
1817}
1818
1819void Document::titleElementTextChanged(Element& titleElement)
1820{
1821 if (m_titleElement != &titleElement)
1822 return;
1823
1824 updateTitleFromTitleElement();
1825}

1836
1837void Document::visibilityStateChanged()
1838{
1839 // https://w3c.github.io/page-visibility/#reacting-to-visibilitychange-changes
1840 queueTaskToDispatchEvent(TaskSource::UserInteraction, Event::create(eventNames().visibilitychangeEvent, Event::CanBubble::Yes, Event::IsCancelable::No));
1841 for (auto& client : m_visibilityStateCallbackClients)
1842 client.visibilityStateChanged();
1843
1844#if ENABLE(MEDIA_STREAM) && PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
1845 if (auto mediaSessionManager = PlatformMediaSessionManager::sharedManagerIfExists()) {
1846 if (!mediaSessionManager->isInterrupted())
1847 MediaStreamTrack::updateCaptureAccordingToMutedState(*this);
1848 }
1849#endif
1850}
1851
1852VisibilityState Document::visibilityState() const
1853{
1854 // The visibility of the document is inherited from the visibility of the
1855 // page. If there is no page associated with the document, we will assume
1856 // that the page is hidden, as specified by the spec:
1857 // https://w3c.github.io/page-visibility/#visibilitystate-attribute
1858 if (!m_frame || !m_frame->page() || m_visibilityHiddenDueToDismissal)
1859 return VisibilityState::Hidden;
1860 return m_frame->page()->visibilityState();
1861}
1862
1863bool Document::hidden() const
1864{
1865 return visibilityState() != VisibilityState::Visible;
1866}

1946void Document::scheduleFullStyleRebuild()
1947{
1948 m_needsFullStyleRebuild = true;
1949 scheduleStyleRecalc();
1950}
1951
1952void Document::scheduleStyleRecalc()
1953{
1954 ASSERT(!m_renderView || !inHitTesting());
1955
1956 if (m_styleRecalcTimer.isActive() || backForwardCacheState() != NotInBackForwardCache)
1957 return;
1958
1959 ASSERT(childNeedsStyleRecalc() || m_needsFullStyleRebuild);
1960
1961 m_styleRecalcTimer.startOneShot(0_s);
1962
1963 InspectorInstrumentation::didScheduleStyleRecalculation(*this);
1964}
1965
1966void Document::unscheduleStyleRecalc()
1967{
1968 ASSERT(!childNeedsStyleRecalc());
1969
1970 m_styleRecalcTimer.stop();
1971 m_needsFullStyleRebuild = false;
1972}
1973
1974bool Document::hasPendingStyleRecalc() const
1975{
1976 return needsStyleRecalc() && !m_inStyleRecalc;
1977}
1978
1979bool Document::hasPendingFullStyleRebuild() const
1980{
1981 return hasPendingStyleRecalc() && m_needsFullStyleRebuild;
1982}
1983
1984void Document::updateRenderTree(std::unique_ptr<const Style::Update> styleUpdate)
1985{
1986 ASSERT(!inRenderTreeUpdate());
1987
1988 Style::PostResolutionCallbackDisabler callbackDisabler(*this);
1989 {
1990 SetForScope<bool> inRenderTreeUpdate(m_inRenderTreeUpdate, true);
1991 {
1992 RenderTreeUpdater updater(*this, callbackDisabler);
1993 updater.commit(WTFMove(styleUpdate));
1994 }
1995 }
1996}
1997
1998void Document::resolveStyle(ResolveStyleType type)
1999{
2000 ASSERT(!view() || !view()->isPainting());
2001
2002 // NOTE: XSL code seems to be the only client stumbling in here without a RenderView.
2003 if (!m_renderView)
2004 return;
2005
2006 FrameView& frameView = m_renderView->frameView();
2007 Ref<FrameView> protect(frameView);
2008 if (frameView.isPainting())
2009 return;
2010
2011 if (m_inStyleRecalc)
2012 return; // Guard against re-entrancy. -dwh
2013
2014 TraceScope tracingScope(StyleRecalcStart, StyleRecalcEnd);
2015
2016 RenderView::RepaintRegionAccumulator repaintRegionAccumulator(renderView());
2017
2018 // FIXME: Do this update per tree scope.
2019 if (auto* extensions = m_svgExtensions.get()) {
2020 auto elements = copyToVectorOf<Ref<SVGUseElement>>(extensions->useElementsWithPendingShadowTreeUpdate());
2021 // We can't clear m_svgUseElements here because updateShadowTree may end up executing arbitrary scripts
2022 // which may insert new SVG use elements or remove existing ones inside sync IPC via ImageLoader::updateFromElement.
2023 for (auto& element : elements)
2024 element->updateShadowTree();
2025 }
2026
2027 // FIXME: We should update style on our ancestor chain before proceeding, however doing so at
2028 // the time this comment was originally written caused several tests to crash.
2029
2030 {
2031 ScriptDisallowedScope::InMainThread scriptDisallowedScope;
2032 styleScope().flushPendingUpdate();
2033 frameView.willRecalcStyle();
2034 }
2035
2036 InspectorInstrumentation::willRecalculateStyle(*this);
2037
2038 bool updatedCompositingLayers = false;
2039 {
2040 Style::PostResolutionCallbackDisabler disabler(*this);
2041 WidgetHierarchyUpdatesSuspensionScope suspendWidgetHierarchyUpdates;
2042 ScriptDisallowedScope::InMainThread scriptDisallowedScope;
2043
2044 m_inStyleRecalc = true;
2045
2046 if (m_needsFullStyleRebuild)
2047 type = ResolveStyleType::Rebuild;
2048
2049 if (type == ResolveStyleType::Rebuild) {
2050 // This may get set again during style resolve.
2051 m_hasNodesWithNonFinalStyle = false;
2052 m_hasNodesWithMissingStyle = false;
2053
2054 auto documentStyle = Style::resolveForDocument(*this);
2055
2056 // Inserting the pictograph font at the end of the font fallback list is done by the
2057 // font selector, so set a font selector if needed.
2058 if (settings().fontFallbackPrefersPictographs())
2059 documentStyle.fontCascade().update(&fontSelector());
2060
2061 auto documentChange = Style::determineChange(documentStyle, m_renderView->style());
2062 if (documentChange != Style::Change::None)
2063 renderView()->setStyle(WTFMove(documentStyle));
2064
2065 if (auto* documentElement = this->documentElement())
2066 documentElement->invalidateStyleForSubtree();
2067 }
2068
2069 Style::TreeResolver resolver(*this, WTFMove(m_pendingRenderTreeTextUpdate));
2070 auto styleUpdate = resolver.resolve();
2071
2072 m_lastStyleUpdateSizeForTesting = styleUpdate ? styleUpdate->size() : 0;
2073
2074 setHasValidStyle();
2075 clearChildNeedsStyleRecalc();
2076 unscheduleStyleRecalc();
2077
2078 m_inStyleRecalc = false;
2079
2080 m_fontLoader->loadPendingFonts();
2081
2082 if (styleUpdate) {
2083 updateRenderTree(WTFMove(styleUpdate));
2084 frameView.styleAndRenderTreeDidChange();
2085 }
2086
2087 updatedCompositingLayers = frameView.updateCompositingLayersAfterStyleChange();
2088
2089 if (m_renderView->needsLayout())
2090 frameView.layoutContext().scheduleLayout();
2091
2092 // Usually this is handled by post-layout.
2093 if (!frameView.needsLayout())
2094 frameView.frame().selection().scheduleAppearanceUpdateAfterStyleChange();
2095
2096 // As a result of the style recalculation, the currently hovered element might have been
2097 // detached (for example, by setting display:none in the :hover style), schedule another mouseMove event
2098 // to check if any other elements ended up under the mouse pointer due to re-layout.
2099 if (m_hoveredElement && !m_hoveredElement->renderer())
2100 frameView.frame().mainFrame().eventHandler().dispatchFakeMouseMoveEventSoon();
2101
2102 ++m_styleRecalcCount;
2103 // FIXME: Assert ASSERT(!needsStyleRecalc()) here. Do we still have some cases where it's not true?
2104 }
2105
2106 InspectorInstrumentation::didRecalculateStyle(*this);
2107
2108 // Some animated images may now be inside the viewport due to style recalc,
2109 // resume them if necessary if there is no layout pending. Otherwise, we'll
2110 // check if they need to be resumed after layout.
2111 if (updatedCompositingLayers && !frameView.needsLayout())
2112 frameView.viewportContentsChanged();
2113}
2114
2115void Document::updateTextRenderer(Text& text, unsigned offsetOfReplacedText, unsigned lengthOfReplacedText)
2116{
2117 if (!m_pendingRenderTreeTextUpdate)
2118 m_pendingRenderTreeTextUpdate = makeUnique<Style::Update>(*this);
2119
2120 m_pendingRenderTreeTextUpdate->addText(text, { offsetOfReplacedText, lengthOfReplacedText, std::nullopt });
2121
2122 scheduleRenderingUpdate({ });
2123}
2124
2125bool Document::needsStyleRecalc() const
2126{
2127 if (backForwardCacheState() != NotInBackForwardCache)
2128 return false;
2129
2130 if (m_needsFullStyleRebuild)
2131 return true;
2132
2133 if (childNeedsStyleRecalc())
2134 return true;
2135
2136 if (m_pendingRenderTreeTextUpdate)
2137 return true;
2138
2139 if (styleScope().hasPendingUpdate())
2140 return true;
2141
2142 return false;
2143}
2144
2145static bool isSafeToUpdateStyleOrLayout(const Document& document)
2146{
2147 bool isSafeToExecuteScript = ScriptDisallowedScope::InMainThread::isScriptAllowed();
2148 auto* frameView = document.view();
2149 bool isInFrameFlattening = frameView && frameView->isInChildFrameWithFrameFlattening();
2150 return isSafeToExecuteScript || isInFrameFlattening || !isInWebProcess();
2151}
2152
2153bool Document::updateStyleIfNeeded()
2154{
2155 RefPtr<FrameView> frameView = view();
2156 {
2157 ScriptDisallowedScope::InMainThread scriptDisallowedScope;
2158 ASSERT(isMainThread());
2159 ASSERT(!frameView || !frameView->isPainting());
2160
2161 if (!frameView || frameView->layoutContext().isInRenderTreeLayout())
2162 return false;
2163
2164 styleScope().flushPendingUpdate();
2165
2166 if (!needsStyleRecalc())
2167 return false;
2168 }
2169
2170#if PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
2171 ContentChangeObserver::StyleRecalcScope observingScope(*this);
2172#endif
2173 // The early exit above for !needsStyleRecalc() is needed when updateWidgetPositions() is called in runOrScheduleAsynchronousTasks().
2174 RELEASE_ASSERT_WITH_SECURITY_IMPLICATION(isSafeToUpdateStyleOrLayout(*this));
2175 resolveStyle();
2176 return true;
2177}
2178
2179void Document::updateLayout()
2180{
2181 ASSERT(isMainThread());
2182
2183 RefPtr<FrameView> frameView = view();
2184 if (frameView && frameView->layoutContext().isInRenderTreeLayout()) {
2185 // View layout should not be re-entrant.
2186 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
2187 return;
2188 }
2189 RELEASE_ASSERT_WITH_SECURITY_IMPLICATION(isSafeToUpdateStyleOrLayout(*this));
2190
2191 RenderView::RepaintRegionAccumulator repaintRegionAccumulator(renderView());
2192
2193 if (HTMLFrameOwnerElement* owner = ownerElement())
2194 owner->document().updateLayout();
2195
2196 updateStyleIfNeeded();
2197
2198 StackStats::LayoutCheckPoint layoutCheckPoint;
2199
2200 // Only do a layout if changes have occurred that make it necessary.
2201 if (frameView && renderView() && (frameView->layoutContext().isLayoutPending() || renderView()->needsLayout()))
2202 frameView->layoutContext().layout();
2203}
2204
2205void Document::updateLayoutIgnorePendingStylesheets(Document::RunPostLayoutTasks runPostLayoutTasks)
2206{
2207 bool oldIgnore = m_ignorePendingStylesheets;
2208
2209 if (!haveStylesheetsLoaded()) {
2210 m_ignorePendingStylesheets = true;
2211 // FIXME: This should just invalidate elements with missing styles.
2212 if (m_hasNodesWithMissingStyle)
2213 scheduleFullStyleRebuild();
2214 }
2215
2216 updateLayout();
2217
2218 if (runPostLayoutTasks == RunPostLayoutTasks::Synchronously && view())
2219 view()->flushAnyPendingPostLayoutTasks();
2220
2221 m_ignorePendingStylesheets = oldIgnore;
2222}
2223
2224std::unique_ptr<RenderStyle> Document::styleForElementIgnoringPendingStylesheets(Element& element, const RenderStyle* parentStyle, PseudoId pseudoElementSpecifier)
2225{
2226 ASSERT(&element.document() == this);
2227 ASSERT(!element.isPseudoElement() || pseudoElementSpecifier == PseudoId::None);
2228 ASSERT(pseudoElementSpecifier == PseudoId::None || parentStyle);
2229 ASSERT(Style::postResolutionCallbacksAreSuspended());
2230
2231 SetForScope<bool> change(m_ignorePendingStylesheets, true);
2232 auto& resolver = element.styleResolver();
2233
2234 if (pseudoElementSpecifier != PseudoId::None)
2235 return resolver.pseudoStyleForElement(element, { pseudoElementSpecifier }, *parentStyle);
2236
2237 auto elementStyle = resolver.styleForElement(element, parentStyle);
2238 if (elementStyle.relations) {
2239 Style::Update emptyUpdate(*this);
2240 Style::commitRelations(WTFMove(elementStyle.relations), emptyUpdate);
2241 }
2242
2243 return WTFMove(elementStyle.renderStyle);
2244}
2245
2246bool Document::updateLayoutIfDimensionsOutOfDate(Element& element, DimensionsCheck dimensionsCheck)
2247{
2248 ASSERT(isMainThread());
2249
2250 // If the stylesheets haven't loaded, just give up and do a full layout ignoring pending stylesheets.
2251 if (!haveStylesheetsLoaded()) {
2252 updateLayoutIgnorePendingStylesheets();
2253 return true;
2254 }
2255
2256 // Check for re-entrancy and assert (same code that is in updateLayout()).
2257 RefPtr<FrameView> frameView = view();
2258 if (frameView && frameView->layoutContext().isInRenderTreeLayout()) {
2259 // View layout should not be re-entrant.
2260 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
2261 return true;
2262 }
2263
2264 RenderView::RepaintRegionAccumulator repaintRegionAccumulator(renderView());
2265
2266 // Mimic the structure of updateLayout(), but at each step, see if we have been forced into doing a full
2267 // layout.
2268 bool requireFullLayout = false;
2269 if (HTMLFrameOwnerElement* owner = ownerElement()) {
2270 if (owner->document().updateLayoutIfDimensionsOutOfDate(*owner))
2271 requireFullLayout = true;
2272 }
2273
2274 updateStyleIfNeeded();
2275
2276 RenderObject* renderer = element.renderer();
2277 if (!renderer || renderer->needsLayout()) {
2278 // If we don't have a renderer or if the renderer needs layout for any reason, give up.
2279 requireFullLayout = true;
2280 }
2281
2282 // Turn off this optimization for input elements with shadow content.
2283 if (is<HTMLInputElement>(element))
2284 requireFullLayout = true;
2285
2286 bool isVertical = renderer && !renderer->isHorizontalWritingMode();
2287 bool checkingLogicalWidth = ((dimensionsCheck & WidthDimensionsCheck) && !isVertical) || ((dimensionsCheck & HeightDimensionsCheck) && isVertical);
2288 bool checkingLogicalHeight = ((dimensionsCheck & HeightDimensionsCheck) && !isVertical) || ((dimensionsCheck & WidthDimensionsCheck) && isVertical);
2289 bool hasSpecifiedLogicalHeight = renderer && renderer->style().logicalMinHeight() == Length(0, LengthType::Fixed) && renderer->style().logicalHeight().isFixed() && renderer->style().logicalMaxHeight().isAuto();
2290
2291 if (!requireFullLayout) {
2292 RenderBox* previousBox = nullptr;
2293 RenderBox* currentBox = nullptr;
2294
2295 // Check our containing block chain. If anything in the chain needs a layout, then require a full layout.
2296 for (RenderObject* currRenderer = element.renderer(); currRenderer && !currRenderer->isRenderView(); currRenderer = currRenderer->container()) {
2297
2298 // Require the entire container chain to be boxes.
2299 if (!is<RenderBox>(currRenderer)) {
2300 requireFullLayout = true;
2301 break;
2302 }
2303
2304 previousBox = currentBox;
2305 currentBox = downcast<RenderBox>(currRenderer);
2306
2307 // If a box needs layout for itself or if a box has changed children and sizes its width to
2308 // its content, then require a full layout.
2309 if (currentBox->selfNeedsLayout() ||
2310 (checkingLogicalWidth && currRenderer->needsLayout() && currentBox->sizesLogicalWidthToFitContent(MainOrPreferredSize))) {
2311 requireFullLayout = true;
2312 break;
2313 }
2314
2315 // If a block contains floats and the child's height isn't specified, then
2316 // give up also, since our height could end up being influenced by the floats.
2317 if (checkingLogicalHeight && !hasSpecifiedLogicalHeight && currentBox->isRenderBlockFlow()) {
2318 RenderBlockFlow* currentBlockFlow = downcast<RenderBlockFlow>(currentBox);
2319 if (currentBlockFlow->containsFloats() && previousBox && !previousBox->isFloatingOrOutOfFlowPositioned()) {
2320 requireFullLayout = true;
2321 break;
2322 }
2323 }
2324
2325 if (!currentBox->isRenderBlockFlow() || currentBox->enclosingFragmentedFlow() || currentBox->isWritingModeRoot()) {
2326 // FIXME: For now require only block flows all the way back to the root. This limits the optimization
2327 // for now, and we'll expand it in future patches to apply to more and more scenarios.
2328 // Disallow columns from having the optimization.
2329 // Give up if the writing mode changes at all in the containing block chain.
2330 requireFullLayout = true;
2331 break;
2332 }
2333
2334 if (currRenderer == frameView->layoutContext().subtreeLayoutRoot())
2335 break;
2336 }
2337 }
2338
2339 StackStats::LayoutCheckPoint layoutCheckPoint;
2340
2341 // Only do a layout if changes have occurred that make it necessary.
2342 if (requireFullLayout && frameView && renderView() && (frameView->layoutContext().isLayoutPending() || renderView()->needsLayout()))
2343 frameView->layoutContext().layout();
2344
2345 return requireFullLayout;
2346}
2347
2348bool Document::isPageBoxVisible(int pageIndex)
2349{
2350 updateStyleIfNeeded();
2351 std::unique_ptr<RenderStyle> pageStyle(styleScope().resolver().styleForPage(pageIndex));
2352 return pageStyle->visibility() != Visibility::Hidden; // display property doesn't apply to @page.
2353}
2354
2355void Document::pageSizeAndMarginsInPixels(int pageIndex, IntSize& pageSize, int& marginTop, int& marginRight, int& marginBottom, int& marginLeft)
2356{
2357 updateStyleIfNeeded();
2358 auto style = styleScope().resolver().styleForPage(pageIndex);
2359
2360 int width = pageSize.width();
2361 int height = pageSize.height();
2362 switch (style->pageSizeType()) {
2363 case PAGE_SIZE_AUTO:
2364 break;
2365 case PAGE_SIZE_AUTO_LANDSCAPE:
2366 if (width < height)
2367 std::swap(width, height);
2368 break;
2369 case PAGE_SIZE_AUTO_PORTRAIT:
2370 if (width > height)
2371 std::swap(width, height);
2372 break;
2373 case PAGE_SIZE_RESOLVED: {
2374 auto& size = style->pageSize();
2375 ASSERT(size.width.isFixed());
2376 ASSERT(size.height.isFixed());
2377 width = valueForLength(size.width, 0);
2378 height = valueForLength(size.height, 0);
2379 break;
2380 }
2381 default:
2382 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
2383 }
2384 pageSize = IntSize(width, height);
2385
2386 // The percentage is calculated with respect to the width even for margin top and bottom.
2387 // http://www.w3.org/TR/CSS2/box.html#margin-properties
2388 marginTop = style->marginTop().isAuto() ? marginTop : intValueForLength(style->marginTop(), width);
2389 marginRight = style->marginRight().isAuto() ? marginRight : intValueForLength(style->marginRight(), width);
2390 marginBottom = style->marginBottom().isAuto() ? marginBottom : intValueForLength(style->marginBottom(), width);
2391 marginLeft = style->marginLeft().isAuto() ? marginLeft : intValueForLength(style->marginLeft(), width);
2392}

2414void Document::createRenderTree()
2415{
2416 ASSERT(!renderView());
2417 ASSERT(m_backForwardCacheState != InBackForwardCache);
2418 ASSERT(!m_axObjectCache || this != &topDocument());
2419
2420 if (m_isNonRenderedPlaceholder)
2421 return;
2422
2423 // FIXME: It would be better if we could pass the resolved document style directly here.
2424 m_renderView = createRenderer<RenderView>(*this, RenderStyle::create());
2425 Node::setRenderer(m_renderView.get());
2426
2427 renderView()->setIsInWindow(true);
2428
2429 resolveStyle(ResolveStyleType::Rebuild);
2430}
2431
2432void Document::didBecomeCurrentDocumentInFrame()
2433{
2434 m_frame->script().updateDocument();
2435
2436 // Many of these functions have event handlers which can detach the frame synchronously, so we must check repeatedly in this function.
2437 if (!m_frame)
2438 return;
2439
2440 if (!hasLivingRenderTree())
2441 createRenderTree();
2442 if (!m_frame)
2443 return;
2444
2445 dispatchDisabledAdaptationsDidChangeForMainFrame();
2446 if (!m_frame)
2447 return;
2448
2449 updateViewportArguments();
2450 if (!m_frame)
2451 return;
2452
2453 // FIXME: Doing this only for the main frame is insufficient.
2454 // Changing a subframe can also change the wheel event handler count.
2455 // FIXME: Doing this only when a document goes into the frame is insufficient.
2456 // Removing a document can also change the wheel event handler count.
2457 // FIXME: Doing this every time is a waste. If the current document and its
2458 // subframes' documents have no wheel event handlers, then the count did not change,
2459 // unless the documents they are replacing had wheel event handlers.
2460 if (page() && m_frame->isMainFrame())
2461 wheelEventHandlersChanged();
2462 if (!m_frame)
2463 return;
2464
2465 // Ensure that the scheduled task state of the document matches the DOM suspension state of the frame. It can
2466 // be out of sync if the DOM suspension state changed while the document was not in the frame (possibly in the
2467 // back/forward cache, or simply newly created).
2468 if (m_frame->activeDOMObjectsAndAnimationsSuspended()) {
2469 if (m_timelinesController)
2470 m_timelinesController->suspendAnimations();
2471 suspendScheduledTasks(ReasonForSuspension::PageWillBeSuspended);
2472 } else {
2473 resumeScheduledTasks(ReasonForSuspension::PageWillBeSuspended);
2474 if (m_timelinesController)
2475 m_timelinesController->resumeAnimations();
2476 }
2477}

2482 RELEASE_ASSERT(!m_frame);
2483
2484 if (auto* window = domWindow())
2485 window->frameDestroyed();
2486
2487 FrameDestructionObserver::frameDestroyed();
2488}

2492 FrameDestructionObserver::willDetachPage();
2493#if PLATFORM(IOS_FAMILY)
2494 contentChangeObserver().willDetachPage();
2495#endif
2496 if (domWindow() && frame())
2497 InspectorInstrumentation::frameWindowDiscarded(*frame(), domWindow());
2498}

2512 ASSERT(m_frame == &cachedFrame.view()->frame());
2513 ASSERT(m_backForwardCacheState == Document::InBackForwardCache);

2515}
2516
2517void Document::destroyRenderTree()
2518{
2519 ASSERT(hasLivingRenderTree());
2520 ASSERT(frame());
2521 ASSERT(frame()->document() == this);
2522 ASSERT(page());
2523
2524 // Prevent Widget tree changes from committing until the RenderView is dead and gone.
2525 WidgetHierarchyUpdatesSuspensionScope suspendWidgetHierarchyUpdates;
2526
2527 SetForScope<bool> change(m_renderTreeBeingDestroyed, true);
2528
2529 if (this == &topDocument())
2530 clearAXObjectCache();
2531
2532 documentWillBecomeInactive();
2533
2534 if (view())
2535 view()->willDestroyRenderTree();
2536
2537 if (m_documentElement)
2538 RenderTreeUpdater::tearDownRenderers(*m_documentElement);
2539
2540 clearChildNeedsStyleRecalc();
2541
2542 unscheduleStyleRecalc();
2543
2544 // FIXME: RenderObject::view() uses m_renderView and we can't null it before destruction is completed
2545 {
2546 RenderTreeBuilder builder(*m_renderView);
2547 // FIXME: This is a workaround for leftover content (see webkit.org/b/182547).
2548 while (m_renderView->firstChild())
2549 builder.destroy(*m_renderView->firstChild());
2550 m_renderView->destroy();
2551 }
2552 m_renderView.release();
2553
2554 Node::setRenderer(nullptr);
2555
2556#if ENABLE(TEXT_AUTOSIZING)
2557 m_textAutoSizing = nullptr;
2558#endif
2559
2560 if (view())
2561 view()->didDestroyRenderTree();
2562}
2563
2564void Document::willBeRemovedFromFrame()
2565{
2566 if (m_hasPreparedForDestruction)
2567 return;
2568
2569#if USE(LIBWEBRTC)
2570 // FIXME: This should be moved to Modules/mediastream.
2571 if (LibWebRTCProvider::webRTCAvailable()) {
2572 if (auto* page = this->page())
2573 page->libWebRTCProvider().unregisterMDNSNames(identifier());
2574 }
2575#endif
2576
2577#if ENABLE(SERVICE_WORKER)
2578 setActiveServiceWorker(nullptr);
2579 setServiceWorkerConnection(nullptr);
2580#endif
2581
2582#if ENABLE(IOS_TOUCH_EVENTS)
2583 clearTouchEventHandlersAndListeners();
2584#endif
2585
2586 m_undoManager->removeAllItems();
2587
2588 m_textManipulationController = nullptr; // Free nodes kept alive by TextManipulationController.
2589
2590#if ENABLE(ACCESSIBILITY)
2591 if (this != &topDocument()) {
2592 // Let the ax cache know that this subframe goes out of scope.
2593 if (auto* cache = existingAXObjectCache())
2594 cache->prepareForDocumentDestruction(*this);
2595 }
2596#endif
2597
2598 {
2599 NavigationDisabler navigationDisabler(m_frame.get());
2600 disconnectDescendantFrames();
2601 }
2602 RELEASE_ASSERT_WITH_SECURITY_IMPLICATION(!m_frame || !m_frame->tree().childCount());
2603
2604 ScriptDisallowedScope::InMainThread scriptDisallowedScope;
2605
2606 if (m_domWindow && m_frame)
2607 m_domWindow->willDetachDocumentFromFrame();
2608
2609 styleScope().clearResolver();
2610
2611 if (hasLivingRenderTree())
2612 destroyRenderTree();
2613
2614 if (is<PluginDocument>(*this))
2615 downcast<PluginDocument>(*this).detachFromPluginElement();
2616
2617 if (auto* page = this->page()) {
2618#if ENABLE(POINTER_LOCK)
2619 page->pointerLockController().documentDetached(*this);
2620#endif
2621 if (auto* imageOverlayController = page->imageOverlayControllerIfExists())
2622 imageOverlayController->documentDetached(*this);
2623 if (auto* validationMessageClient = page->validationMessageClient())
2624 validationMessageClient->documentDetached(*this);
2625 }
2626
2627 InspectorInstrumentation::documentDetached(*this);
2628
2629 commonTeardown();
2630
2631#if ENABLE(TOUCH_EVENTS)
2632 if (m_touchEventTargets && m_touchEventTargets->size() && parentDocument())
2633 parentDocument()->didRemoveEventTargetNode(*this);
2634#endif
2635
2636 if (m_wheelEventTargets && m_wheelEventTargets->size() && parentDocument())
2637 parentDocument()->didRemoveEventTargetNode(*this);
2638
2639 if (m_mediaQueryMatcher)
2640 m_mediaQueryMatcher->documentDestroyed();
2641
2642#if ENABLE(WIRELESS_PLAYBACK_TARGET)
2643 if (!m_clientToIDMap.isEmpty() && page()) {
2644 for (auto* client : copyToVector(m_clientToIDMap.keys()))
2645 removePlaybackTargetPickerClient(*client);
2646 }
2647#endif
2648
2649 m_cachedResourceLoader->stopUnusedPreloadsTimer();
2650
2651 if (page() && !m_mediaState.isEmpty()) {
2652 m_mediaState = MediaProducer::IsNotPlaying;
2653 page()->updateIsPlayingMedia();
2654 }
2655
2656 selection().willBeRemovedFromFrame();
2657 editor().clear();
2658 detachFromFrame();
2659
2660#if ENABLE(CSS_PAINTING_API)
2661 for (auto& scope : m_paintWorkletGlobalScopes.values())
2662 scope->prepareForDestruction();
2663 m_paintWorkletGlobalScopes.clear();
2664#endif
2665
2666 m_hasPreparedForDestruction = true;
2667
2668 // Note that m_backForwardCacheState can be Document::AboutToEnterBackForwardCache if our frame
2669 // was removed in an onpagehide event handler fired when the top-level frame is
2670 // about to enter the back/forward cache.
2671 RELEASE_ASSERT(m_backForwardCacheState != Document::InBackForwardCache);
2672}
2673
2674void Document::removeAllEventListeners()

2676 EventTarget::removeAllEventListeners();
2677
2678 if (m_domWindow)
2679 m_domWindow->removeAllEventListeners();
2680
2681#if ENABLE(IOS_TOUCH_EVENTS)
2682 clearTouchEventHandlersAndListeners();
2683#endif
2684 for (Node* node = firstChild(); node; node = NodeTraversal::next(*node))
2685 node->removeAllEventListeners();
2686
2687#if ENABLE(TOUCH_EVENTS)
2688 m_touchEventTargets = nullptr;
2689#endif
2690 m_wheelEventTargets = nullptr;
2691}

2724bool Document::shouldBypassMainWorldContentSecurityPolicy() const
2725{
2726 // Bypass this policy when the world is known, and it not the normal world.
2727 JSC::VM& vm = commonVM();
2728 auto* callFrame = vm.topCallFrame;
2729 return callFrame && callFrame != JSC::CallFrame::noCaller() && !currentWorld(*callFrame->lexicalGlobalObject(vm)).isNormal();
2730}

2744 suspendDeviceMotionAndOrientationUpdates();

2749{

2751 m_documentTaskGroup->resume();

2753 resumeDeviceMotionAndOrientationUpdates();
2754 // FIXME: For iOS, do we need to add content change observers that were removed in Document::suspendActiveDOMObjects()?
2755}

2762 platformSuspendOrStopActiveDOMObjects();

2771}

2773AXObjectCache* Document::existingAXObjectCacheSlow() const
2774{
2775 ASSERT(hasEverCreatedAnAXObjectCache);
2776 return topDocument().m_axObjectCache.get();
2777}
2778
2779AXObjectCache* Document::axObjectCache() const
2780{
2781 if (!AXObjectCache::accessibilityEnabled())
2782 return nullptr;
2783
2784 // The only document that actually has a AXObjectCache is the top-level
2785 // document. This is because we need to be able to get from any WebCoreAXObject
2786 // to any other WebCoreAXObject on the same page. Using a single cache allows
2787 // lookups across nested webareas (i.e. multiple documents).
2788 Document& topDocument = this->topDocument();
2789
2790 // If the document has already been detached, do not make a new axObjectCache.
2791 if (!topDocument.hasLivingRenderTree())
2792 return nullptr;
2793
2794 ASSERT(&topDocument == this || !m_axObjectCache);
2795 if (!topDocument.m_axObjectCache) {
2796 topDocument.m_axObjectCache = makeUnique<AXObjectCache>(topDocument);
2797 hasEverCreatedAnAXObjectCache = true;
2798 }
2799 return topDocument.m_axObjectCache.get();
2800}

2805 if (renderView())
2806 renderView()->mutableStyle().setRTLOrdering(Order::Visual);
2807}

2839void Document::collectRangeDataFromRegister(Vector<WeakPtr<HighlightRangeData>>& rangesData, const HighlightRegister& highlightRegister)
2840{
2841 for (auto& highlight : highlightRegister.map()) {
2842 for (auto& rangeData : highlight.value->rangesData()) {
2843 if (rangeData->startPosition && rangeData->endPosition)
2844 continue;
2845 if (&rangeData->range->startContainer().treeScope() != &rangeData->range->endContainer().treeScope())
2846 continue;
2847 rangesData.append(makeWeakPtr(rangeData.ptr()));
2848 }
2849 }
2850}
2851
2852void Document::updateHighlightPositions()
2853{
2854 Vector<WeakPtr<HighlightRangeData>> rangesData;
2855 if (m_highlightRegister)
2856 collectRangeDataFromRegister(rangesData, *m_highlightRegister.get());
2857#if ENABLE(APP_HIGHLIGHTS)
2858 if (m_appHighlightRegister)
2859 collectRangeDataFromRegister(rangesData, *m_appHighlightRegister.get());
2860#endif
2861
2862 for (auto& weakRangeData : rangesData) {
2863 if (auto* rangeData = weakRangeData.get()) {
2864 VisibleSelection visibleSelection(rangeData->range);
2865 Position startPosition;
2866 Position endPosition;
2867 if (!rangeData->startPosition.has_value())
2868 startPosition = visibleSelection.visibleStart().deepEquivalent();
2869 if (!rangeData->endPosition.has_value())
2870 endPosition = visibleSelection.visibleEnd().deepEquivalent();
2871 if (!weakRangeData.get())
2872 continue;
2873
2874 rangeData->startPosition = startPosition;
2875 rangeData->endPosition = endPosition;
2876 }
2877 }
2878}

2892
2893ExceptionOr<Document&> Document::openForBindings(Document* responsibleDocument, const String&, const String&)
2894{
2895 if (!isHTMLDocument() || m_throwOnDynamicMarkupInsertionCount)
2896 return Exception { InvalidStateError };
2897
2898 auto result = open(responsibleDocument);
2899 if (UNLIKELY(result.hasException()))
2900 return result.releaseException();
2901
2902 return *this;
2903}
2904
2905ExceptionOr<void> Document::open(Document* responsibleDocument)
2906{
2907 if (responsibleDocument && !responsibleDocument->securityOrigin().isSameOriginAs(securityOrigin()))
2908 return Exception { SecurityError };
2909
2910 if (m_ignoreOpensDuringUnloadCount)
2911 return { };
2912
2913 if (m_activeParserWasAborted)
2914 return { };
2915
2916 if (m_frame) {
2917 if (ScriptableDocumentParser* parser = scriptableDocumentParser()) {
2918 if (parser->isParsing()) {
2919 // FIXME: HTML5 doesn't tell us to check this, it might not be correct.
2920 if (parser->isExecutingScript())
2921 return { };
2922
2923 if (!parser->wasCreatedByScript() && parser->hasInsertionPoint())
2924 return { };
2925 }
2926 }
2927
2928 if (m_frame->loader().policyChecker().delegateIsDecidingNavigationPolicy())
2929 m_frame->loader().policyChecker().stopCheck();
2930 if (m_frame && m_frame->loader().state() == FrameState::Provisional)
2931 m_frame->loader().stopAllLoaders();
2932 }
2933
2934 removeAllEventListeners();
2935
2936 if (responsibleDocument && isFullyActive()) {
2937 auto newURL = responsibleDocument->url();
2938 if (responsibleDocument != this)
2939 newURL.removeFragmentIdentifier();
2940 setURL(newURL);
2941 auto newCookieURL = responsibleDocument->cookieURL();
2942 if (responsibleDocument != this)
2943 newCookieURL.removeFragmentIdentifier();
2944 setCookieURL(newCookieURL);
2945 setSecurityOriginPolicy(responsibleDocument->securityOriginPolicy());
2946 }
2947
2948 implicitOpen();
2949 if (ScriptableDocumentParser* parser = scriptableDocumentParser())
2950 parser->setWasCreatedByScript(true);
2951
2952 if (m_frame)
2953 m_frame->loader().didExplicitOpen();
2954
2955 return { };
2956}
2957
2958// https://html.spec.whatwg.org/#fully-active
2959bool Document::isFullyActive() const
2960{
2961 auto* frame = this->frame();
2962 if (!frame || frame->document() != this)
2963 return false;
2964
2965 if (frame->isMainFrame())
2966 return true;
2967
2968 auto* parentFrame = frame->tree().parent();
2969 return parentFrame && parentFrame->document() && parentFrame->document()->isFullyActive();
2970}
2971
2972void Document::detachParser()
2973{
2974 if (!m_parser)
2975 return;
2976 m_parser->detach();
2977 m_parser = nullptr;
2978}
2979
2980void Document::cancelParsing()
2981{
2982 if (!m_parser)
2983 return;
2984
2985 if (m_parser->processingData())
2986 m_activeParserWasAborted = true;
2987
2988 // We have to clear the parser to avoid possibly triggering
2989 // the onload handler when closing as a side effect of a cancel-style
2990 // change, such as opening a new document or closing the window while
2991 // still parsing
2992 detachParser();
2993 explicitClose();
2994}
2995
2996void Document::implicitOpen()
2997{
2998 removeChildren();
2999
3000 setCompatibilityMode(DocumentCompatibilityMode::NoQuirksMode);
3001
3002 detachParser();
3003 m_parser = createParser();
3004
3005 if (hasActiveParserYieldToken())
3006 m_parser->didBeginYieldingParser();
3007
3008 setParsing(true);
3009 setReadyState(Loading);
3010}
