3032
3033HTMLElement* Document::bodyOrFrameset() const
3034{
3035 // Return the first body or frameset child of the html element.
3036 auto* element = documentElement();
3037 if (!is<HTMLHtmlElement>(element))
3038 return nullptr;
3039 for (auto& child : childrenOfType<HTMLElement>(*element)) {
3040 if (is<HTMLBodyElement>(child) || is<HTMLFrameSetElement>(child))
3041 return &child;
3042 }
3043 return nullptr;
3044}
3045
3046ExceptionOr<void> Document::setBodyOrFrameset(RefPtr<HTMLElement>&& newBody)
3047{
3048 if (!is<HTMLBodyElement>(newBody) && !is<HTMLFrameSetElement>(newBody))
3049 return Exception { HierarchyRequestError };
3050
3051 auto* currentBody = bodyOrFrameset();
3052 if (newBody == currentBody)
3053 return { };
3054
3055 if (!m_documentElement)
3056 return Exception { HierarchyRequestError };
3057
3058 if (currentBody)
3059 return m_documentElement->replaceChild(*newBody, *currentBody);
3060 return m_documentElement->appendChild(*newBody);
3061}

3088void Document::close()

3095
3096void Document::explicitClose()
3097{
3098 if (RefPtr<DocumentParser> parser = m_parser)
3099 parser->finish();
3100
3101 if (!m_frame) {
3102 // Because we have no frame, we don't know if all loading has completed,
3103 // so we just call implicitClose() immediately. FIXME: This might fire
3104 // the load event prematurely <http://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=14568>.
3105 implicitClose();
3106 return;
3107 }
3108
3109 checkCompleted();
3110}
3111
3112void Document::implicitClose()
3113{
3114 RELEASE_ASSERT(!m_inStyleRecalc);
3115 bool wasLocationChangePending = frame() && frame()->navigationScheduler().locationChangePending();
3116 bool doload = !parsing() && m_parser && !m_processingLoadEvent && !wasLocationChangePending;
3117
3118 if (!doload)
3119 return;
3120
3121 // Call to dispatchWindowLoadEvent can blow us from underneath.
3122 Ref<Document> protectedThis(*this);
3123
3124 m_processingLoadEvent = true;
3125
3126 ScriptableDocumentParser* parser = scriptableDocumentParser();
3127 m_wellFormed = parser && parser->wellFormed();
3128
3129 // We have to clear the parser, in case someone document.write()s from the
3130 // onLoad event handler, as in Radar 3206524.
3131 detachParser();
3132
3133 // FIXME: We kick off the icon loader when the Document is done parsing.
3134 // There are earlier opportunities we could start it:
3135 // -When the <head> finishes parsing
3136 // -When any new HTMLLinkElement is inserted into the document
3137 // But those add a dynamic component to the favicon that has UI
3138 // ramifications, and we need to decide what is the Right Thing To Do(tm)
3139 RefPtr<Frame> f = frame();
3140 if (f) {
3141#if ENABLE(XSLT)
3142 // Apply XSL transforms before load events so that event handlers can access the transformed DOM tree.
3143 applyPendingXSLTransformsNowIfScheduled();
3144#endif
3145
3146 if (auto* documentLoader = loader())
3147 documentLoader->startIconLoading();
3148
3149 // FIXME: We shouldn't be dispatching pending events globally on all Documents here.
3150 // For now, only do this when there is a Frame, otherwise this could cause JS reentrancy
3151 // below SVG font parsing, for example. <https://webkit.org/b/136269>
3152 if (auto* currentPage = page()) {
3153 ImageLoader::dispatchPendingBeforeLoadEvents(currentPage);
3154 ImageLoader::dispatchPendingLoadEvents(currentPage);
3155 ImageLoader::dispatchPendingErrorEvents(currentPage);
3156 HTMLLinkElement::dispatchPendingLoadEvents(currentPage);
3157 HTMLStyleElement::dispatchPendingLoadEvents(currentPage);
3158 }
3159
3160 if (svgExtensions())
3161 accessSVGExtensions().dispatchLoadEventToOutermostSVGElements();
3162 }
3163
3164 dispatchWindowLoadEvent();
3165 dispatchPageshowEvent(PageshowEventNotPersisted);
3166 if (m_pendingStateObject)
3167 dispatchPopstateEvent(WTFMove(m_pendingStateObject));
3168
3169 if (f)
3170 f->loader().dispatchOnloadEvents();
3171
3172 // An event handler may have removed the frame
3173 if (!frame()) {
3174 m_processingLoadEvent = false;
3175 return;
3176 }
3177
3178 frame()->loader().checkCallImplicitClose();
3179
3180 // We used to force a synchronous display and flush here. This really isn't
3181 // necessary and can in fact be actively harmful if pages are loading at a rate of > 60fps
3182 // (if your platform is syncing flushes and limiting them to 60fps).
3183 if (!ownerElement() || (ownerElement()->renderer() && !ownerElement()->renderer()->needsLayout())) {
3184 updateStyleIfNeeded();
3185
3186 // Always do a layout after loading if needed.
3187 if (view() && renderView() && (!renderView()->firstChild() || renderView()->needsLayout()))
3188 view()->layoutContext().layout();
3189 }
3190
3191 m_processingLoadEvent = false;
3192
3193 if (auto fontFaceSet = makeRefPtr(fontSelector().fontFaceSetIfExists()))
3194 fontFaceSet->documentDidFinishLoading();
3195
3196#if PLATFORM(COCOA) || PLATFORM(WIN) || PLATFORM(GTK)
3197 if (f && hasLivingRenderTree() && AXObjectCache::accessibilityEnabled()) {
3198 // The AX cache may have been cleared at this point, but we need to make sure it contains an
3199 // AX object to send the notification to. getOrCreate will make sure that an valid AX object
3200 // exists in the cache (we ignore the return value because we don't need it here). This is
3201 // only safe to call when a layout is not in progress, so it can not be used in postNotification.
3202 //
3203 // This notification is now called AXNewDocumentLoadComplete because there are other handlers that will
3204 // catch new AND page history loads, and that uses AXLoadComplete
3205
3206 axObjectCache()->getOrCreate(renderView());
3207 if (this == &topDocument())
3208 axObjectCache()->postNotification(renderView(), AXObjectCache::AXNewDocumentLoadComplete);
3209 else {
3210 // AXLoadComplete can only be posted on the top document, so if it's a document
3211 // in an iframe that just finished loading, post AXLayoutComplete instead.
3212 axObjectCache()->postNotification(renderView(), AXObjectCache::AXLayoutComplete);
3213 }
3214 }
3215#endif
3216
3217 if (svgExtensions())
3218 accessSVGExtensions().startAnimations();
3219}
3220
3221void Document::setParsing(bool b)
3222{
3223 m_bParsing = b;
3224
3225 if (m_bParsing && !m_sharedObjectPool)
3226 m_sharedObjectPool = makeUnique<DocumentSharedObjectPool>();
3227
3228 if (!m_bParsing && view() && !view()->needsLayout())
3229 view()->fireLayoutRelatedMilestonesIfNeeded();
3230}

3232bool Document::shouldScheduleLayout() const
3233{
3234 if (!documentElement())
3235 return false;
3236 if (!is<HTMLHtmlElement>(*documentElement()))
3237 return true;
3238 if (!bodyOrFrameset())
3239 return false;
3240 if (styleScope().hasPendingSheetsBeforeBody())
3241 return false;
3242 if (view() && !view()->isVisuallyNonEmpty())
3243 return false;
3244 return true;
3245}

3250}

3252bool Document::supportsPaintTiming() const
3253{
3254 return RuntimeEnabledFeatures::sharedFeatures().paintTimingEnabled() && securityOrigin().isSameOriginDomain(topOrigin());
3255}
3256
3257// https://w3c.github.io/paint-timing/#ref-for-mark-paint-timing
3258void Document::enqueuePaintTimingEntryIfNeeded()
3259{
3260 if (m_didEnqueueFirstContentfulPaint)
3261 return;
3262
3263 if (!supportsPaintTiming())
3264 return;
3265
3266 if (!domWindow() || !view())
3267 return;
3268
3269 // To make sure we don't report paint while the layer tree is still frozen.
3270 if (!view()->isVisuallyNonEmpty() || view()->needsLayout())
3271 return;
3272
3273 if (!view()->hasContentfulDescendants())
3274 return;
3275
3276 if (!ContentfulPaintChecker::qualifiesForContentfulPaint(*view()))
3277 return;
3278
3279 domWindow()->performance().reportFirstContentfulPaint();
3280 m_didEnqueueFirstContentfulPaint = true;
3281}
3282
3283ExceptionOr<void> Document::write(Document* responsibleDocument, SegmentedString&& text)
3284{
3285 if (m_activeParserWasAborted)
3286 return { };
3287
3288 NestingLevelIncrementer nestingLevelIncrementer(m_writeRecursionDepth);
3289
3290 m_writeRecursionIsTooDeep = (m_writeRecursionDepth > 1) && m_writeRecursionIsTooDeep;
3291 m_writeRecursionIsTooDeep = (m_writeRecursionDepth > cMaxWriteRecursionDepth) || m_writeRecursionIsTooDeep;
3292
3293 if (m_writeRecursionIsTooDeep)
3294 return { };
3295
3296 bool hasInsertionPoint = m_parser && m_parser->hasInsertionPoint();
3297 if (!hasInsertionPoint && (m_ignoreOpensDuringUnloadCount || m_ignoreDestructiveWriteCount))
3298 return { };
3299
3300 if (!hasInsertionPoint) {
3301 auto result = open(responsibleDocument);
3302 if (UNLIKELY(result.hasException()))
3303 return result.releaseException();
3304 }
3305
3306 ASSERT(m_parser);
3307 m_parser->insert(WTFMove(text));
3308 return { };
3309}
3310
3311ExceptionOr<void> Document::write(Document* responsibleDocument, Vector<String>&& strings)
3312{
3313 if (!isHTMLDocument() || m_throwOnDynamicMarkupInsertionCount)
3314 return Exception { InvalidStateError };
3315
3316 SegmentedString text;
3317 for (auto& string : strings)
3318 text.append(WTFMove(string));
3319
3320 return write(responsibleDocument, WTFMove(text));
3321}
3322
3323ExceptionOr<void> Document::writeln(Document* responsibleDocument, Vector<String>&& strings)
3324{
3325 if (!isHTMLDocument() || m_throwOnDynamicMarkupInsertionCount)
3326 return Exception { InvalidStateError };
3327
3328 SegmentedString text;
3329 for (auto& string : strings)
3330 text.append(WTFMove(string));
3331
3332 text.append("\n"_s);
3333 return write(responsibleDocument, WTFMove(text));
3334}

3361
3362Seconds Document::domTimerAlignmentInterval(bool hasReachedMaxNestingLevel) const
3363{
3364 auto alignmentInterval = ScriptExecutionContext::domTimerAlignmentInterval(hasReachedMaxNestingLevel);
3365 if (!hasReachedMaxNestingLevel)
3366 return alignmentInterval;
3367
3368 // Apply Document-level DOMTimer throttling only if timers have reached their maximum nesting level as the Page may still be visible.
3369 if (m_isTimerThrottlingEnabled)
3370 alignmentInterval = std::max(alignmentInterval, DOMTimer::hiddenPageAlignmentInterval());
3371
3372 if (Page* page = this->page())
3373 alignmentInterval = std::max(alignmentInterval, page->domTimerAlignmentInterval());
3374
3375 if (!topOrigin().isSameOriginDomain(securityOrigin()) && !hasHadUserInteraction())
3376 alignmentInterval = std::max(alignmentInterval, DOMTimer::nonInteractedCrossOriginFrameAlignmentInterval());
3377
3378 return alignmentInterval;
3379}

3390
3391void Document::setURL(const URL& url)
3392{
3393 const URL& newURL = url.isEmpty() ? aboutBlankURL() : url;
3394 if (newURL == m_url)
3395 return;
3396
3397 m_url = newURL;
3398 if (SecurityOrigin::shouldIgnoreHost(m_url))
3399 m_url.setHostAndPort({ });
3400
3401 m_documentURI = m_url.string();
3402 updateBaseURL();
3403}
3404
3405void Document::updateBaseURL()
3406{
3407 URL oldBaseURL = m_baseURL;
3408 // DOM 3 Core: When the Document supports the feature "HTML" [DOM Level 2 HTML], the base URI is computed using
3409 // first the value of the href attribute of the HTML BASE element if any, and the value of the documentURI attribute
3410 // from the Document interface otherwise.
3411 if (!m_baseElementURL.isEmpty())
3412 m_baseURL = m_baseElementURL;
3413 else if (!m_baseURLOverride.isEmpty())
3414 m_baseURL = m_baseURLOverride;
3415 else {
3416 // The documentURI attribute is read-only from JavaScript, but writable from Objective C, so we need to retain
3417 // this fallback behavior. We use a null base URL, since the documentURI attribute is an arbitrary string
3418 // and DOM 3 Core does not specify how it should be resolved.
3419 m_baseURL = URL({ }, documentURI());
3420 }
3421
3422 clearSelectorQueryCache();
3423
3424 if (!m_baseURL.isValid())
3425 m_baseURL = URL();
3426}
3427
3428void Document::setBaseURLOverride(const URL& url)
3429{
3430 m_baseURLOverride = url;
3431 updateBaseURL();
3432}
3433
3434void Document::processBaseElement()
3435{
3436 // Find the first href attribute in a base element and the first target attribute in a base element.
3437 const AtomString* href = nullptr;
3438 const AtomString* target = nullptr;
3439 auto baseDescendants = descendantsOfType<HTMLBaseElement>(*this);
3440 for (auto& base : baseDescendants) {
3441 if (!href) {
3442 const AtomString& value = base.attributeWithoutSynchronization(hrefAttr);
3443 if (!value.isNull()) {
3444 href = &value;
3445 if (target)
3446 break;
3447 }
3448 }
3449 if (!target) {
3450 const AtomString& value = base.attributeWithoutSynchronization(targetAttr);
3451 if (!value.isNull()) {
3452 target = &value;
3453 if (href)
3454 break;
3455 }
3456 }
3457 }
3458
3459 // FIXME: Since this doesn't share code with completeURL it may not handle encodings correctly.
3460 URL baseElementURL;
3461 if (href) {
3462 String strippedHref = stripLeadingAndTrailingHTMLSpaces(*href);
3463 if (!strippedHref.isEmpty())
3464 baseElementURL = URL(url(), strippedHref);
3465 }
3466 if (m_baseElementURL != baseElementURL && contentSecurityPolicy()->allowBaseURI(baseElementURL)) {
3467 if (settings().shouldRestrictBaseURLSchemes() && !SecurityPolicy::isBaseURLSchemeAllowed(baseElementURL))
3468 addConsoleMessage(MessageSource::Security, MessageLevel::Error, "Blocked setting " + baseElementURL.stringCenterEllipsizedToLength() + " as the base URL because it does not have an allowed scheme.");
3469 else {
3470 m_baseElementURL = baseElementURL;
3471 updateBaseURL();
3472 }
3473 }
3474
3475 m_baseTarget = target ? *target : nullAtom();
3476}

3523
3524bool Document::canNavigate(Frame* targetFrame, const URL& destinationURL)
3525{
3526 if (!m_frame)
3527 return false;
3528
3529 // FIXME: We shouldn't call this function without a target frame, but
3530 // fast/forms/submit-to-blank-multiple-times.html depends on this function
3531 // returning true when supplied with a 0 targetFrame.
3532 if (!targetFrame)
3533 return true;
3534
3535 if (!canNavigateInternal(*targetFrame))
3536 return false;
3537
3538 if (isNavigationBlockedByThirdPartyIFrameRedirectBlocking(*targetFrame, destinationURL)) {
3539 printNavigationErrorMessage(*targetFrame, url(), "The frame attempting navigation of the top-level window is cross-origin or untrusted and the user has never interacted with the frame."_s);
3540 DOCUMENT_RELEASE_LOG_ERROR(Loading, "Navigation was prevented because it was triggered by a cross-origin or untrusted iframe");
3541 return false;
3542 }
3543
3544 return true;
3545}
3546
3547bool Document::canNavigateInternal(Frame& targetFrame)
3548{
3549 ASSERT(m_frame);
3550
3551 // Cases (i), (ii) and (iii) pass the tests from the specifications but might not pass the "security origin" tests.
3552
3553 // i. A frame can navigate its top ancestor when its 'allow-top-navigation' flag is set (sometimes known as 'frame-busting').
3554 if (!isSandboxed(SandboxTopNavigation) && &targetFrame == &m_frame->tree().top())
3555 return true;
3556
3557 // The user gesture only relaxes permissions for the purpose of navigating if its impacts the current document.
3558 bool isProcessingUserGestureForDocument = UserGestureIndicator::processingUserGesture(m_frame->document());
3559
3560 // ii. A frame can navigate its top ancestor when its 'allow-top-navigation-by-user-activation' flag is set and navigation is triggered by user activation.
3561 if (!isSandboxed(SandboxTopNavigationByUserActivation) && isProcessingUserGestureForDocument && &targetFrame == &m_frame->tree().top())
3562 return true;
3563
3564 // iii. A sandboxed frame can always navigate its descendants.
3565 if (isSandboxed(SandboxNavigation) && targetFrame.tree().isDescendantOf(m_frame.get()))
3566 return true;
3567
3568 // From https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/browsers.html#allowed-to-navigate.
3569 // 1. If A is not the same browsing context as B, and A is not one of the ancestor browsing contexts of B, and B is not a top-level browsing context, and A's active document's active sandboxing
3570 // flag set has its sandboxed navigation browsing context flag set, then abort these steps negatively.
3571 if (m_frame != &targetFrame && isSandboxed(SandboxNavigation) && targetFrame.tree().parent() && !targetFrame.tree().isDescendantOf(m_frame.get())) {
3572 printNavigationErrorMessage(targetFrame, url(), "The frame attempting navigation is sandboxed, and is therefore disallowed from navigating its ancestors."_s);
3573 return false;
3574 }
3575
3576 // 2. Otherwise, if B is a top-level browsing context, and is one of the ancestor browsing contexts of A, then:
3577 if (m_frame != &targetFrame && &targetFrame == &m_frame->tree().top()) {
3578 // 1. If this algorithm is triggered by user activation and A's active document's active sandboxing flag set has its sandboxed top-level navigation with user activation browsing context flag set, then abort these steps negatively.
3579 if (isProcessingUserGestureForDocument && isSandboxed(SandboxTopNavigationByUserActivation)) {
3580 printNavigationErrorMessage(targetFrame, url(), "The frame attempting navigation of the top-level window is sandboxed, but the 'allow-top-navigation-by-user-activation' flag is not set and navigation is not triggered by user activation."_s);
3581 return false;
3582 }
3583 // 2. Otherwise, If this algorithm is not triggered by user activation and A's active document's active sandboxing flag set has its sandboxed top-level navigation without user activation browsing context flag set, then abort these steps negatively.
3584 if (!isProcessingUserGestureForDocument && isSandboxed(SandboxTopNavigation)) {
3585 printNavigationErrorMessage(targetFrame, url(), "The frame attempting navigation of the top-level window is sandboxed, but the 'allow-top-navigation' flag is not set."_s);
3586 return false;
3587 }
3588 }
3589
3590 // 3. Otherwise, if B is a top-level browsing context, and is neither A nor one of the ancestor browsing contexts of A, and A's Document's active sandboxing flag set has its
3591 // sandboxed navigation browsing context flag set, and A is not the one permitted sandboxed navigator of B, then abort these steps negatively.
3592 if (!targetFrame.tree().parent() && m_frame != &targetFrame && &targetFrame != &m_frame->tree().top() && isSandboxed(SandboxNavigation) && targetFrame.loader().opener() != m_frame) {
3593 printNavigationErrorMessage(targetFrame, url(), "The frame attempting navigation is sandboxed, and is not allowed to navigate this popup."_s);
3594 return false;
3595 }
3596
3597 // 4. Otherwise, terminate positively!
3598
3599 // This is the normal case. A document can navigate its descendant frames,
3600 // or, more generally, a document can navigate a frame if the document is
3601 // in the same origin as any of that frame's ancestors (in the frame
3602 // hierarchy).
3603 //
3604 // See http://www.adambarth.com/papers/2008/barth-jackson-mitchell.pdf for
3605 // historical information about this security check.
3606 if (canAccessAncestor(securityOrigin(), &targetFrame))
3607 return true;
3608
3609 // Top-level frames are easier to navigate than other frames because they
3610 // display their URLs in the address bar (in most browsers). However, there
3611 // are still some restrictions on navigation to avoid nuisance attacks.
3612 // Specifically, a document can navigate a top-level frame if that frame
3613 // opened the document or if the document is the same-origin with any of
3614 // the top-level frame's opener's ancestors (in the frame hierarchy).
3615 //
3616 // In both of these cases, the document performing the navigation is in
3617 // some way related to the frame being navigate (e.g., by the "opener"
3618 // and/or "parent" relation). Requiring some sort of relation prevents a
3619 // document from navigating arbitrary, unrelated top-level frames.
3620 if (!targetFrame.tree().parent()) {
3621 if (&targetFrame == m_frame->loader().opener())
3622 return true;
3623
3624 if (canAccessAncestor(securityOrigin(), targetFrame.loader().opener()))
3625 return true;
3626 }
3627
3628 printNavigationErrorMessage(targetFrame, url(), "The frame attempting navigation is neither same-origin with the target, nor is it the target's parent or opener.");
3629 return false;
3630}

3632void Document::willLoadScriptElement(const URL& scriptURL)

3636
3637void Document::willLoadFrameElement(const URL& frameURL)

3640}
3641
3642// Prevent cross-site top-level redirects from third-party iframes unless the user has ever interacted with the frame.
3643bool Document::isNavigationBlockedByThirdPartyIFrameRedirectBlocking(Frame& targetFrame, const URL& destinationURL)
3644{
3645 if (!settings().thirdPartyIframeRedirectBlockingEnabled())
3646 return false;
3647
3648 // Only prevent top frame navigations by subframes.
3649 if (m_frame == &targetFrame || &targetFrame != &m_frame->tree().top())
3650 return false;
3651
3652 // Only prevent navigations by subframes that the user has not interacted with.
3653 if (m_frame->hasHadUserInteraction())
3654 return false;
3655
3656 // Only prevent navigations by unsandboxed iframes. Such navigations by unsandboxed iframes would have already been blocked unless
3657 // "allow-top-navigation" / "allow-top-navigation-by-user-activation" was explicitly specified.
3658 if (sandboxFlags() != SandboxNone) {
3659 // Navigation is only allowed if the parent of the sandboxed iframe is first-party.
3660 auto* parentDocument = m_frame->tree().parent() ? m_frame->tree().parent()->document() : nullptr;
3661 if (parentDocument && canAccessAncestor(parentDocument->securityOrigin(), &targetFrame))
3662 return false;
3663 }
3664
3665 // Only prevent navigations by third-party iframes or untrusted first-party iframes.
3666 bool isUntrustedIframe = m_hasLoadedThirdPartyScript && m_hasLoadedThirdPartyFrame;
3667 if (canAccessAncestor(securityOrigin(), &targetFrame) && !isUntrustedIframe)
3668 return false;
3669
3670 // Only prevent cross-site navigations.
3671 auto* targetDocument = targetFrame.document();
3672 if (targetDocument && (targetDocument->securityOrigin().isSameOriginDomain(SecurityOrigin::create(destinationURL)) || areRegistrableDomainsEqual(targetDocument->url(), destinationURL)))
3673 return false;
3674
3675 return true;
3676}
3677
3678void Document::didRemoveAllPendingStylesheet()
3679{
3680 if (auto* parser = scriptableDocumentParser())
3681 parser->executeScriptsWaitingForStylesheetsSoon();
3682
3683 if (m_gotoAnchorNeededAfterStylesheetsLoad) {
3684 // https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/browsing-the-web.html#try-to-scroll-to-the-fragment
3685 eventLoop().queueTask(TaskSource::Networking, [protectedThis = makeRef(*this), this] {
3686 auto frameView = makeRefPtr(view());
3687 if (!frameView)
3688 return;
3689 if (!haveStylesheetsLoaded()) {
3690 m_gotoAnchorNeededAfterStylesheetsLoad = true;
3691 return;
3692 }
3693 frameView->scrollToFragment(m_url);
3694 });
3695 }
3696}

3715
3716void Document::processHttpEquiv(const String& equiv, const String& content, bool isInDocumentHead)
3717{
3718 ASSERT(!equiv.isNull());
3719 ASSERT(!content.isNull());
3720
3721 HttpEquivPolicy policy = httpEquivPolicy();
3722 if (policy != HttpEquivPolicy::Enabled) {
3723 String reason;
3724 switch (policy) {
3725 case HttpEquivPolicy::Enabled:
3726 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
3727 break;
3728 case HttpEquivPolicy::DisabledBySettings:
3729 reason = "by the embedder.";
3730 break;
3731 case HttpEquivPolicy::DisabledByContentDispositionAttachmentSandbox:
3732 reason = "for documents with Content-Disposition: attachment.";
3733 break;
3734 }
3735 String message = "http-equiv '" + equiv + "' is disabled " + reason;
3736 addConsoleMessage(MessageSource::Security, MessageLevel::Error, message);
3737 return;
3738 }
3739
3740 Frame* frame = this->frame();
3741 auto* documentLoader = frame ? frame->loader().documentLoader() : nullptr;
3742 auto httpStatusCode = documentLoader ? documentLoader->response().httpStatusCode() : 0;
3743
3744 HTTPHeaderName headerName;
3745 if (!findHTTPHeaderName(equiv, headerName))
3746 return;
3747
3748 switch (headerName) {
3749 case HTTPHeaderName::DefaultStyle:
3750 // The preferred style set has been overridden as per section
3751 // 14.3.2 of the HTML4.0 specification. We need to update the
3752 // sheet used variable and then update our style selector.
3753 // For more info, see the test at:
3754 // http://www.hixie.ch/tests/evil/css/import/main/preferred.html
3755 // -dwh
3756 styleScope().setPreferredStylesheetSetName(content);
3757 break;
3758
3759 case HTTPHeaderName::Refresh:
3760 if (frame)
3761 frame->loader().scheduleRefreshIfNeeded(*this, content);
3762 break;
3763
3764 case HTTPHeaderName::SetCookie:
3765 if (isHTMLDocument())
3766 addConsoleMessage(MessageSource::Security, MessageLevel::Error, "The Set-Cookie meta tag is obsolete and was ignored. Use the HTTP header Set-Cookie or document.cookie instead."_s);
3767 break;
3768
3769 case HTTPHeaderName::ContentLanguage:
3770 setContentLanguage(content);
3771 break;
3772
3773 case HTTPHeaderName::XDNSPrefetchControl:
3774 parseDNSPrefetchControlHeader(content);
3775 break;
3776
3777 case HTTPHeaderName::XFrameOptions:
3778 if (frame) {
3779 FrameLoader& frameLoader = frame->loader();
3780 unsigned long requestIdentifier = 0;
3781 if (frameLoader.activeDocumentLoader() && frameLoader.activeDocumentLoader()->mainResourceLoader())
3782 requestIdentifier = frameLoader.activeDocumentLoader()->mainResourceLoader()->identifier();
3783
3784 String message = "The X-Frame-Option '" + content + "' supplied in a <meta> element was ignored. X-Frame-Options may only be provided by an HTTP header sent with the document.";
3785 addConsoleMessage(MessageSource::Security, MessageLevel::Error, message, requestIdentifier);
3786 }
3787 break;
3788
3789 case HTTPHeaderName::ContentSecurityPolicy:
3790 if (isInDocumentHead)
3791 contentSecurityPolicy()->didReceiveHeader(content, ContentSecurityPolicyHeaderType::Enforce, ContentSecurityPolicy::PolicyFrom::HTTPEquivMeta, referrer(), httpStatusCode);
3792 break;
3793
3794 default:
3795 break;
3796 }
3797}

3820void Document::processViewport(const String& features, ViewportArguments::Type origin)

3825

3827 return;
3828

3838}

3859void Document::metaElementThemeColorChanged(HTMLMetaElement& metaElement)
3860{
3861 // If the current content color isn't valid and it wasn't previously in the list of elements
3862 // with a valid content color, don't bother recalculating `m_metaThemeColorElements`.
3863 if (!metaElement.contentColor().isValid() && m_metaThemeColorElements && !m_metaThemeColorElements->contains(&metaElement))
3864 return;
3865
3866 auto oldThemeColor = std::exchange(m_cachedThemeColor, Color());
3867 m_metaThemeColorElements = std::nullopt;
3868 m_activeThemeColorMetaElement = nullptr;
3869 if (themeColor() == oldThemeColor)
3870 return;
3871
3872 themeColorChanged();
3873}
3874
3875WeakPtr<HTMLMetaElement> Document::determineActiveThemeColorMetaElement()
3876{
3877 if (!m_metaThemeColorElements) {
3878 Vector<WeakPtr<HTMLMetaElement>> metaThemeColorElements;
3879 for (auto& metaElement : descendantsOfType<HTMLMetaElement>(*this)) {
3880 if (equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(metaElement.name(), "theme-color") && metaElement.contentColor().isValid())
3881 metaThemeColorElements.append(makeWeakPtr(metaElement));
3882 }
3883 m_metaThemeColorElements = WTFMove(metaThemeColorElements);
3884 }
3885
3886 for (auto& metaElement : *m_metaThemeColorElements) {
3887 if (metaElement && metaElement->contentColor().isValid() && metaElement->mediaAttributeMatches())
3888 return metaElement;
3889 }
3890 return nullptr;
3891}
3892
3893void Document::themeColorChanged()
3894{
3895 scheduleRenderingUpdate({ });
3896
3897 if (auto* page = this->page())
3898 page->chrome().client().themeColorChanged();
3899}

3901#if ENABLE(DARK_MODE_CSS)
3902static void processColorSchemeString(StringView colorScheme, const WTF::Function<void(StringView key)>& callback)
3903{
3904 unsigned length = colorScheme.length();
3905 for (unsigned i = 0; i < length; ) {
3906 // Skip to first non-separator.
3907 while (i < length && isHTMLSpace(colorScheme[i]))
3908 ++i;
3909 unsigned keyBegin = i;
3910
3911 // Skip to first separator.
3912 while (i < length && !isHTMLSpace(colorScheme[i]))
3913 ++i;
3914 unsigned keyEnd = i;
3915
3916 if (keyBegin == keyEnd)
3917 continue;
3918
3919 callback(colorScheme.substring(keyBegin, keyEnd - keyBegin));
3920 }
3921}
3922
3923void Document::processColorScheme(const String& colorSchemeString)
3924{
3925 OptionSet<ColorScheme> colorScheme;
3926 bool allowsTransformations = true;
3927 bool autoEncountered = false;
3928
3929 processColorSchemeString(colorSchemeString, [&] (StringView key) {
3930 if (equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(key, "auto")) {
3931 colorScheme = { };
3932 allowsTransformations = true;
3933 autoEncountered = true;
3934 return;
3935 }
3936
3937 if (autoEncountered)
3938 return;
3939
3940 if (equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(key, "light"))
3941 colorScheme.add(ColorScheme::Light);
3942 else if (equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(key, "dark"))
3943 colorScheme.add(ColorScheme::Dark);
3944 else if (equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(key, "only"))
3945 allowsTransformations = false;
3946 });
3947
3948 // If the value was just "only", that is synonymous for "only light".
3949 if (colorScheme.isEmpty() && !allowsTransformations)
3950 colorScheme.add(ColorScheme::Light);
3951
3952 m_colorScheme = colorScheme;
3953 m_allowsColorSchemeTransformations = allowsTransformations;
3954
3955 if (auto* frameView = view())
3956 frameView->recalculateBaseBackgroundColor();
3957
3958 if (auto* page = this->page())
3959 page->updateStyleAfterChangeInEnvironment();
3960}
3961#endif

3970 m_isTelephoneNumberParsingAllowed = false;

3981
3982void Document::processReferrerPolicy(const String& policy, ReferrerPolicySource source)
3983{
3984 ASSERT(!policy.isNull());
3985
3986 // Documents in a Content-Disposition: attachment sandbox should never send a Referer header,
3987 // even if the document has a meta tag saying otherwise.
3988 if (shouldEnforceContentDispositionAttachmentSandbox())
3989 return;
3990
3991#if USE(QUICK_LOOK)
3992 if (shouldEnforceQuickLookSandbox())
3993 return;
3994#endif
3995
3996 auto referrerPolicy = parseReferrerPolicy(policy, source);
3997 if (!referrerPolicy) {
3998 // Unknown policy values are ignored (https://w3c.github.io/webappsec-referrer-policy/#unknown-policy-values).
3999 addConsoleMessage(MessageSource::Rendering, MessageLevel::Error, "Failed to set referrer policy: The value '" + policy + "' is not one of 'no-referrer', 'no-referrer-when-downgrade', 'same-origin', 'origin', 'strict-origin', 'origin-when-cross-origin', 'strict-origin-when-cross-origin' or 'unsafe-url'.");
4000 return;
4001 }
4002 setReferrerPolicy(referrerPolicy.value());
4003}

4008{

4010 m_applicationManifestThemeColor = applicationManifest.themeColor;
4011 if (themeColor() == oldThemeColor)
4012 return;
4013
4014 themeColorChanged();
4015}

4018
4019MouseEventWithHitTestResults Document::prepareMouseEvent(const HitTestRequest& request, const LayoutPoint& documentPoint, const PlatformMouseEvent& event)
4020{
4021 if (!hasLivingRenderTree())
4022 return MouseEventWithHitTestResults(event, HitTestResult(LayoutPoint()));
4023
4024 HitTestResult result(documentPoint);
4025 hitTest(request, result);
4026
4027 auto captureElementChanged = CaptureChange::No;
4028 if (!request.readOnly()) {
4029 auto targetElement = makeRefPtr(result.targetElement());
4030 if (auto* page = this->page()) {
4031 // Before we dispatch a new mouse event, we must run the Process Pending Capture Element steps as defined
4032 // in https://w3c.github.io/pointerevents/#process-pending-pointer-capture.
4033 auto& pointerCaptureController = page->pointerCaptureController();
4034 auto* previousCaptureElement = pointerCaptureController.pointerCaptureElement(this, event.pointerId());
4035 pointerCaptureController.processPendingPointerCapture(event.pointerId());
4036 auto* captureElement = pointerCaptureController.pointerCaptureElement(this, event.pointerId());
4037 // If the capture element has changed while running the Process Pending Capture Element steps then
4038 // we need to indicate that when calling updateHoverActiveState to be sure that the :active and :hover
4039 // element chains are updated.
4040 if (previousCaptureElement != captureElement)
4041 captureElementChanged = CaptureChange::Yes;
4042 // If we have a capture element, we must target it instead of what would normally hit-test for this event.
4043 if (captureElement)
4044 targetElement = captureElement;
4045 }
4046 updateHoverActiveState(request, targetElement.get(), captureElementChanged);
4047 }
4048
4049 return MouseEventWithHitTestResults(event, result);
4050}
4051
4052// DOM Section 1.1.1
4053bool Document::childTypeAllowed(NodeType type) const
4054{
4055 switch (type) {
4056 case ATTRIBUTE_NODE:
4057 case CDATA_SECTION_NODE:
4058 case DOCUMENT_FRAGMENT_NODE:
4059 case DOCUMENT_NODE:
4060 case TEXT_NODE:
4061 return false;
4062 case COMMENT_NODE:
4063 case PROCESSING_INSTRUCTION_NODE:
4064 return true;
4065 case DOCUMENT_TYPE_NODE:
4066 case ELEMENT_NODE:
4067 // Documents may contain no more than one of each of these.
4068 // (One Element and one DocumentType.)
4069 for (Node* c = firstChild(); c; c = c->nextSibling())
4070 if (c->nodeType() == type)
4071 return false;
4072 return true;
4073 }
4074 return false;
4075}
4076
4077bool Document::canAcceptChild(const Node& newChild, const Node* refChild, AcceptChildOperation operation) const
4078{
4079 if (operation == AcceptChildOperation::Replace && refChild->parentNode() == this && refChild->nodeType() == newChild.nodeType())
4080 return true;
4081
4082 switch (newChild.nodeType()) {
4083 case ATTRIBUTE_NODE:
4084 case CDATA_SECTION_NODE:
4085 case DOCUMENT_NODE:
4086 case TEXT_NODE:
4087 return false;
4088 case COMMENT_NODE:
4089 case PROCESSING_INSTRUCTION_NODE:
4090 return true;
4091 case DOCUMENT_FRAGMENT_NODE: {
4092 bool hasSeenElementChild = false;
4093 for (auto* node = downcast<DocumentFragment>(newChild).firstChild(); node; node = node->nextSibling()) {
4094 if (is<Element>(*node)) {
4095 if (hasSeenElementChild)
4096 return false;
4097 hasSeenElementChild = true;
4098 }
4099 if (!canAcceptChild(*node, refChild, operation))
4100 return false;
4101 }
4102 break;
4103 }
4104 case DOCUMENT_TYPE_NODE: {
4105 auto* existingDocType = childrenOfType<DocumentType>(*this).first();
4106 if (operation == AcceptChildOperation::Replace) {
4107 // parent has a doctype child that is not child, or an element is preceding child.
4108 if (existingDocType && existingDocType != refChild)
4109 return false;
4110 if (refChild->previousElementSibling())
4111 return false;
4112 } else {
4113 ASSERT(operation == AcceptChildOperation::InsertOrAdd);
4114 if (existingDocType)
4115 return false;
4116 if ((refChild && refChild->previousElementSibling()) || (!refChild && firstElementChild()))
4117 return false;
4118 }
4119 break;
4120 }
4121 case ELEMENT_NODE: {
4122 auto* existingElementChild = firstElementChild();
4123 if (operation == AcceptChildOperation::Replace) {
4124 if (existingElementChild && existingElementChild != refChild)
4125 return false;
4126 for (auto* child = refChild->nextSibling(); child; child = child->nextSibling()) {
4127 if (is<DocumentType>(*child))
4128 return false;
4129 }
4130 } else {
4131 ASSERT(operation == AcceptChildOperation::InsertOrAdd);
4132 if (existingElementChild)
4133 return false;
4134 for (auto* child = refChild; child; child = child->nextSibling()) {
4135 if (is<DocumentType>(*child))
4136 return false;
4137 }
4138 }
4139 break;
4140 }
4141 }
4142 return true;
4143}
4144
4145Ref<Node> Document::cloneNodeInternal(Document&, CloningOperation type)
4146{
4147 Ref<Document> clone = cloneDocumentWithoutChildren();
4148 clone->cloneDataFromDocument(*this);
4149 switch (type) {
4150 case CloningOperation::OnlySelf:
4151 case CloningOperation::SelfWithTemplateContent:
4152 break;
4153 case CloningOperation::Everything:
4154 cloneChildNodes(clone);
4155 break;
4156 }
4157 return clone;
4158}
4159
4160Ref<Document> Document::cloneDocumentWithoutChildren() const
4161{
4162 if (isXMLDocument()) {
4163 if (isXHTMLDocument())
4164 return XMLDocument::createXHTML(nullptr, m_settings, url());
4165 return XMLDocument::create(nullptr, m_settings, url());
4166 }
4167 return create(m_settings, url());
4168}

4193 ScriptDisallowedScope::InMainThread scriptDisallowedScope;

4247// https://drafts.csswg.org/cssom-view/#run-the-resize-steps
4248void Document::runResizeSteps()
4249{
4250 // FIXME: The order of dispatching is not specified: https://github.com/WICG/visual-viewport/issues/65.
4251 if (m_needsDOMWindowResizeEvent) {
4252 LOG_WITH_STREAM(Events, stream << "Document " << this << " sending resize events to window");
4253 m_needsDOMWindowResizeEvent = false;
4254 dispatchWindowEvent(Event::create(eventNames().resizeEvent, Event::CanBubble::No, Event::IsCancelable::No));
4255 }
4256 if (m_needsVisualViewportResizeEvent) {
4257 LOG_WITH_STREAM(Events, stream << "Document " << this << " sending resize events to visualViewport");
4258 m_needsVisualViewportResizeEvent = false;
4259 if (auto* window = domWindow())
4260 window->visualViewport().dispatchEvent(Event::create(eventNames().resizeEvent, Event::CanBubble::No, Event::IsCancelable::No));
4261 }
4262}
4263
4264void Document::addPendingScrollEventTarget(ContainerNode& target)
4265{
4266 if (!m_pendingScrollEventTargetList)
4267 m_pendingScrollEventTargetList = makeUnique<PendingScrollEventTargetList>();
4268
4269 auto& targets = m_pendingScrollEventTargetList->targets;
4270 if (targets.findMatching([&] (auto& entry) { return entry.ptr() == &target; }) != notFound)
4271 return;
4272
4273 if (targets.isEmpty())
4274 scheduleRenderingUpdate(RenderingUpdateStep::Scroll);
4275
4276 targets.append(target);
4277}
4278
4279void Document::setNeedsVisualViewportScrollEvent()
4280{
4281 if (!m_needsVisualViewportScrollEvent)
4282 scheduleRenderingUpdate(RenderingUpdateStep::Scroll);
4283 m_needsVisualViewportScrollEvent = true;
4284}
4285
4286// https://drafts.csswg.org/cssom-view/#run-the-scroll-steps
4287void Document::runScrollSteps()
4288{
4289 // FIXME: The order of dispatching is not specified: https://github.com/WICG/visual-viewport/issues/66.
4290 if (m_pendingScrollEventTargetList && !m_pendingScrollEventTargetList->targets.isEmpty()) {
4291 LOG_WITH_STREAM(Events, stream << "Document " << this << " sending scroll events to pending scroll event targets");
4292 auto currentTargets = WTFMove(m_pendingScrollEventTargetList->targets);
4293 for (auto& target : currentTargets) {
4294 auto bubbles = target->isDocumentNode() ? Event::CanBubble::Yes : Event::CanBubble::No;
4295 target->dispatchEvent(Event::create(eventNames().scrollEvent, bubbles, Event::IsCancelable::No));
4296 }
4297 }
4298 if (m_needsVisualViewportScrollEvent) {
4299 LOG_WITH_STREAM(Events, stream << "Document " << this << " sending scroll events to visualViewport");
4300 m_needsVisualViewportScrollEvent = false;
4301 if (auto* window = domWindow())
4302 window->visualViewport().dispatchEvent(Event::create(eventNames().scrollEvent, Event::CanBubble::No, Event::IsCancelable::No));
4303 }
4304}

4345
4346void Document::updateIsPlayingMedia()
4347{
4348 ASSERT(!m_audioProducers.hasNullReferences());
4349 MediaProducer::MediaStateFlags state;
4350 for (auto& audioProducer : m_audioProducers)
4351 state.add(audioProducer.mediaState());
4352
4353#if ENABLE(MEDIA_STREAM)
4354 state.add(MediaStreamTrack::captureState(*this));
4355 if (m_activeSpeechRecognition)
4356 state.add(MediaProducer::MediaState::HasActiveAudioCaptureDevice);
4357#endif
4358
4359 if (m_userHasInteractedWithMediaElement)
4360 state.add(MediaProducer::MediaState::HasUserInteractedWithMediaElement);
4361
4362 if (state == m_mediaState)
4363 return;
4364
4365#if ENABLE(MEDIA_STREAM)
4366 bool captureStateChanged = MediaProducer::isCapturing(m_mediaState) != MediaProducer::isCapturing(state);
4367#endif
4368
4369 m_mediaState = state;
4370
4371 if (auto* page = this->page())
4372 page->updateIsPlayingMedia();
4373
4374#if ENABLE(MEDIA_STREAM)
4375 if (captureStateChanged)
4376 mediaStreamCaptureStateChanged();
4377#endif
4378}

4390static bool isNodeInSubtree(Node& node, Node& container, Document::NodeRemoval nodeRemoval)
4391{
4392 if (nodeRemoval == Document::NodeRemoval::ChildrenOfNode)
4393 return node.isDescendantOf(container);
4394
4395 return &node == &container || node.isDescendantOf(container);
4396}
4397
4398void Document::adjustFocusedNodeOnNodeRemoval(Node& node, NodeRemoval nodeRemoval)
4399{
4400 if (!m_focusedElement || backForwardCacheState() != NotInBackForwardCache) // If the document is in the back/forward cache, then we don't need to clear out the focused node.
4401 return;
4402
4403 Element* focusedElement = node.treeScope().focusedElementInScope();
4404 if (!focusedElement)
4405 return;
4406
4407 if (isNodeInSubtree(*focusedElement, node, nodeRemoval)) {
4408 // FIXME: We should avoid synchronously updating the style inside setFocusedElement.
4409 // FIXME: Object elements should avoid loading a frame synchronously in a post style recalc callback.
4410 SubframeLoadingDisabler disabler(is<ContainerNode>(node) ? &downcast<ContainerNode>(node) : nullptr);
4411 setFocusedElement(nullptr, { { }, { }, FocusRemovalEventsMode::DoNotDispatch, { }, { } });
4412 // Set the focus navigation starting node to the previous focused element so that
4413 // we can fallback to the siblings or parent node for the next search.
4414 // Also we need to call removeFocusNavigationNodeOfSubtree after this function because
4415 // setFocusedElement(nullptr) will reset m_focusNavigationStartingNode.
4416 setFocusNavigationStartingNode(focusedElement);
4417 }
4418}
4419
4420void Document::hoveredElementDidDetach(Element& element)
4421{
4422 if (!m_hoveredElement || &element != m_hoveredElement)
4423 return;
4424
4425 m_hoveredElement = element.parentElement();
4426 while (m_hoveredElement && !m_hoveredElement->renderer())
4427 m_hoveredElement = m_hoveredElement->parentElement();
4428 if (frame())
4429 frame()->eventHandler().scheduleHoverStateUpdate();
4430}
4431
4432void Document::elementInActiveChainDidDetach(Element& element)
4433{
4434 if (!m_activeElement || &element != m_activeElement)
4435 return;
4436
4437 m_activeElement = element.parentElement();
4438 while (m_activeElement && !m_activeElement->renderer())
4439 m_activeElement = m_activeElement->parentElement();
4440}

4459 }
4460 if (auto* ownerElement = this->ownerElement())
4461 ownerElement->document().invalidateEventRegionsForFrame(*ownerElement);
4462}

4464void Document::invalidateEventListenerRegions()
4465{
4466 if (!renderView() || !documentElement())
4467 return;
4468
4469 // We don't track style validity for Document and full rebuild is too big of a hammer.
4470 // Instead just mutate the style directly and trigger a minimal style update.
4471 auto& rootStyle = renderView()->mutableStyle();
4472 Style::Adjuster::adjustEventListenerRegionTypesForRootStyle(rootStyle, *this);
4473
4474 documentElement()->invalidateStyleInternal();
4475}

4481#endif
4482

4487 scrollingCoordinator->frameViewEventTrackingRegionsChanged(*frameView);
4488 }
4489 }
4490#endif
4491}
4492
4493bool Document::setFocusedElement(Element* element, const FocusOptions& options)
4494{
4495 RefPtr<Element> newFocusedElement = element;
4496 // Make sure newFocusedElement is actually in this document
4497 if (newFocusedElement && (&newFocusedElement->document() != this))
4498 return true;
4499
4500 if (m_focusedElement == newFocusedElement)
4501 return true;
4502
4503 if (backForwardCacheState() != NotInBackForwardCache)
4504 return false;
4505
4506 RefPtr<Element> oldFocusedElement = WTFMove(m_focusedElement);
4507
4508 // Remove focus from the existing focus node (if any)
4509 if (oldFocusedElement) {
4510 bool focusChangeBlocked = false;
4511
4512 oldFocusedElement->setFocus(false);
4513 setFocusNavigationStartingNode(nullptr);
4514
4515 if (options.removalEventsMode == FocusRemovalEventsMode::Dispatch) {
4516 // Dispatch a change event for form control elements that have been edited.
4517 if (is<HTMLFormControlElement>(*oldFocusedElement)) {
4518 HTMLFormControlElement& formControlElement = downcast<HTMLFormControlElement>(*oldFocusedElement);
4519 if (formControlElement.wasChangedSinceLastFormControlChangeEvent())
4520 formControlElement.dispatchFormControlChangeEvent();
4521 }
4522
4523 // Dispatch the blur event and let the node do any other blur related activities (important for text fields)
4524 oldFocusedElement->dispatchBlurEvent(newFocusedElement.copyRef());
4525
4526 if (m_focusedElement) {
4527 // handler shifted focus
4528 focusChangeBlocked = true;
4529 newFocusedElement = nullptr;
4530 }
4531
4532 oldFocusedElement->dispatchFocusOutEvent(eventNames().focusoutEvent, newFocusedElement.copyRef()); // DOM level 3 name for the bubbling blur event.
4533 // FIXME: We should remove firing DOMFocusOutEvent event when we are sure no content depends
4534 // on it, probably when <rdar://problem/8503958> is resolved.
4535 oldFocusedElement->dispatchFocusOutEvent(eventNames().DOMFocusOutEvent, newFocusedElement.copyRef()); // DOM level 2 name for compatibility.
4536
4537 if (m_focusedElement) {
4538 // handler shifted focus
4539 focusChangeBlocked = true;
4540 newFocusedElement = nullptr;
4541 }
4542 } else {
4543 // Match the order in HTMLTextFormControlElement::dispatchBlurEvent.
4544 if (is<HTMLInputElement>(*oldFocusedElement))
4545 downcast<HTMLInputElement>(*oldFocusedElement).endEditing();
4546 if (page())
4547 page()->chrome().client().elementDidBlur(*oldFocusedElement);
4548 ASSERT(!m_focusedElement);
4549 }
4550
4551 if (oldFocusedElement->isRootEditableElement())
4552 editor().didEndEditing();
4553
4554 if (view()) {
4555 if (Widget* oldWidget = widgetForElement(oldFocusedElement.get()))
4556 oldWidget->setFocus(false);
4557 else
4558 view()->setFocus(false);
4559 }
4560
4561 if (is<HTMLInputElement>(oldFocusedElement)) {
4562 // HTMLInputElement::didBlur just scrolls text fields back to the beginning.
4563 // FIXME: This could be done asynchronusly.
4564 downcast<HTMLInputElement>(*oldFocusedElement).didBlur();
4565 }
4566
4567 if (focusChangeBlocked)
4568 return false;
4569 }
4570
4571 if (newFocusedElement && newFocusedElement->isFocusable()) {
4572 if (&newFocusedElement->document() != this) {
4573 // Bluring oldFocusedElement may have moved newFocusedElement across documents.
4574 return false;
4575 }
4576 if (newFocusedElement->isRootEditableElement() && !acceptsEditingFocus(*newFocusedElement)) {
4577 // delegate blocks focus change
4578 return false;
4579 }
4580 // Set focus on the new node
4581 m_focusedElement = newFocusedElement;
4582 setFocusNavigationStartingNode(m_focusedElement.get());
4583 m_focusedElement->setFocus(true, options.visibility);
4584 m_latestFocusTrigger = options.trigger;
4585
4586 // The setFocus call triggers a blur and a focus event. Event handlers could cause the focused element to be cleared.
4587 if (m_focusedElement != newFocusedElement) {
4588 // handler shifted focus
4589 return false;
4590 }
4591
4592 // Dispatch the focus event and let the node do any other focus related activities (important for text fields)
4593 m_focusedElement->dispatchFocusEvent(oldFocusedElement.copyRef(), options.direction);
4594
4595 if (m_focusedElement != newFocusedElement) {
4596 // handler shifted focus
4597 return false;
4598 }
4599
4600 m_focusedElement->dispatchFocusInEvent(eventNames().focusinEvent, oldFocusedElement.copyRef()); // DOM level 3 bubbling focus event.
4601
4602 if (m_focusedElement != newFocusedElement) {
4603 // handler shifted focus
4604 return false;
4605 }
4606
4607 // FIXME: We should remove firing DOMFocusInEvent event when we are sure no content depends
4608 // on it, probably when <rdar://problem/8503958> is m.
4609 m_focusedElement->dispatchFocusInEvent(eventNames().DOMFocusInEvent, oldFocusedElement.copyRef()); // DOM level 2 for compatibility.
4610
4611 if (m_focusedElement != newFocusedElement) {
4612 // handler shifted focus
4613 return false;
4614 }
4615
4616 if (m_focusedElement->isRootEditableElement())
4617 editor().didBeginEditing();
4618
4619 // eww, I suck. set the qt focus correctly
4620 // ### find a better place in the code for this
4621 if (view()) {
4622 Widget* focusWidget = widgetForElement(m_focusedElement.get());
4623 if (focusWidget) {
4624 // Make sure a widget has the right size before giving it focus.
4625 // Otherwise, we are testing edge cases of the Widget code.
4626 // Specifically, in WebCore this does not work well for text fields.
4627 updateLayout();
4628 // Re-get the widget in case updating the layout changed things.
4629 focusWidget = widgetForElement(m_focusedElement.get());
4630 }
4631 if (focusWidget)
4632 focusWidget->setFocus(true);
4633 else if (auto* frameView = view())
4634 frameView->setFocus(true);
4635 }
4636 }
4637
4638 if (m_focusedElement) {
4639 // Create the AXObject cache in a focus change because GTK relies on it.
4640 if (AXObjectCache* cache = axObjectCache())
4641 cache->deferFocusedUIElementChangeIfNeeded(oldFocusedElement.get(), newFocusedElement.get());
4642 }
4643
4644 if (page())
4645 page()->chrome().focusedElementChanged(m_focusedElement.get());
4646
4647 return true;
4648}
4649
4650static bool shouldResetFocusNavigationStartingNode(Node& node)
4651{
4652 // Setting focus navigation starting node to the following nodes means that we should start
4653 // the search from the beginning of the document.
4654 return is<HTMLHtmlElement>(node) || is<HTMLDocument>(node);
4655}
4656
4657void Document::setFocusNavigationStartingNode(Node* node)
4658{
4659 if (!m_frame)
4660 return;
4661
4662 m_focusNavigationStartingNodeIsRemoved = false;
4663 if (!node || shouldResetFocusNavigationStartingNode(*node)) {
4664 m_focusNavigationStartingNode = nullptr;
4665 return;
4666 }
4667
4668 ASSERT(!node || node != this);
4669 m_focusNavigationStartingNode = node;
4670}
4671
4672Element* Document::focusNavigationStartingNode(FocusDirection direction) const
4673{
4674 if (m_focusedElement) {
4675 if (!m_focusNavigationStartingNode || !m_focusNavigationStartingNode->isDescendantOf(m_focusedElement.get()))
4676 return m_focusedElement.get();
4677 }
4678
4679 if (!m_focusNavigationStartingNode)
4680 return nullptr;
4681
4682 Node* node = m_focusNavigationStartingNode.get();
4683
4684 // When the node was removed from the document tree. This case is not specified in the spec:
4685 // https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/interaction.html#sequential-focus-navigation-starting-point
4686 // Current behaivor is to move the sequential navigation node to / after (based on the focus direction)
4687 // the previous sibling of the removed node.
4688 if (m_focusNavigationStartingNodeIsRemoved) {
4689 Node* nextNode = NodeTraversal::next(*node);
4690 if (!nextNode)
4691 nextNode = node;
4692 if (direction == FocusDirection::Forward)
4693 return ElementTraversal::previous(*nextNode);
4694 if (is<Element>(*nextNode))
4695 return downcast<Element>(nextNode);
4696 return ElementTraversal::next(*nextNode);
4697 }
4698
4699 if (is<Element>(*node))
4700 return downcast<Element>(node);
4701 if (Element* elementBeforeNextFocusableElement = direction == FocusDirection::Forward ? ElementTraversal::previous(*node) : ElementTraversal::next(*node))
4702 return elementBeforeNextFocusableElement;
4703 return node->parentOrShadowHostElement();
4704}
4705
4706void Document::setCSSTarget(Element* targetNode)
4707{
4708 if (m_cssTarget)
4709 m_cssTarget->invalidateStyleForSubtree();
4710 m_cssTarget = targetNode;
4711 if (targetNode)
4712 targetNode->invalidateStyleForSubtree();
4713}

4715void Document::registerNodeListForInvalidation(LiveNodeList& list)
4716{
4717 m_nodeListAndCollectionCounts[list.invalidationType()]++;
4718 if (!list.isRootedAtDocument())
4719 return;
4720 ASSERT(!list.isRegisteredForInvalidationAtDocument());
4721 list.setRegisteredForInvalidationAtDocument(true);
4722 m_listsInvalidatedAtDocument.add(&list);
4723}
4724
4725void Document::unregisterNodeListForInvalidation(LiveNodeList& list)
4726{
4727 m_nodeListAndCollectionCounts[list.invalidationType()]--;
4728 if (!list.isRegisteredForInvalidationAtDocument())
4729 return;
4730
4731 list.setRegisteredForInvalidationAtDocument(false);
4732 ASSERT(m_listsInvalidatedAtDocument.contains(&list));
4733 m_listsInvalidatedAtDocument.remove(&list);
4734}

4770
4771void Document::detachNodeIterator(NodeIterator& iterator)
4772{
4773 // The node iterator can be detached without having been attached if its root node didn't have a document
4774 // when the iterator was created, but has it now.
4775 m_nodeIterators.remove(&iterator);
4776}
4777
4778void Document::moveNodeIteratorsToNewDocumentSlowCase(Node& node, Document& newDocument)
4779{
4780 ASSERT(!m_nodeIterators.isEmpty());
4781 for (auto* iterator : copyToVector(m_nodeIterators)) {
4782 if (&iterator->root() == &node) {
4783 detachNodeIterator(*iterator);
4784 newDocument.attachNodeIterator(*iterator);
4785 }
4786 }
4787}
4788
4789void Document::updateRangesAfterChildrenChanged(ContainerNode& container)
4790{
4791 for (auto* range : m_ranges)
4792 range->nodeChildrenChanged(container);
4793}
4794
4795void Document::nodeChildrenWillBeRemoved(ContainerNode& container)
4796{
4797 ASSERT(ScriptDisallowedScope::InMainThread::hasDisallowedScope());
4798
4799 adjustFocusedNodeOnNodeRemoval(container, NodeRemoval::ChildrenOfNode);
4800 adjustFocusNavigationNodeOnNodeRemoval(container, NodeRemoval::ChildrenOfNode);
4801
4802#if ENABLE(FULLSCREEN_API)
4803 m_fullscreenManager->adjustFullscreenElementOnNodeRemoval(container, NodeRemoval::ChildrenOfNode);
4804#endif
4805
4806 for (auto* range : m_ranges)
4807 range->nodeChildrenWillBeRemoved(container);
4808
4809 for (auto* it : m_nodeIterators) {
4810 for (Node* n = container.firstChild(); n; n = n->nextSibling())
4811 it->nodeWillBeRemoved(*n);
4812 }
4813
4814 if (RefPtr<Frame> frame = this->frame()) {
4815 for (Node* n = container.firstChild(); n; n = n->nextSibling()) {
4816 frame->eventHandler().nodeWillBeRemoved(*n);
4817 frame->selection().nodeWillBeRemoved(*n);
4818 frame->page()->dragCaretController().nodeWillBeRemoved(*n);
4819 }
4820 }
4821
4822 if (m_markers->hasMarkers()) {
4823 for (Text* textNode = TextNodeTraversal::firstChild(container); textNode; textNode = TextNodeTraversal::nextSibling(*textNode))
4824 m_markers->removeMarkers(*textNode);
4825 }
4826}
4827
4828void Document::nodeWillBeRemoved(Node& node)
4829{
4830 ASSERT(ScriptDisallowedScope::InMainThread::hasDisallowedScope());
4831
4832 adjustFocusedNodeOnNodeRemoval(node);
4833 adjustFocusNavigationNodeOnNodeRemoval(node);
4834
4835#if ENABLE(FULLSCREEN_API)
4836 m_fullscreenManager->adjustFullscreenElementOnNodeRemoval(node, NodeRemoval::Node);
4837#endif
4838
4839 for (auto* it : m_nodeIterators)
4840 it->nodeWillBeRemoved(node);
4841
4842 for (auto* range : m_ranges)
4843 range->nodeWillBeRemoved(node);
4844
4845 if (RefPtr<Frame> frame = this->frame()) {
4846 frame->eventHandler().nodeWillBeRemoved(node);
4847 frame->selection().nodeWillBeRemoved(node);
4848 frame->page()->dragCaretController().nodeWillBeRemoved(node);
4849 }
4850
4851 if (is<Text>(node))
4852 m_markers->removeMarkers(node);
4853}
4854
4855void Document::parentlessNodeMovedToNewDocument(Node& node)
4856{
4857 Vector<Range*, 5> rangesAffected;
4858
4859 for (auto* range : m_ranges) {
4860 if (range->parentlessNodeMovedToNewDocumentAffectsRange(node))
4861 rangesAffected.append(range);
4862 }
4863
4864 for (auto* range : rangesAffected)
4865 range->updateRangeForParentlessNodeMovedToNewDocument(node);
4866}
4867
4868static Node* fallbackFocusNavigationStartingNodeAfterRemoval(Node& node)
4869{
4870 return node.previousSibling() ? node.previousSibling() : node.parentNode();
4871}
4872
4873void Document::adjustFocusNavigationNodeOnNodeRemoval(Node& node, NodeRemoval nodeRemoval)
4874{
4875 if (!m_focusNavigationStartingNode)
4876 return;
4877
4878 if (isNodeInSubtree(*m_focusNavigationStartingNode, node, nodeRemoval)) {
4879 auto* newNode = (nodeRemoval == NodeRemoval::ChildrenOfNode) ? &node : fallbackFocusNavigationStartingNodeAfterRemoval(node);
4880 m_focusNavigationStartingNode = (newNode != this) ? newNode : nullptr;
4881 m_focusNavigationStartingNodeIsRemoved = true;
4882 }
4883}

4885void Document::textInserted(Node& text, unsigned offset, unsigned length)
4886{
4887 if (!m_ranges.isEmpty()) {
4888 for (auto* range : m_ranges)
4889 range->textInserted(text, offset, length);
4890 }
4891
4892 // Update the markers for spelling and grammar checking.
4893 m_markers->shiftMarkers(text, offset, length);
4894
4895#if ENABLE(PLATFORM_DRIVEN_TEXT_CHECKING)
4896 // Freshly inserted text is expected to not inherit PlatformTextChecking markers.
4897 m_markers->removeMarkers(text, { offset, offset + length }, DocumentMarker::PlatformTextChecking);
4898#endif
4899}

4901void Document::textRemoved(Node& text, unsigned offset, unsigned length)
4902{
4903 if (!m_ranges.isEmpty()) {
4904 for (auto* range : m_ranges)
4905 range->textRemoved(text, offset, length);
4906 }
4907
4908 // Update the markers for spelling and grammar checking.
4909 m_markers->removeMarkers(text, { offset, offset + length });
4910 m_markers->shiftMarkers(text, offset + length, 0 - length);
4911}

4922}

5036void Document::enqueueOverflowEvent(Ref<Event>&& event)
5037{
5038 // https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/Element/overflow_event
5039 // FIXME: This event is totally unspecified.
5040 auto* target = event->target();
5041 RELEASE_ASSERT(target);
5042 RELEASE_ASSERT(is<Node>(target));
5043 eventLoop().queueTask(TaskSource::DOMManipulation, [protectedTarget = GCReachableRef<Node>(downcast<Node>(*target)), event = WTFMove(event)] {
5044 protectedTarget->dispatchEvent(event);
5045 });
5046}
5047
5048ExceptionOr<Ref<Event>> Document::createEvent(const String& type)
5049{
5050 // Please do *not* add new event classes to this function unless they are required
5051 // for compatibility with the DOM specification or some actual legacy web content.
5052
5053 // This mechanism is superseded by use of event constructors.
5054 // That is what we should use for any new event classes.
5055
5056 // The following strings are the ones from the DOM specification
5057 // <https://dom.spec.whatwg.org/#dom-document-createevent>.
5058
5059 if (equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(type, "beforeunloadevent"))
5060 return Ref<Event> { BeforeUnloadEvent::createForBindings() };
5061 if (equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(type, "compositionevent"))
5062 return Ref<Event> { CompositionEvent::createForBindings() };
5063 if (equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(type, "customevent"))
5064 return Ref<Event> { CustomEvent::create() };
5065 if (equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(type, "dragevent"))
5066 return Ref<Event> { DragEvent::createForBindings() };
5067 if (equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(type, "event") || equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(type, "events") || equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(type, "htmlevents") || equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(type, "svgevents"))
5068 return Event::createForBindings();
5069 if (equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(type, "focusevent"))
5070 return Ref<Event> { FocusEvent::createForBindings() };
5071 if (equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(type, "hashchangeevent"))
5072 return Ref<Event> { HashChangeEvent::createForBindings() };
5073 if (equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(type, "keyboardevent"))
5074 return Ref<Event> { KeyboardEvent::createForBindings() };
5075 if (equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(type, "messageevent"))
5076 return Ref<Event> { MessageEvent::createForBindings() };
5077 if (equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(type, "storageevent"))
5078 return Ref<Event> { StorageEvent::createForBindings() };
5079 if (equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(type, "mouseevent") || equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(type, "mouseevents"))
5080 return Ref<Event> { MouseEvent::createForBindings() };
5081 if (equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(type, "textevent"))
5082 return Ref<Event> { TextEvent::createForBindings() }; // FIXME: HTML specification says this should create a CompositionEvent, not a TextEvent.
5083 if (equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(type, "uievent") || equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(type, "uievents"))
5084 return Ref<Event> { UIEvent::createForBindings() };
5085
5086 // FIXME: Consider including support for these event classes even when device orientation
5087 // support is not enabled.
5088#if ENABLE(DEVICE_ORIENTATION)
5089 if (equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(type, "devicemotionevent"))
5090 return Ref<Event> { DeviceMotionEvent::createForBindings() };
5091 if (equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(type, "deviceorientationevent"))
5092 return Ref<Event> { DeviceOrientationEvent::createForBindings() };
5093#endif
5094
5095#if ENABLE(TOUCH_EVENTS)
5096 if (equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(type, "touchevent"))
5097 return Ref<Event> { TouchEvent::createForBindings() };
5098#endif
5099
5100 // FIXME: Add support for "dragevent", which the DOM specification calls for.
5101
5102 // The following string comes from the SVG specification
5103 // <http://www.w3.org/TR/SVG/script.html#InterfaceSVGZoomEvent>
5104 // However, since there is no provision for initializing the event once it is created,
5105 // there is no practical value in this feature.
5106 // FIXME: Confirm there is no content depending on this and remove it.
5107
5108 if (equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(type, "svgzoomevents"))
5109 return Ref<Event> { SVGZoomEvent::createForBindings() };
5110
5111 // The following strings are not part of the DOM specification and we would like to eliminate them.
5112 // However, we currently include them until we resolve any issues with backward compatibility.
5113 // FIXME: For each of the strings below, confirm that there is no content depending on it and remove
5114 // the string, remove the createForBindings function, and also consider removing the corresponding
5115 // init function for that class.
5116
5117 if (equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(type, "keyboardevents"))
5118 return Ref<Event> { KeyboardEvent::createForBindings() };
5119 if (equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(type, "mutationevent") || equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(type, "mutationevents"))
5120 return Ref<Event> { MutationEvent::createForBindings() };
5121 if (equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(type, "overflowevent"))
5122 return Ref<Event> { OverflowEvent::createForBindings() };
5123 if (equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(type, "popstateevent"))
5124 return Ref<Event> { PopStateEvent::createForBindings() };
5125 if (equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(type, "wheelevent"))
5126 return Ref<Event> { WheelEvent::createForBindings() };
5127
5128 return Exception { NotSupportedError };
5129}
5130
5131bool Document::hasListenerTypeForEventType(PlatformEvent::Type eventType) const
5132{
5133 switch (eventType) {
5134 case PlatformEvent::MouseForceChanged:
5135 return m_listenerTypes & Document::FORCECHANGED_LISTENER;
5136 case PlatformEvent::MouseForceDown:
5137 return m_listenerTypes & Document::FORCEDOWN_LISTENER;
5138 case PlatformEvent::MouseForceUp:
5139 return m_listenerTypes & Document::FORCEUP_LISTENER;
5140 case PlatformEvent::MouseScroll:
5141 return m_listenerTypes & Document::SCROLL_LISTENER;
5142 default:
5143 return false;
5144 }
5145}

5147void Document::addListenerTypeIfNeeded(const AtomString& eventType)
5148{
5149 if (eventType == eventNames().DOMSubtreeModifiedEvent)
5150 addListenerType(DOMSUBTREEMODIFIED_LISTENER);
5151 else if (eventType == eventNames().DOMNodeInsertedEvent)
5152 addListenerType(DOMNODEINSERTED_LISTENER);
5153 else if (eventType == eventNames().DOMNodeRemovedEvent)
5154 addListenerType(DOMNODEREMOVED_LISTENER);
5155 else if (eventType == eventNames().DOMNodeRemovedFromDocumentEvent)
5156 addListenerType(DOMNODEREMOVEDFROMDOCUMENT_LISTENER);
5157 else if (eventType == eventNames().DOMNodeInsertedIntoDocumentEvent)
5158 addListenerType(DOMNODEINSERTEDINTODOCUMENT_LISTENER);
5159 else if (eventType == eventNames().DOMCharacterDataModifiedEvent)
5160 addListenerType(DOMCHARACTERDATAMODIFIED_LISTENER);
5161 else if (eventType == eventNames().overflowchangedEvent)
5162 addListenerType(OVERFLOWCHANGED_LISTENER);
5163 else if (eventType == eventNames().webkitAnimationStartEvent || eventType == eventNames().animationstartEvent)
5164 addListenerType(ANIMATIONSTART_LISTENER);
5165 else if (eventType == eventNames().webkitAnimationEndEvent || eventType == eventNames().animationendEvent)
5166 addListenerType(ANIMATIONEND_LISTENER);
5167 else if (eventType == eventNames().webkitAnimationIterationEvent || eventType == eventNames().animationiterationEvent)
5168 addListenerType(ANIMATIONITERATION_LISTENER);
5169 else if (eventType == eventNames().webkitTransitionEndEvent || eventType == eventNames().transitionendEvent)
5170 addListenerType(TRANSITIONEND_LISTENER);
5171 else if (eventType == eventNames().beforeloadEvent)
5172 addListenerType(BEFORELOAD_LISTENER);
5173 else if (eventType == eventNames().scrollEvent)
5174 addListenerType(SCROLL_LISTENER);
5175 else if (eventType == eventNames().webkitmouseforcewillbeginEvent)
5176 addListenerType(FORCEWILLBEGIN_LISTENER);
5177 else if (eventType == eventNames().webkitmouseforcechangedEvent)
5178 addListenerType(FORCECHANGED_LISTENER);
5179 else if (eventType == eventNames().webkitmouseforcedownEvent)
5180 addListenerType(FORCEDOWN_LISTENER);
5181 else if (eventType == eventNames().webkitmouseforceupEvent)
5182 addListenerType(FORCEUP_LISTENER);
5183 else if (eventType == eventNames().resizeEvent)
5184 addListenerType(RESIZE_LISTENER);
5185}

5193
5194// https://html.spec.whatwg.org/#cookie-averse-document-object
5195bool Document::isCookieAverse() const
5196{
5197 // A Document that has no browsing context is cookie-averse.
5198 if (!frame())
5199 return true;
5200
5201 URL cookieURL = this->cookieURL();
5202
5203 // This is not part of the specification but we have historically allowed cookies over file protocol
5204 // and some developers rely on this for testing.
5205 if (cookieURL.isLocalFile())
5206 return false;
5207
5208 // A Document whose URL's scheme is not a network scheme is cookie-averse (https://fetch.spec.whatwg.org/#network-scheme).
5209 return !cookieURL.protocolIsInHTTPFamily() && !cookieURL.protocolIs("ftp");
5210}
5211
5212ExceptionOr<String> Document::cookie()
5213{
5214 if (page() && !page()->settings().cookieEnabled())
5215 return String();
5216
5217 if (isCookieAverse())
5218 return String();
5219
5220 if (!securityOrigin().canAccessCookies())
5221 return Exception { SecurityError };
5222
5223 URL cookieURL = this->cookieURL();
5224 if (cookieURL.isEmpty())
5225 return String();
5226
5227 if (!isDOMCookieCacheValid() && page())
5228 setCachedDOMCookies(page()->cookieJar().cookies(*this, cookieURL));
5229
5230 return String { cachedDOMCookies() };
5231}
5232
5233ExceptionOr<void> Document::setCookie(const String& value)
5234{
5235 if (page() && !page()->settings().cookieEnabled())
5236 return { };
5237
5238 if (isCookieAverse())
5239 return { };
5240
5241 if (!securityOrigin().canAccessCookies())
5242 return Exception { SecurityError };
5243
5244 URL cookieURL = this->cookieURL();
5245 if (cookieURL.isEmpty())
5246 return { };
5247
5248 invalidateDOMCookieCache();
5249 if (page())
5250 page()->cookieJar().setCookies(*this, cookieURL, value);
5251 return { };
5252}
5253
5254String Document::referrer()
5255{
5256#if ENABLE(RESOURCE_LOAD_STATISTICS)
5257 if (!m_referrerOverride.isEmpty())
5258 return m_referrerOverride;
5259 if (DeprecatedGlobalSettings::resourceLoadStatisticsEnabled() && frame()) {
5260 auto referrerStr = frame()->loader().referrer();
5261 if (!referrerStr.isEmpty()) {
5262 URL referrerURL { URL(), referrerStr };
5263 RegistrableDomain referrerRegistrableDomain { referrerURL };
5264 if (!referrerRegistrableDomain.matches(securityOrigin().data())) {
5265 m_referrerOverride = referrerURL.protocolHostAndPort();
5266 return m_referrerOverride;
5267 }
5268 }
5269 }
5270#endif
5271 if (frame())
5272 return frame()->loader().referrer();
5273 return String();
5274}
5275
5276String Document::domain() const
5277{
5278 return securityOrigin().domain();
5279}
5280
5281ExceptionOr<void> Document::setDomain(const String& newDomain)
5282{
5283 if (!frame())
5284 return Exception { SecurityError, "A browsing context is required to set a domain." };
5285
5286 if (isSandboxed(SandboxDocumentDomain))
5287 return Exception { SecurityError, "Assignment is forbidden for sandboxed iframes." };
5288
5289 if (LegacySchemeRegistry::isDomainRelaxationForbiddenForURLScheme(securityOrigin().protocol()))
5290 return Exception { SecurityError };
5291
5292 // FIXME: We should add logging indicating why a domain was not allowed.
5293
5294 const String& effectiveDomain = domain();
5295 if (effectiveDomain.isEmpty())
5296 return Exception { SecurityError, "The document has a null effectiveDomain." };
5297
5298 if (!securityOrigin().isMatchingRegistrableDomainSuffix(newDomain, settings().treatIPAddressAsDomain()))
5299 return Exception { SecurityError, "Attempted to use a non-registrable domain." };
5300
5301 securityOrigin().setDomainFromDOM(newDomain);
5302 return { };
5303}
5304
5305void Document::overrideLastModified(const std::optional<WallTime>& lastModified)
5306{
5307 m_overrideLastModified = lastModified;
5308}
5309
5310// http://www.whatwg.org/specs/web-apps/current-work/#dom-document-lastmodified
5311String Document::lastModified() const
5312{
5313 std::optional<WallTime> dateTime;
5314 if (m_overrideLastModified)
5315 dateTime = m_overrideLastModified;
5316 else if (loader())
5317 dateTime = loader()->response().lastModified();
5318
5319 // FIXME: If this document came from the file system, the HTML specification tells
5320 // us to read the last modification date from the file system.
5321 if (!dateTime)
5322 dateTime = WallTime::now();
5323
5324 auto ctime = dateTime.value().secondsSinceEpoch().secondsAs<time_t>();
5325 auto localDateTime = std::localtime(&ctime);
5326 return makeString(pad('0', 2, localDateTime->tm_mon + 1), '/',
5327 pad('0', 2, localDateTime->tm_mday), '/',
5328 pad('0', 4, 1900 + localDateTime->tm_year), ' ',
5329 pad('0', 2, localDateTime->tm_hour), ':',
5330 pad('0', 2, localDateTime->tm_min), ':',
5331 pad('0', 2, localDateTime->tm_sec));
5332}
5333
5334void Document::setCookieURL(const URL& url)
5335{
5336 if (m_cookieURL == url)
5337 return;
5338 m_cookieURL = url;
5339 invalidateDOMCookieCache();
5340}
5341
5342static bool isValidNameNonASCII(const LChar* characters, unsigned length)
5343{
5344 if (!isValidNameStart(characters[0]))
5345 return false;
5346
5347 for (unsigned i = 1; i < length; ++i) {
5348 if (!isValidNamePart(characters[i]))
5349 return false;
5350 }
5351
5352 return true;
5353}
5354
5355static bool isValidNameNonASCII(const UChar* characters, unsigned length)
5356{
5357 unsigned i = 0;
5358
5359 UChar32 c;
5360 U16_NEXT(characters, i, length, c);
5361 if (!isValidNameStart(c))
5362 return false;
5363
5364 while (i < length) {
5365 U16_NEXT(characters, i, length, c);
5366 if (!isValidNamePart(c))
5367 return false;
5368 }
5369
5370 return true;
5371}
5372
5373template<typename CharType>
5374static inline bool isValidNameASCII(const CharType* characters, unsigned length)
5375{
5376 CharType c = characters[0];
5377 if (!(isASCIIAlpha(c) || c == ':' || c == '_'))
5378 return false;
5379
5380 for (unsigned i = 1; i < length; ++i) {
5381 c = characters[i];
5382 if (!(isASCIIAlphanumeric(c) || c == ':' || c == '_' || c == '-' || c == '.'))
5383 return false;
5384 }
5385
5386 return true;
5387}
5388
5389bool Document::isValidName(const String& name)
5390{
5391 unsigned length = name.length();
5392 if (!length)
5393 return false;
5394
5395 if (name.is8Bit()) {
5396 const LChar* characters = name.characters8();
5397
5398 if (isValidNameASCII(characters, length))
5399 return true;
5400
5401 return isValidNameNonASCII(characters, length);
5402 }
5403
5404 const UChar* characters = name.characters16();
5405
5406 if (isValidNameASCII(characters, length))
5407 return true;
5408
5409 return isValidNameNonASCII(characters, length);
5410}
5411
5412ExceptionOr<std::pair<AtomString, AtomString>> Document::parseQualifiedName(const String& qualifiedName)
5413{
5414 unsigned length = qualifiedName.length();
5415
5416 if (!length)
5417 return Exception { InvalidCharacterError };
5418
5419 bool nameStart = true;
5420 bool sawColon = false;
5421 unsigned colonPosition = 0;
5422
5423 for (unsigned i = 0; i < length; ) {
5424 UChar32 c;
5425 U16_NEXT(qualifiedName, i, length, c);
5426 if (c == ':') {
5427 if (sawColon)
5428 return Exception { InvalidCharacterError };
5429 nameStart = true;
5430 sawColon = true;
5431 colonPosition = i - 1;
5432 } else if (nameStart) {
5433 if (!isValidNameStart(c))
5434 return Exception { InvalidCharacterError };
5435 nameStart = false;
5436 } else {
5437 if (!isValidNamePart(c))
5438 return Exception { InvalidCharacterError };
5439 }
5440 }
5441
5442 if (!sawColon)
5443 return std::pair<AtomString, AtomString> { { }, { qualifiedName } };
5444
5445 if (!colonPosition || length - colonPosition <= 1)
5446 return Exception { InvalidCharacterError };
5447
5448 return std::pair<AtomString, AtomString> { StringView { qualifiedName }.substring(0, colonPosition).toAtomString(), StringView { qualifiedName }.substring(colonPosition + 1).toAtomString() };
5449}
5450
5451ExceptionOr<QualifiedName> Document::parseQualifiedName(const AtomString& namespaceURI, const String& qualifiedName)
5452{
5453 auto parseResult = parseQualifiedName(qualifiedName);
5454 if (parseResult.hasException())
5455 return parseResult.releaseException();
5456 auto parsedPieces = parseResult.releaseReturnValue();
5457 return QualifiedName { parsedPieces.first, parsedPieces.second, namespaceURI };
5458}

5460void Document::setDecoder(RefPtr<TextResourceDecoder>&& decoder)
5461{
5462 m_decoder = WTFMove(decoder);
5463}
5464
5465URL Document::completeURL(const String& url, const URL& baseURLOverride, ForceUTF8 forceUTF8) const
5466{
5467 // Always return a null URL when passed a null string.
5468 // FIXME: Should we change the URL constructor to have this behavior?
5469 // See also [CSS]StyleSheet::completeURL(const String&)
5470 if (url.isNull())
5471 return URL();
5472 const URL& baseURL = ((baseURLOverride.isEmpty() || baseURLOverride == aboutBlankURL()) && parentDocument()) ? parentDocument()->baseURL() : baseURLOverride;
5473 if (!m_decoder || forceUTF8 == ForceUTF8::Yes)
5474 return URL(baseURL, url);
5475 return URL(baseURL, url, m_decoder->encodingForURLParsing());
5476}
5477
5478URL Document::completeURL(const String& url, ForceUTF8 forceUTF8) const
5479{
5480 return completeURL(url, m_baseURL, forceUTF8);
5481}
5482
5483void Document::setBackForwardCacheState(BackForwardCacheState state)
5484{
5485 if (m_backForwardCacheState == state)
5486 return;
5487
5488 m_backForwardCacheState = state;
5489
5490 FrameView* v = view();
5491 Page* page = this->page();
5492
5493 switch (state) {
5494 case InBackForwardCache:
5495 if (v) {
5496 // FIXME: There is some scrolling related work that needs to happen whenever a page goes into the
5497 // back/forward cache and similar work that needs to occur when it comes out. This is where we do the work
5498 // that needs to happen when we enter, and the work that needs to happen when we exit is in
5499 // HistoryController::restoreScrollPositionAndViewState(). It can't be here because this function is
5500 // called too early on in the process of a page exiting the cache for that work to be possible in this
5501 // function. It would be nice if there was more symmetry here.
5502 // https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=98698
5503 v->cacheCurrentScrollPosition();
5504 if (page && m_frame->isMainFrame()) {
5505 v->resetScrollbarsAndClearContentsSize();
5506 if (ScrollingCoordinator* scrollingCoordinator = page->scrollingCoordinator())
5507 scrollingCoordinator->clearAllNodes();
5508 }
5509 }
5510
5511#if ENABLE(POINTER_LOCK)
5512 exitPointerLock();
5513#endif
5514
5515 styleScope().clearResolver();
5516 clearSelectorQueryCache();
5517 m_styleRecalcTimer.stop();
5518
5519 clearSharedObjectPool();
5520
5521 if (m_idbConnectionProxy)
5522 m_idbConnectionProxy->setContextSuspended(*scriptExecutionContext(), true);
5523 break;
5524 case NotInBackForwardCache:
5525 if (childNeedsStyleRecalc())
5526 scheduleStyleRecalc();
5527 if (m_idbConnectionProxy)
5528 m_idbConnectionProxy->setContextSuspended(*scriptExecutionContext(), false);
5529 break;
5530 case AboutToEnterBackForwardCache:
5531 break;
5532 }
5533}
5534
5535void Document::documentWillBecomeInactive()
5536{
5537 ASSERT_IMPLIES(renderView(), view());
5538 if (auto* frameView = view())
5539 frameView->setIsInWindow(false);
5540}
5541
5542void Document::suspend(ReasonForSuspension reason)
5543{
5544 if (m_isSuspended)
5545 return;
5546
5547 documentWillBecomeInactive();
5548
5549 for (auto& element : m_documentSuspensionCallbackElements)
5550 element.prepareForDocumentSuspension();
5551
5552#if ASSERT_ENABLED
5553 // Clear the update flag to be able to check if the viewport arguments update
5554 // is dispatched, after the document is restored from the back/forward cache.
5555 m_didDispatchViewportPropertiesChanged = false;
5556#endif
5557
5558 if (auto* page = this->page())
5559 page->lockAllOverlayScrollbarsToHidden(true);
5560
5561 if (auto* view = renderView()) {
5562 if (view->usesCompositing())
5563 view->compositor().cancelCompositingLayerUpdate();
5564 }
5565
5566#if USE(LIBWEBRTC)
5567 // FIXME: This should be moved to Modules/mediastream.
5568 if (LibWebRTCProvider::webRTCAvailable()) {
5569 if (auto* page = this->page())
5570 page->libWebRTCProvider().unregisterMDNSNames(identifier());
5571 }
5572#endif
5573
5574#if ENABLE(SERVICE_WORKER)
5575 if (RuntimeEnabledFeatures::sharedFeatures().serviceWorkerEnabled() && reason == ReasonForSuspension::BackForwardCache)
5576 setServiceWorkerConnection(nullptr);
5577#endif
5578
5579 suspendScheduledTasks(reason);
5580
5581 ASSERT(m_frame);
5582 m_frame->clearTimers();
5583
5584 m_visualUpdatesAllowed = false;
5585 m_visualUpdatesSuppressionTimer.stop();
5586
5587 m_fontLoader->suspendFontLoading();
5588
5589 m_isSuspended = true;
5590}
5591
5592void Document::resume(ReasonForSuspension reason)
5593{
5594 if (!m_isSuspended)
5595 return;
5596
5597 for (auto element : copyToVectorOf<Ref<Element>>(m_documentSuspensionCallbackElements))
5598 element->resumeFromDocumentSuspension();
5599
5600 if (renderView())
5601 renderView()->setIsInWindow(true);
5602
5603 if (auto* page = this->page())
5604 page->lockAllOverlayScrollbarsToHidden(false);
5605
5606 ASSERT(m_frame);
5607
5608 if (m_timelinesController)
5609 m_timelinesController->resumeAnimations();
5610
5611 resumeScheduledTasks(reason);
5612
5613 m_visualUpdatesAllowed = true;
5614
5615 m_fontLoader->resumeFontLoading();
5616
5617 m_isSuspended = false;
5618
5619#if ENABLE(SERVICE_WORKER)
5620 if (RuntimeEnabledFeatures::sharedFeatures().serviceWorkerEnabled() && reason == ReasonForSuspension::BackForwardCache)
5621 setServiceWorkerConnection(&ServiceWorkerProvider::singleton().serviceWorkerConnection());
5622#endif
5623}

5628}
5629

5632 m_documentSuspensionCallbackElements.remove(element);
5633}
