5635bool Document::audioPlaybackRequiresUserGesture() const
5636{
5637 if (DocumentLoader* loader = this->loader()) {
5638 // If an audio playback policy was set during navigation, use it. If not, use the global settings.
5639 AutoplayPolicy policy = loader->autoplayPolicy();
5640 if (policy != AutoplayPolicy::Default)
5641 return policy == AutoplayPolicy::AllowWithoutSound || policy == AutoplayPolicy::Deny;
5642 }
5643
5644 return settings().audioPlaybackRequiresUserGesture();
5645}
5646
5647bool Document::videoPlaybackRequiresUserGesture() const
5648{
5649 if (DocumentLoader* loader = this->loader()) {
5650 // If a video playback policy was set during navigation, use it. If not, use the global settings.
5651 AutoplayPolicy policy = loader->autoplayPolicy();
5652 if (policy != AutoplayPolicy::Default)
5653 return policy == AutoplayPolicy::Deny;
5654 }
5655
5656 return settings().videoPlaybackRequiresUserGesture();
5657}

5659bool Document::mediaDataLoadsAutomatically() const
5660{

5739// Support for Javascript execCommand, and related methods
5740
5741static Editor::Command command(Document* document, const String& commandName, bool userInterface = false)
5742{
5743 auto protectedDocument = makeRef(*document);
5744
5745 document->updateStyleIfNeeded();
5746
5747 auto frame = makeRefPtr(document->frame());
5748
5749 if (!frame || frame->document() != document)
5750 return Editor::Command();
5751
5752 return frame->editor().command(commandName,
5753 userInterface ? CommandFromDOMWithUserInterface : CommandFromDOM);
5754}
5755
5756ExceptionOr<bool> Document::execCommand(const String& commandName, bool userInterface, const String& value)
5757{
5758 if (UNLIKELY(!isHTMLDocument() && !isXHTMLDocument()))
5759 return Exception { InvalidStateError, "execCommand is only supported on HTML documents." };
5760
5761 EventQueueScope eventQueueScope;
5762 return command(this, commandName, userInterface).execute(value);
5763}
5764
5765ExceptionOr<bool> Document::queryCommandEnabled(const String& commandName)
5766{
5767 if (UNLIKELY(!isHTMLDocument() && !isXHTMLDocument()))
5768 return Exception { InvalidStateError, "queryCommandEnabled is only supported on HTML documents." };
5769 return command(this, commandName).isEnabled();
5770}
5771
5772ExceptionOr<bool> Document::queryCommandIndeterm(const String& commandName)
5773{
5774 if (UNLIKELY(!isHTMLDocument() && !isXHTMLDocument()))
5775 return Exception { InvalidStateError, "queryCommandIndeterm is only supported on HTML documents." };
5776 return command(this, commandName).state() == TriState::Indeterminate;
5777}
5778
5779ExceptionOr<bool> Document::queryCommandState(const String& commandName)
5780{
5781 if (UNLIKELY(!isHTMLDocument() && !isXHTMLDocument()))
5782 return Exception { InvalidStateError, "queryCommandState is only supported on HTML documents." };
5783 return command(this, commandName).state() == TriState::True;
5784}
5785
5786ExceptionOr<bool> Document::queryCommandSupported(const String& commandName)
5787{
5788 if (UNLIKELY(!isHTMLDocument() && !isXHTMLDocument()))
5789 return Exception { InvalidStateError, "queryCommandSupported is only supported on HTML documents." };
5790 return command(this, commandName).isSupported();
5791}
5792
5793ExceptionOr<String> Document::queryCommandValue(const String& commandName)
5794{
5795 if (UNLIKELY(!isHTMLDocument() && !isXHTMLDocument()))
5796 return Exception { InvalidStateError, "queryCommandValue is only supported on HTML documents." };
5797 return command(this, commandName).value();
5798}

5811bool Document::shouldDeferAsynchronousScriptsUntilParsingFinishes() const
5812{
5813 if (!settings().shouldDeferAsynchronousScriptsUntilAfterDocumentLoadOrFirstPaint())
5814 return false;
5815
5816 if (quirks().shouldBypassAsyncScriptDeferring())
5817 return false;
5818
5819 return parsing() && !(view() && view()->hasEverPainted());
5820}
5821
5822#if ENABLE(XSLT)
5823
5824void Document::scheduleToApplyXSLTransforms()
5825{
5826 m_hasPendingXSLTransforms = true;
5827 if (!m_applyPendingXSLTransformsTimer.isActive())
5828 m_applyPendingXSLTransformsTimer.startOneShot(0_s);
5829}
5830
5831void Document::applyPendingXSLTransformsNowIfScheduled()
5832{
5833 if (!m_hasPendingXSLTransforms)
5834 return;
5835 m_applyPendingXSLTransformsTimer.stop();
5836 applyPendingXSLTransformsTimerFired();
5837}
5838
5839void Document::applyPendingXSLTransformsTimerFired()
5840{
5841 if (parsing())
5842 return;
5843
5844 m_hasPendingXSLTransforms = false;
5845 ASSERT_WITH_SECURITY_IMPLICATION(ScriptDisallowedScope::InMainThread::isScriptAllowed());
5846 for (auto& processingInstruction : styleScope().collectXSLTransforms()) {
5847 ASSERT(processingInstruction->isXSL());
5848
5849 // Don't apply XSL transforms to already transformed documents -- <rdar://problem/4132806>
5850 if (transformSourceDocument() || !processingInstruction->sheet())
5851 return;
5852
5853 // If the Document has already been detached from the frame, or the frame is currently in the process of
5854 // changing to a new document, don't attempt to create a new Document from the XSLT.
5855 if (!frame() || frame()->documentIsBeingReplaced())
5856 return;
5857
5858 auto processor = XSLTProcessor::create();
5859 processor->setXSLStyleSheet(downcast<XSLStyleSheet>(processingInstruction->sheet()));
5860 String resultMIMEType;
5861 String newSource;
5862 String resultEncoding;
5863 if (!processor->transformToString(*this, resultMIMEType, newSource, resultEncoding))
5864 continue;
5865 // FIXME: If the transform failed we should probably report an error (like Mozilla does).
5866 processor->createDocumentFromSource(newSource, resultEncoding, resultMIMEType, this, frame());
5867 }
5868}

5870void Document::setTransformSource(std::unique_ptr<TransformSource> source)
5871{
5872 m_transformSource = WTFMove(source);
5873}
5874
5875#endif
5876
5877void Document::setDesignMode(InheritedBool value)
5878{
5879 m_designMode = value;
5880 for (auto* frame = m_frame.get(); frame && frame->document(); frame = frame->tree().traverseNext(m_frame.get()))
5881 frame->document()->scheduleFullStyleRebuild();
5882}
5883
5884String Document::designMode() const
5885{
5886 return inDesignMode() ? "on"_s : "off"_s;
5887}
5888
5889void Document::setDesignMode(const String& value)
5890{
5891 InheritedBool mode;
5892 if (equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(value, "on"))
5893 mode = on;
5894 else if (equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(value, "off"))
5895 mode = off;
5896 else
5897 mode = inherit;
5898 setDesignMode(mode);
5899}
5900
5901bool Document::inDesignMode() const
5902{
5903 for (const Document* d = this; d; d = d->parentDocument()) {
5904 if (d->m_designMode != inherit)
5905 return d->m_designMode;
5906 }
5907 return false;
5908}
5909
5910Document* Document::parentDocument() const
5911{
5912 if (!m_frame)
5913 return nullptr;
5914 Frame* parent = m_frame->tree().parent();
5915 if (!parent)
5916 return nullptr;
5917 return parent->document();
5918}
5919
5920Document& Document::topDocument() const
5921{
5922 // FIXME: This special-casing avoids incorrectly determined top documents during the process
5923 // of AXObjectCache teardown or notification posting for cached or being-destroyed documents.
5924 if (backForwardCacheState() == NotInBackForwardCache && !m_renderTreeBeingDestroyed) {
5925 if (!m_frame)
5926 return const_cast<Document&>(*this);
5927 // This should always be non-null.
5928 Document* mainFrameDocument = m_frame->mainFrame().document();
5929 return mainFrameDocument ? *mainFrameDocument : const_cast<Document&>(*this);
5930 }
5931
5932 Document* document = const_cast<Document*>(this);
5933 while (HTMLFrameOwnerElement* element = document->ownerElement())
5934 document = &element->document();
5935 return *document;
5936}

5938ExceptionOr<Ref<Attr>> Document::createAttribute(const String& localName)
5939{
5940 if (!isValidName(localName))
5941 return Exception { InvalidCharacterError };
5942 return Attr::create(*this, QualifiedName { nullAtom(), isHTMLDocument() ? localName.convertToASCIILowercase() : localName, nullAtom() }, emptyString());
5943}
5944
5945ExceptionOr<Ref<Attr>> Document::createAttributeNS(const AtomString& namespaceURI, const String& qualifiedName, bool shouldIgnoreNamespaceChecks)
5946{
5947 auto parseResult = parseQualifiedName(namespaceURI, qualifiedName);
5948 if (parseResult.hasException())
5949 return parseResult.releaseException();
5950 QualifiedName parsedName { parseResult.releaseReturnValue() };
5951 if (!shouldIgnoreNamespaceChecks && !hasValidNamespaceForAttributes(parsedName))
5952 return Exception { NamespaceError };
5953 return Attr::create(*this, parsedName, emptyString());
5954}

6039
6040void Document::finishedParsing()
6041{
6042 ASSERT(!scriptableDocumentParser() || !m_parser->isParsing());
6043 ASSERT(!scriptableDocumentParser() || m_readyState != Loading);
6044 setParsing(false);
6045
6046 Ref<Document> protectedThis(*this);
6047
6048 scriptRunner().documentFinishedParsing();
6049
6050 if (!m_eventTiming.domContentLoadedEventStart)
6051 m_eventTiming.domContentLoadedEventStart = MonotonicTime::now();
6052
6053 // FIXME: Schedule a task to fire DOMContentLoaded event instead. See webkit.org/b/82931
6054 eventLoop().performMicrotaskCheckpoint();
6055 dispatchEvent(Event::create(eventNames().DOMContentLoadedEvent, Event::CanBubble::Yes, Event::IsCancelable::No));
6056
6057 if (!m_eventTiming.domContentLoadedEventEnd)
6058 m_eventTiming.domContentLoadedEventEnd = MonotonicTime::now();
6059
6060 if (RefPtr<Frame> frame = this->frame()) {
6061#if ENABLE(XSLT)
6062 applyPendingXSLTransformsNowIfScheduled();
6063#endif
6064
6065 // FrameLoader::finishedParsing() might end up calling Document::implicitClose() if all
6066 // resource loads are complete. HTMLObjectElements can start loading their resources from
6067 // post attach callbacks triggered by resolveStyle(). This means if we parse out an <object>
6068 // tag and then reach the end of the document without updating styles, we might not have yet
6069 // started the resource load and might fire the window load event too early. To avoid this
6070 // we force the styles to be up to date before calling FrameLoader::finishedParsing().
6071 // See https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=36864 starting around comment 35.
6072 updateStyleIfNeeded();
6073
6074 frame->loader().finishedParsing();
6075 InspectorInstrumentation::domContentLoadedEventFired(*frame);
6076 }
6077
6078 // Schedule dropping of the DocumentSharedObjectPool. We keep it alive for a while after parsing finishes
6079 // so that dynamically inserted content can also benefit from sharing optimizations.
6080 // Note that we don't refresh the timer on pool access since that could lead to huge caches being kept
6081 // alive indefinitely by something innocuous like JS setting .innerHTML repeatedly on a timer.
6082 static const Seconds timeToKeepSharedObjectPoolAliveAfterParsingFinished { 10_s };
6083 m_sharedObjectPoolClearTimer.startOneShot(timeToKeepSharedObjectPoolAliveAfterParsingFinished);
6084
6085 // Parser should have picked up all speculative preloads by now
6086 m_cachedResourceLoader->clearPreloads(CachedResourceLoader::ClearPreloadsMode::ClearSpeculativePreloads);
6087
6088#if ENABLE(SERVICE_WORKER)
6089 if (RuntimeEnabledFeatures::sharedFeatures().serviceWorkerEnabled()) {
6090 // Stop queuing service worker client messages now that the DOMContentLoaded event has been fired.
6091 if (auto* serviceWorkerContainer = this->serviceWorkerContainer())
6092 serviceWorkerContainer->startMessages();
6093 }
6094#endif
6095
6096#if ENABLE(APP_HIGHLIGHTS)
6097 if (auto* appHighlightStorage = appHighlightStorageIfExists())
6098 appHighlightStorage->restoreUnrestoredAppHighlights();
6099#endif
6100}
6101
6102void Document::clearSharedObjectPool()
6103{
6104 m_sharedObjectPool = nullptr;
6105 m_sharedObjectPoolClearTimer.stop();
6106}

6154
6155void Document::initSecurityContext()
6156{
6157 if (haveInitializedSecurityOrigin()) {
6158 ASSERT(SecurityContext::securityOrigin());
6159 return;
6160 }
6161
6162 if (!m_frame) {
6163 // No source for a security context.
6164 // This can occur via document.implementation.createDocument().
6165 setCookieURL(URL({ }, emptyString()));
6166 setSecurityOriginPolicy(SecurityOriginPolicy::create(SecurityOrigin::createUnique()));
6167 setContentSecurityPolicy(makeUnique<ContentSecurityPolicy>(URL { { }, emptyString() }, *this));
6168 return;
6169 }
6170
6171 // In the common case, create the security context from the currently
6172 // loading URL with a fresh content security policy.
6173 setCookieURL(m_url);
6174 enforceSandboxFlags(m_frame->loader().effectiveSandboxFlags());
6175 setReferrerPolicy(m_frame->loader().effectiveReferrerPolicy());
6176
6177 if (shouldEnforceContentDispositionAttachmentSandbox())
6178 applyContentDispositionAttachmentSandbox();
6179
6180 auto* documentLoader = m_frame->loader().documentLoader();
6181 bool isSecurityOriginUnique = isSandboxed(SandboxOrigin);
6182 if (!isSecurityOriginUnique)
6183 isSecurityOriginUnique = documentLoader && documentLoader->response().tainting() == ResourceResponse::Tainting::Opaque;
6184
6185 setSecurityOriginPolicy(SecurityOriginPolicy::create(isSecurityOriginUnique ? SecurityOrigin::createUnique() : SecurityOrigin::create(m_url)));
6186 setContentSecurityPolicy(makeUnique<ContentSecurityPolicy>(URL { m_url }, *this));
6187
6188 String overrideContentSecurityPolicy = m_frame->loader().client().overrideContentSecurityPolicy();
6189 if (!overrideContentSecurityPolicy.isNull())
6190 contentSecurityPolicy()->didReceiveHeader(overrideContentSecurityPolicy, ContentSecurityPolicyHeaderType::Enforce, ContentSecurityPolicy::PolicyFrom::API, referrer(), documentLoader ? documentLoader->response().httpStatusCode() : 0);
6191
6192#if USE(QUICK_LOOK)
6193 if (shouldEnforceQuickLookSandbox())
6194 applyQuickLookSandbox();
6195#endif
6196
6197 if (shouldEnforceHTTP09Sandbox()) {
6198 auto message = makeString("Sandboxing '", m_url.stringCenterEllipsizedToLength(), "' because it is using HTTP/0.9.");
6199 addConsoleMessage(MessageSource::Security, MessageLevel::Error, message);
6200 enforceSandboxFlags(SandboxScripts | SandboxPlugins);
6201 }
6202
6203 if (settings().needsStorageAccessFromFileURLsQuirk())
6204 securityOrigin().grantStorageAccessFromFileURLsQuirk();
6205 if (!settings().webSecurityEnabled()) {
6206 // Web security is turned off. We should let this document access every other document. This is used primary by testing
6207 // harnesses for web sites.
6208 securityOrigin().grantUniversalAccess();
6209 } else if (securityOrigin().isLocal()) {
6210 if (settings().allowUniversalAccessFromFileURLs() || m_frame->loader().client().shouldForceUniversalAccessFromLocalURL(m_url)) {
6211 // Some clients want local URLs to have universal access, but that setting is dangerous for other clients.
6212 securityOrigin().grantUniversalAccess();
6213 } else if (!settings().allowFileAccessFromFileURLs()) {
6214 // Some clients want local URLs to have even tighter restrictions by default, and not be able to access other local files.
6215 // FIXME 81578: The naming of this is confusing. Files with restricted access to other local files
6216 // still can have other privileges that can be remembered, thereby not making them unique origins.
6217 securityOrigin().setEnforcesFilePathSeparation();
6218 }
6219 }
6220 securityOrigin().setStorageBlockingPolicy(settings().storageBlockingPolicy());
6221
6222 Document* parentDocument = ownerElement() ? &ownerElement()->document() : nullptr;
6223 if (parentDocument && m_frame->loader().shouldTreatURLAsSrcdocDocument(url())) {
6224 m_isSrcdocDocument = true;
6225 setBaseURLOverride(parentDocument->baseURL());
6226 }
6227 if (parentDocument)
6228 setStrictMixedContentMode(parentDocument->isStrictMixedContentMode());
6229
6230 if (!SecurityPolicy::shouldInheritSecurityOriginFromOwner(m_url))
6231 return;
6232
6233 // If we do not obtain a meaningful origin from the URL, then we try to
6234 // find one via the frame hierarchy.
6235 Frame* parentFrame = m_frame->tree().parent();
6236 Frame* openerFrame = m_frame->loader().opener();
6237
6238 Frame* ownerFrame = parentFrame;
6239 if (!ownerFrame)
6240 ownerFrame = openerFrame;
6241
6242 if (!ownerFrame) {
6243 didFailToInitializeSecurityOrigin();
6244 return;
6245 }
6246
6247 contentSecurityPolicy()->copyStateFrom(ownerFrame->document()->contentSecurityPolicy());
6248 contentSecurityPolicy()->updateSourceSelf(ownerFrame->document()->securityOrigin());
6249
6250 // Per <http://www.w3.org/TR/upgrade-insecure-requests/>, new browsing contexts must inherit from an
6251 // ongoing set of upgraded requests. When opening a new browsing context, we need to capture its
6252 // existing upgrade request. Nested browsing contexts are handled during DocumentWriter::begin.
6253 if (auto* openerDocument = openerFrame ? openerFrame->document() : nullptr)
6254 contentSecurityPolicy()->inheritInsecureNavigationRequestsToUpgradeFromOpener(*openerDocument->contentSecurityPolicy());
6255
6256 if (isSandboxed(SandboxOrigin)) {
6257 // If we're supposed to inherit our security origin from our owner,
6258 // but we're also sandboxed, the only thing we inherit is the ability
6259 // to load local resources. This lets about:blank iframes in file://
6260 // URL documents load images and other resources from the file system.
6261 if (ownerFrame->document()->securityOrigin().canLoadLocalResources())
6262 securityOrigin().grantLoadLocalResources();
6263 return;
6264 }
6265
6266 setCookieURL(ownerFrame->document()->cookieURL());
6267 // We alias the SecurityOrigins to match Firefox, see Bug 15313
6268 // https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=15313
6269 setSecurityOriginPolicy(ownerFrame->document()->securityOriginPolicy());
6270}
6271
6272void Document::initContentSecurityPolicy()
6273{
6274 if (!m_frame)
6275 return;
6276 auto* parentFrame = m_frame->tree().parent();
6277 if (parentFrame)
6278 contentSecurityPolicy()->copyUpgradeInsecureRequestStateFrom(*parentFrame->document()->contentSecurityPolicy());
6279
6280 // FIXME: Remove this special plugin document logic. We are stricter than the CSP 3 spec. with regards to plugins: we prefer to
6281 // inherit the full policy unless the plugin document is opened in a new window. The CSP 3 spec. implies that only plugin documents
6282 // delivered with a local scheme (e.g. blob, file, data) should inherit a policy.
6283 if (!isPluginDocument())
6284 return;
6285 auto* openerFrame = m_frame->loader().opener();
6286 bool shouldInhert = parentFrame || (openerFrame && openerFrame->document()->securityOrigin().isSameOriginDomain(securityOrigin()));
6287 if (!shouldInhert)
6288 return;
6289 setContentSecurityPolicy(makeUnique<ContentSecurityPolicy>(URL { m_url }, *this));
6290 if (openerFrame)
6291 contentSecurityPolicy()->createPolicyForPluginDocumentFrom(*openerFrame->document()->contentSecurityPolicy());
6292 else
6293 contentSecurityPolicy()->copyStateFrom(parentFrame->document()->contentSecurityPolicy());
6294}
6295
6296bool Document::isContextThread() const
6297{
6298 return isMainThread();
6299}
6300
6301// https://w3c.github.io/webappsec-secure-contexts/#is-url-trustworthy
6302static bool isURLPotentiallyTrustworthy(const URL& url)
6303{
6304 if (url.protocolIsAbout())
6305 return url.isAboutBlank() || url.isAboutSrcDoc();
6306 if (url.protocolIsData())
6307 return true;
6308 return SecurityOrigin::create(url)->isPotentiallyTrustworthy();
6309}
6310
6311// https://w3c.github.io/webappsec-secure-contexts/#is-settings-object-contextually-secure step 5.3 and 5.4
6312static inline bool isDocumentSecure(const Document& document)
6313{
6314 if (document.isSandboxed(SandboxOrigin))
6315 return isURLPotentiallyTrustworthy(document.url());
6316 return document.securityOrigin().isPotentiallyTrustworthy();
6317}
6318
6319// https://w3c.github.io/webappsec-secure-contexts/#is-settings-object-contextually-secure
6320bool Document::isSecureContext() const
6321{
6322 if (!m_frame)
6323 return true;
6324 if (!RuntimeEnabledFeatures::sharedFeatures().secureContextChecksEnabled())
6325 return true;
6326
6327 for (auto* frame = m_frame->tree().parent(); frame; frame = frame->tree().parent()) {
6328 if (!isDocumentSecure(*frame->document()))
6329 return false;
6330 }
6331
6332 return isDocumentSecure(*this);
6333}
6334
6335void Document::updateURLForPushOrReplaceState(const URL& url)
6336{
6337 Frame* f = frame();
6338 if (!f)
6339 return;
6340
6341 setURL(url);
6342 f->loader().setOutgoingReferrer(url);
6343
6344 if (DocumentLoader* documentLoader = loader())
6345 documentLoader->replaceRequestURLForSameDocumentNavigation(url);
6346}
6347
6348void Document::statePopped(Ref<SerializedScriptValue>&& stateObject)
6349{
6350 if (!frame())
6351 return;
6352
6353 // Per step 11 of section 6.5.9 (history traversal) of the HTML5 spec, we
6354 // defer firing of popstate until we're in the complete state.
6355 if (m_readyState == Complete)
6356 dispatchPopstateEvent(WTFMove(stateObject));
6357 else
6358 m_pendingStateObject = WTFMove(stateObject);
6359}

6374std::optional<RenderingContext> Document::getCSSCanvasContext(const String& type, const String& name, int width, int height)
6375{
6376 HTMLCanvasElement* element = getCSSCanvasElement(name);
6377 if (!element)
6378 return std::nullopt;
6379 element->setSize({ width, height });
6380 auto context = element->getContext(type);
6381 if (!context)
6382 return std::nullopt;
6383
6384#if ENABLE(WEBGL)
6385 if (is<WebGLRenderingContext>(*context))
6386 return RenderingContext { RefPtr<WebGLRenderingContext> { &downcast<WebGLRenderingContext>(*context) } };
6387#endif
6388#if ENABLE(WEBGL2)
6389 if (is<WebGL2RenderingContext>(*context))
6390 return RenderingContext { RefPtr<WebGL2RenderingContext> { &downcast<WebGL2RenderingContext>(*context) } };
6391#endif
6392#if ENABLE(WEBGPU)
6393 if (is<GPUCanvasContext>(*context))
6394 return RenderingContext { RefPtr<GPUCanvasContext> { &downcast<GPUCanvasContext>(*context) } };
6395#endif
6396
6397 return RenderingContext { RefPtr<CanvasRenderingContext2D> { &downcast<CanvasRenderingContext2D>(*context) } };
6398}

6403 if (!element)

6405 return element.get();
6406}

6414 return String();

6439{

6441 return;

6443 if (equalLettersIgnoringASCIICase(dnsPrefetchControl, "on") && !m_haveExplicitlyDisabledDNSPrefetch) {
6444 m_isDNSPrefetchEnabled = true;
6445 return;
6446 }
6447
6448 m_isDNSPrefetchEnabled = false;
6449 m_haveExplicitlyDisabledDNSPrefetch = true;
6450}
6451
6452void Document::getParserLocation(String& completedURL, unsigned& line, unsigned& column) const
6453{
6454 // We definitely cannot associate the message with a location being parsed if we are not even parsing.
6455 if (!parsing())
6456 return;
6457
6458 ScriptableDocumentParser* parser = scriptableDocumentParser();
6459 if (!parser)
6460 return;
6461
6462 // When the parser waits for scripts, any messages must be coming from some other source, and are not related to the location of the script element that made the parser wait.
6463 if (!parser->shouldAssociateConsoleMessagesWithTextPosition())
6464 return;
6465
6466 completedURL = url().string();
6467 TextPosition position = parser->textPosition();
6468 line = position.m_line.oneBasedInt();
6469 column = position.m_column.oneBasedInt();
6470}

6472void Document::addConsoleMessage(std::unique_ptr<Inspector::ConsoleMessage>&& consoleMessage)
6473{
6474 if (!isContextThread()) {
6475 postTask(AddConsoleMessageTask(WTFMove(consoleMessage)));
6476 return;
6477 }
6478
6479 if (Page* page = this->page())
6480 page->console().addMessage(WTFMove(consoleMessage));
6481}
6482
6483void Document::addConsoleMessage(MessageSource source, MessageLevel level, const String& message, unsigned long requestIdentifier)
6484{
6485 if (!isContextThread()) {
6486 postTask(AddConsoleMessageTask(source, level, message));
6487 return;
6488 }
6489
6490 if (Page* page = this->page())
6491 page->console().addMessage(source, level, message, requestIdentifier, this);
6492
6493 if (m_consoleMessageListener)
6494 m_consoleMessageListener->scheduleCallback(*this, message);
6495}
6496
6497void Document::addMessage(MessageSource source, MessageLevel level, const String& message, const String& sourceURL, unsigned lineNumber, unsigned columnNumber, RefPtr<Inspector::ScriptCallStack>&& callStack, JSC::JSGlobalObject* state, unsigned long requestIdentifier)
6498{
6499 if (!isContextThread()) {
6500 postTask(AddConsoleMessageTask(source, level, message));
6501 return;
6502 }
6503
6504 if (Page* page = this->page())
6505 page->console().addMessage(source, level, message, sourceURL, lineNumber, columnNumber, WTFMove(callStack), state, requestIdentifier);
6506}
6507
6508void Document::postTask(Task&& task)
6509{
6510 callOnMainThread([documentID = identifier(), task = WTFMove(task)]() mutable {
6511 ASSERT(isMainThread());
6512
6513 auto* document = allDocumentsMap().get(documentID);
6514 if (!document)
6515 return;
6516
6517 Page* page = document->page();
6518 if ((page && page->defersLoading() && document->activeDOMObjectsAreSuspended()) || !document->m_pendingTasks.isEmpty())
6519 document->m_pendingTasks.append(WTFMove(task));
6520 else
6521 task.performTask(*document);
6522 });
6523}
6524
6525void Document::pendingTasksTimerFired()
6526{
6527 Vector<Task> pendingTasks = WTFMove(m_pendingTasks);
6528 for (auto& task : pendingTasks)
6529 task.performTask(*this);
6530}
6531
6532EventLoopTaskGroup& Document::eventLoop()
6533{
6534 ASSERT(isMainThread());
6535 if (UNLIKELY(!m_documentTaskGroup)) {
6536 m_documentTaskGroup = makeUnique<EventLoopTaskGroup>(windowEventLoop());
6537 if (activeDOMObjectsAreStopped())
6538 m_documentTaskGroup->markAsReadyToStop();
6539 else if (activeDOMObjectsAreSuspended())
6540 m_documentTaskGroup->suspend();
6541 }
6542 return *m_documentTaskGroup;
6543}
6544
6545WindowEventLoop& Document::windowEventLoop()
6546{
6547 ASSERT(isMainThread());
6548 if (UNLIKELY(!m_eventLoop))
6549 m_eventLoop = WindowEventLoop::eventLoopForSecurityOrigin(securityOrigin());
6550 return *m_eventLoop;
6551}
6552
6553void Document::suspendScheduledTasks(ReasonForSuspension reason)
6554{
6555 if (m_scheduledTasksAreSuspended) {
6556 // A page may subsequently suspend DOM objects, say as part of handling a scroll or zoom gesture, after the
6557 // embedding client requested the page be suspended. We ignore such requests so long as the embedding client
6558 // requested the suspension first. See <rdar://problem/13754896> for more details.
6559 ASSERT(reasonForSuspendingActiveDOMObjects() == ReasonForSuspension::PageWillBeSuspended);
6560 return;
6561 }
6562
6563 suspendScriptedAnimationControllerCallbacks();
6564 suspendActiveDOMObjects(reason);
6565 scriptRunner().suspend();
6566 m_pendingTasksTimer.stop();
6567
6568#if ENABLE(XSLT)
6569 m_applyPendingXSLTransformsTimer.stop();
6570#endif
6571
6572 // Deferring loading and suspending parser is necessary when we need to prevent re-entrant JavaScript execution
6573 // (e.g. while displaying an alert).
6574 // It is not currently possible to suspend parser unless loading is deferred, because new data arriving from network
6575 // will trigger parsing, and leave the scheduler in an inconsistent state where it doesn't know whether it's suspended or not.
6576 if (reason == ReasonForSuspension::WillDeferLoading && m_parser)
6577 m_parser->suspendScheduledTasks();
6578
6579 m_scheduledTasksAreSuspended = true;
6580}
6581
6582void Document::resumeScheduledTasks(ReasonForSuspension reason)
6583{
6584 if (reasonForSuspendingActiveDOMObjects() != reason)
6585 return;
6586
6587 ASSERT(m_scheduledTasksAreSuspended);
6588
6589 if (reason == ReasonForSuspension::WillDeferLoading && m_parser)
6590 m_parser->resumeScheduledTasks();
6591
6592#if ENABLE(XSLT)
6593 if (m_hasPendingXSLTransforms)
6594 m_applyPendingXSLTransformsTimer.startOneShot(0_s);
6595#endif
6596
6597 if (!m_pendingTasks.isEmpty())
6598 m_pendingTasksTimer.startOneShot(0_s);
6599 scriptRunner().resume();
6600 resumeActiveDOMObjects(reason);
6601 resumeScriptedAnimationControllerCallbacks();
6602
6603 m_scheduledTasksAreSuspended = false;
6604}
6605
6606void Document::suspendScriptedAnimationControllerCallbacks()
6607{
6608 if (m_scriptedAnimationController)
6609 m_scriptedAnimationController->suspend();
6610}
6611
6612void Document::resumeScriptedAnimationControllerCallbacks()
6613{
6614 if (m_scriptedAnimationController)
6615 m_scriptedAnimationController->resume();
6616}
6617
6618void Document::serviceRequestAnimationFrameCallbacks()
6619{
6620 if (m_scriptedAnimationController && domWindow())
6621 m_scriptedAnimationController->serviceRequestAnimationFrameCallbacks(domWindow()->frozenNowTimestamp());
6622}

6634 }

6738
6739void Document::loadEventDelayTimerFired()
6740{
6741 // FIXME: Should the call to FrameLoader::checkLoadComplete be moved inside Document::checkCompleted?
6742 // FIXME: Should this also call DocumentLoader::checkLoadComplete?
6743 // FIXME: Not obvious why checkCompleted needs to go first. The order these are called is
6744 // visible to WebKit clients, but it's more like a race than a well-defined relationship.
6745 Ref<Document> protectedThis(*this);
6746 checkCompleted();
6747 if (auto* frame = this->frame())
6748 frame->loader().checkLoadComplete();
6749}

6752{
6753 if (auto* frame = this->frame())
6754 frame->loader().checkCompleted();
6755}
6756
6757double Document::monotonicTimestamp() const
6758{
6759 auto* loader = this->loader();
6760 if (!loader)
6761 return 0.0;
6762 return (MonotonicTime::now() - loader->timing().startTime()).seconds();
6763}
6764
6765int Document::requestAnimationFrame(Ref<RequestAnimationFrameCallback>&& callback)
6766{
6767 if (!m_scriptedAnimationController) {
6768 m_scriptedAnimationController = ScriptedAnimationController::create(*this);
6769
6770 // It's possible that the Page may have suspended scripted animations before
6771 // we were created. We need to make sure that we don't start up the animation
6772 // controller on a background tab, for example.
6773 if (!page() || page()->scriptedAnimationsSuspended())
6774 m_scriptedAnimationController->suspend();
6775
6776 if (!topOrigin().isSameOriginDomain(securityOrigin()) && !hasHadUserInteraction())
6777 m_scriptedAnimationController->addThrottlingReason(ThrottlingReason::NonInteractedCrossOriginFrame);
6778 }
6779
6780 return m_scriptedAnimationController->registerCallback(WTFMove(callback));
6781}
6782
6783void Document::cancelAnimationFrame(int id)
6784{
6785 if (!m_scriptedAnimationController)
6786 return;
6787 m_scriptedAnimationController->cancelCallback(id);
6788}
6789
6790void Document::clearScriptedAnimationController()
6791{
6792 // FIXME: consider using ActiveDOMObject.
6793 if (m_scriptedAnimationController)
6794 m_scriptedAnimationController->clearDocumentPointer();
6795 m_scriptedAnimationController = nullptr;
6796}
6797
6798int Document::requestIdleCallback(Ref<IdleRequestCallback>&& callback, Seconds timeout)
6799{
6800 if (!m_idleCallbackController)
6801 m_idleCallbackController = makeUnique<IdleCallbackController>(*this);
6802 return m_idleCallbackController->queueIdleCallback(WTFMove(callback), timeout);
6803}
6804
6805void Document::cancelIdleCallback(int id)
6806{
6807 if (!m_idleCallbackController)
6808 return;
6809 m_idleCallbackController->removeIdleCallback(id);
6810}
6811
6812void Document::wheelEventHandlersChanged(Node* node)
6813{
6814 Page* page = this->page();
6815 if (!page)
6816 return;
6817
6818 if (FrameView* frameView = view()) {
6819 if (ScrollingCoordinator* scrollingCoordinator = page->scrollingCoordinator())
6820 scrollingCoordinator->frameViewEventTrackingRegionsChanged(*frameView);
6821 }
6822
6823#if ENABLE(WHEEL_EVENT_REGIONS)
6824 if (is<Element>(node)) {
6825 // Style is affected via eventListenerRegionTypes().
6826 downcast<Element>(*node).invalidateStyle();
6827 }
6828
6829 m_frame->invalidateContentEventRegionsIfNeeded(Frame::InvalidateContentEventRegionsReason::EventHandlerChange);
6830#else
6831 UNUSED_PARAM(node);
6832#endif
6833
6834 bool haveHandlers = m_wheelEventTargets && !m_wheelEventTargets->isEmpty();
6835 page->chrome().client().wheelEventHandlersChanged(haveHandlers);
6836}
6837
6838void Document::didAddWheelEventHandler(Node& node)
6839{
6840 if (!m_wheelEventTargets)
6841 m_wheelEventTargets = makeUnique<EventTargetSet>();
6842
6843 m_wheelEventTargets->add(&node);
6844 wheelEventHandlersChanged(&node);
6845
6846 if (Frame* frame = this->frame())
6847 DebugPageOverlays::didChangeEventHandlers(*frame);
6848}
6849
6850HttpEquivPolicy Document::httpEquivPolicy() const
6851{
6852 if (shouldEnforceContentDispositionAttachmentSandbox())
6853 return HttpEquivPolicy::DisabledByContentDispositionAttachmentSandbox;
6854 if (page() && !page()->settings().httpEquivEnabled())
6855 return HttpEquivPolicy::DisabledBySettings;
6856 return HttpEquivPolicy::Enabled;
6857}
6858
6859static bool removeHandlerFromSet(EventTargetSet& handlerSet, Node& node, EventHandlerRemoval removal)
6860{
6861 switch (removal) {
6862 case EventHandlerRemoval::One:
6863 return handlerSet.remove(&node);
6864 case EventHandlerRemoval::All:
6865 return handlerSet.removeAll(&node);
6866 }
6867 return false;
6868}
6869
6870void Document::didRemoveWheelEventHandler(Node& node, EventHandlerRemoval removal)
6871{
6872 if (!m_wheelEventTargets)
6873 return;
6874
6875 if (!removeHandlerFromSet(*m_wheelEventTargets, node, removal))
6876 return;
6877
6878 wheelEventHandlersChanged(&node);
6879
6880 if (Frame* frame = this->frame())
6881 DebugPageOverlays::didChangeEventHandlers(*frame);
6882}
6883
6884unsigned Document::wheelEventHandlerCount() const
6885{
6886 if (!m_wheelEventTargets)
6887 return 0;
6888
6889 unsigned count = 0;
6890 for (auto& handler : *m_wheelEventTargets)
6891 count += handler.value;
6892
6893 return count;
6894}
6895
6896void Document::didAddTouchEventHandler(Node& handler)
6897{
6898#if ENABLE(TOUCH_EVENTS)
6899 if (!m_touchEventTargets)
6900 m_touchEventTargets = makeUnique<EventTargetSet>();
6901
6902 m_touchEventTargets->add(&handler);
6903
6904 if (Document* parent = parentDocument()) {
6905 parent->didAddTouchEventHandler(*this);
6906 return;
6907 }
6908#else
6909 UNUSED_PARAM(handler);
6910#endif
6911}
6912
6913void Document::didRemoveTouchEventHandler(Node& handler, EventHandlerRemoval removal)
6914{
6915#if ENABLE(TOUCH_EVENTS)
6916 if (!m_touchEventTargets)
6917 return;
6918
6919 removeHandlerFromSet(*m_touchEventTargets, handler, removal);
6920
6921 if (Document* parent = parentDocument())
6922 parent->didRemoveTouchEventHandler(*this);
6923#else
6924 UNUSED_PARAM(handler);
6925 UNUSED_PARAM(removal);
6926#endif
6927}
6928
6929void Document::didRemoveEventTargetNode(Node& handler)
6930{
6931#if ENABLE(TOUCH_EVENTS)
6932 if (m_touchEventTargets) {
6933 m_touchEventTargets->removeAll(&handler);
6934 if ((&handler == this || m_touchEventTargets->isEmpty()) && parentDocument())
6935 parentDocument()->didRemoveEventTargetNode(*this);
6936 }
6937#endif
6938
6939 if (m_wheelEventTargets) {
6940 m_wheelEventTargets->removeAll(&handler);
6941 if ((&handler == this || m_wheelEventTargets->isEmpty()) && parentDocument())
6942 parentDocument()->didRemoveEventTargetNode(*this);
6943 }
6944}

6946unsigned Document::touchEventHandlerCount() const
6947{
6948#if ENABLE(TOUCH_EVENTS)
6949 if (!m_touchEventTargets)
6950 return 0;
6951
6952 unsigned count = 0;
6953 for (auto& handler : *m_touchEventTargets)
6954 count += handler.value;
6955
6956 return count;
6957#else
6958 return 0;
6959#endif
6960}

6962LayoutRect Document::absoluteEventHandlerBounds(bool& includesFixedPositionElements)
6963{
6964 includesFixedPositionElements = false;
6965 if (RenderView* renderView = this->renderView())
6966 return renderView->documentRect();
6967
6968 return LayoutRect();
6969}
6970
6971Document::RegionFixedPair Document::absoluteEventRegionForNode(Node& node)
6972{
6973 Region region;
6974 LayoutRect rootRelativeBounds;
6975 bool insideFixedPosition = false;
6976
6977 if (is<Document>(node)) {
6978 auto& document = downcast<Document>(node);
6979 if (&document == this)
6980 rootRelativeBounds = absoluteEventHandlerBounds(insideFixedPosition);
6981 else if (Element* element = document.ownerElement())
6982 rootRelativeBounds = element->absoluteEventHandlerBounds(insideFixedPosition);
6983 } else if (is<Element>(node)) {
6984 auto& element = downcast<Element>(node);
6985 if (is<HTMLBodyElement>(element)) {
6986 // For the body, just use the document bounds.
6987 // The body may not cover this whole area, but it's OK for this region to be an overestimate.
6988 rootRelativeBounds = absoluteEventHandlerBounds(insideFixedPosition);
6989 } else
6990 rootRelativeBounds = element.absoluteEventHandlerBounds(insideFixedPosition);
6991 }
6992
6993 if (!rootRelativeBounds.isEmpty())
6994 region.unite(Region(enclosingIntRect(rootRelativeBounds)));
6995
6996 return RegionFixedPair(region, insideFixedPosition);
6997}
6998
6999Document::RegionFixedPair Document::absoluteRegionForEventTargets(const EventTargetSet* targets)
7000{
7001 LayoutDisallowedScope layoutDisallowedScope(LayoutDisallowedScope::Reason::ReentrancyAvoidance);
7002
7003 if (!targets)
7004 return RegionFixedPair(Region(), false);
7005
7006 Region targetRegion;
7007 bool insideFixedPosition = false;
7008
7009 for (auto& keyValuePair : *targets) {
7010 if (auto* node = keyValuePair.key) {
7011 auto targetRegionFixedPair = absoluteEventRegionForNode(*node);
7012 targetRegion.unite(targetRegionFixedPair.first);
7013 insideFixedPosition |= targetRegionFixedPair.second;
7014 }
7015 }
7016
7017 return RegionFixedPair(targetRegion, insideFixedPosition);
7018}

7020void Document::updateLastHandledUserGestureTimestamp(MonotonicTime time)
7021{
7022 m_lastHandledUserGestureTimestamp = time;
7023
7024 if (static_cast<bool>(time) && m_scriptedAnimationController) {
7025 // It's OK to always remove NonInteractedCrossOriginFrame even if this frame isn't cross-origin.
7026 m_scriptedAnimationController->removeThrottlingReason(ThrottlingReason::NonInteractedCrossOriginFrame);
7027 }
7028
7029 // DOM Timer alignment may depend on the user having interacted with the document.
7030 didChangeTimerAlignmentInterval();
7031
7032 if (HTMLFrameOwnerElement* element = ownerElement())
7033 element->document().updateLastHandledUserGestureTimestamp(time);
7034}
7035
7036bool Document::processingUserGestureForMedia() const
7037{
7038 if (UserGestureIndicator::processingUserGestureForMedia())
7039 return true;
7040
7041 if (m_userActivatedMediaFinishedPlayingTimestamp + maxIntervalForUserGestureForwardingAfterMediaFinishesPlaying >= MonotonicTime::now())
7042 return true;
7043
7044 if (settings().mediaUserGestureInheritsFromDocument())
7045 return topDocument().hasHadUserInteraction();
7046
7047 auto* loader = this->loader();
7048 if (loader && loader->allowedAutoplayQuirks().contains(AutoplayQuirk::InheritedUserGestures))
7049 return topDocument().hasHadUserInteraction();
7050
7051 return false;
7052}

7064DocumentLoader* Document::loader() const
7065{
7066 if (!m_frame)
7067 return nullptr;
7068
7069 DocumentLoader* loader = m_frame->loader().documentLoader();
7070 if (!loader)
7071 return nullptr;
7072
7073 if (m_frame->document() != this)
7074 return nullptr;
7075
7076 return loader;
7077}
7078
7079bool Document::allowsContentJavaScript() const
7080{
7081 // FIXME: Get all SPI clients off of this potentially dangerous Setting.
7082 if (!settings().scriptMarkupEnabled())
7083 return false;
7084
7085 if (!m_frame || m_frame->document() != this) {
7086 // If this Document is frameless or in the wrong frame, its context document
7087 // must allow for it to run content JavaScript.
7088 return !m_contextDocument || m_contextDocument->allowsContentJavaScript();
7089 }
7090
7091 return m_frame->loader().client().allowsContentJavaScriptFromMostRecentNavigation() == AllowsContentJavaScript::Yes;
7092}

7094Element* eventTargetElementForDocument(Document* document)
7095{
7096 if (!document)
7097 return nullptr;
7098 Element* element = document->focusedElement();
7099 if (!element && is<PluginDocument>(*document))
7100 element = downcast<PluginDocument>(*document).pluginElement();
7101 if (!element && document->isHTMLDocument())
7102 element = document->bodyOrFrameset();
7103 if (!element)
7104 element = document->documentElement();
7105 return element;
7106}
7107
7108void Document::convertAbsoluteToClientQuads(Vector<FloatQuad>& quads, const RenderStyle& style)
7109{
7110 if (!view())
7111 return;
7112
7113 const auto& frameView = *view();
7114 float inverseFrameScale = frameView.absoluteToDocumentScaleFactor(style.effectiveZoom());
7115 auto documentToClientOffset = frameView.documentToClientOffset();
7116
7117 for (auto& quad : quads) {
7118 if (inverseFrameScale != 1)
7119 quad.scale(inverseFrameScale);
7120
7121 quad.move(documentToClientOffset);
7122 }
7123}

7125void Document::convertAbsoluteToClientRects(Vector<FloatRect>& rects, const RenderStyle& style)
7126{
7127 if (!view())
7128 return;
7129
7130 auto& frameView = *view();
7131 float inverseFrameScale = frameView.absoluteToDocumentScaleFactor(style.effectiveZoom());
7132 auto documentToClientOffset = frameView.documentToClientOffset();
7133
7134 for (auto& rect : rects) {
7135 if (inverseFrameScale != 1)
7136 rect.scale(inverseFrameScale);
7137
7138 rect.move(documentToClientOffset);
7139 }
7140}
7141
7142void Document::convertAbsoluteToClientRect(FloatRect& rect, const RenderStyle& style)
7143{

7145 return;
7146
7147 const auto& frameView = *view();

7149 rect = frameView.documentToClientRect(rect);
7150}

7157void Document::decrementActiveParserCount()
7158{

7164 // but it seems to cause http/tests/security/feed-urls-from-remote.html
7165 // to timeout on Mac WK1; see http://webkit.org/b/110554 and http://webkit.org/b/110401.

7167}

7169DocumentParserYieldToken::DocumentParserYieldToken(Document& document)
7170 : m_document(makeWeakPtr(document))
7171{
7172 if (++document.m_parserYieldTokenCount != 1)
7173 return;
7174
7175 document.scriptRunner().didBeginYieldingParser();
7176 if (auto* parser = document.parser())
7177 parser->didBeginYieldingParser();
7178}
7179
7180DocumentParserYieldToken::~DocumentParserYieldToken()
7181{
7182 if (!m_document)
7183 return;
7184
7185 ASSERT(m_document->m_parserYieldTokenCount);
7186 if (--m_document->m_parserYieldTokenCount)
7187 return;
7188
7189 m_document->scriptRunner().didEndYieldingParser();
7190 if (auto* parser = m_document->parser())
7191 parser->didEndYieldingParser();
7192}
7193
7194static Element* findNearestCommonComposedAncestor(Element* elementA, Element* elementB)
7195{
7196 if (!elementA || !elementB)
7197 return nullptr;
7198
7199 if (elementA == elementB)
7200 return elementA;
7201
7202 HashSet<Element*> ancestorChain;
7203 for (auto* element = elementA; element; element = element->parentElementInComposedTree())
7204 ancestorChain.add(element);
7205
7206 for (auto* element = elementB; element; element = element->parentElementInComposedTree()) {
7207 if (ancestorChain.contains(element))
7208 return element;
7209 }
7210 return nullptr;
7211}
7212
7213void Document::updateHoverActiveState(const HitTestRequest& request, Element* innerElement, CaptureChange captureElementChanged)
7214{
7215 ASSERT(!request.readOnly());
7216
7217 Vector<RefPtr<Element>, 32> elementsToClearActive;
7218 Vector<RefPtr<Element>, 32> elementsToSetActive;
7219 Vector<RefPtr<Element>, 32> elementsToClearHover;
7220 Vector<RefPtr<Element>, 32> elementsToSetHover;
7221
7222 Element* innerElementInDocument = innerElement;
7223 while (innerElementInDocument && &innerElementInDocument->document() != this) {
7224 innerElementInDocument->document().updateHoverActiveState(request, innerElementInDocument);
7225 innerElementInDocument = innerElementInDocument->document().ownerElement();
7226 }
7227
7228 Element* oldActiveElement = m_activeElement.get();
7229 if (oldActiveElement && !request.active()) {
7230 // We are clearing the :active chain because the mouse has been released.
7231 for (auto* currentElement = oldActiveElement; currentElement; currentElement = currentElement->parentElementInComposedTree()) {
7232 elementsToClearActive.append(currentElement);
7233 m_userActionElements.setInActiveChain(*currentElement, false);
7234 }
7235 m_activeElement = nullptr;
7236 } else {
7237 Element* newActiveElement = innerElementInDocument;
7238 if (!oldActiveElement && newActiveElement && request.active() && !request.touchMove()) {
7239 // We are setting the :active chain and freezing it. If future moves happen, they
7240 // will need to reference this chain.
7241 for (RenderElement* curr = newActiveElement->renderer(); curr; curr = curr->parent()) {
7242 Element* element = curr->element();
7243 if (!element || curr->isTextOrLineBreak())
7244 continue;
7245 m_userActionElements.setInActiveChain(*element, true);
7246 }
7247
7248 m_activeElement = newActiveElement;
7249 }
7250 }
7251 // If the mouse has just been pressed, set :active on the chain. Those (and only those)
7252 // nodes should remain :active until the mouse is released.
7253 bool allowActiveChanges = !oldActiveElement && m_activeElement;
7254
7255 // If the mouse is down and if this is a mouse move event, we want to restrict changes in
7256 // :hover/:active to only apply to elements that are in the :active chain that we froze
7257 // at the time the mouse went down, unless the capture element changed.
7258 bool mustBeInActiveChain = request.active() && request.move() && captureElementChanged == CaptureChange::No;
7259
7260 RefPtr<Element> oldHoveredElement = WTFMove(m_hoveredElement);
7261
7262 // A touch release does not set a new hover target; clearing the element we're working with
7263 // will clear the chain of hovered elements all the way to the top of the tree.
7264 if (request.touchRelease())
7265 innerElementInDocument = nullptr;
7266
7267 // Check to see if the hovered Element has changed.
7268 // If it hasn't, we do not need to do anything.
7269 Element* newHoveredElement = innerElementInDocument;
7270 while (newHoveredElement && !newHoveredElement->renderer())
7271 newHoveredElement = newHoveredElement->parentElementInComposedTree();
7272
7273 m_hoveredElement = newHoveredElement;
7274
7275 auto* commonAncestor = findNearestCommonComposedAncestor(oldHoveredElement.get(), newHoveredElement);
7276
7277 if (oldHoveredElement != newHoveredElement) {
7278 for (auto* element = oldHoveredElement.get(); element; element = element->parentElementInComposedTree()) {
7279 if (element == commonAncestor)
7280 break;
7281 if (mustBeInActiveChain && !element->isInActiveChain())
7282 continue;
7283 elementsToClearHover.append(element);
7284 }
7285 // Unset hovered nodes in sub frame documents if the old hovered node was a frame owner.
7286 if (is<HTMLFrameOwnerElement>(oldHoveredElement)) {
7287 if (auto* contentDocument = downcast<HTMLFrameOwnerElement>(*oldHoveredElement).contentDocument())
7288 contentDocument->updateHoverActiveState(request, nullptr);
7289 }
7290 }
7291
7292 bool sawCommonAncestor = false;
7293 for (auto* element = newHoveredElement; element; element = element->parentElementInComposedTree()) {
7294 if (mustBeInActiveChain && !element->isInActiveChain())
7295 continue;
7296 if (allowActiveChanges)
7297 elementsToSetActive.append(element);
7298 if (element == commonAncestor)
7299 sawCommonAncestor = true;
7300 if (!sawCommonAncestor)
7301 elementsToSetHover.append(element);
7302 }
7303
7304 auto changeState = [](auto& elements, auto pseudoClassType, auto&& setter) {
7305 if (elements.isEmpty())
7306 return;
7307 Style::PseudoClassChangeInvalidation styleInvalidation { *elements.last(), pseudoClassType, Style::InvalidationScope::Descendants };
7308 for (auto& element : elements)
7309 setter(*element);
7310 };
7311
7312 changeState(elementsToClearActive, CSSSelector::PseudoClassActive, [](auto& element) {
7313 element.setActive(false, false, Style::InvalidationScope::SelfChildrenAndSiblings);
7314 });
7315 changeState(elementsToSetActive, CSSSelector::PseudoClassActive, [](auto& element) {
7316 element.setActive(true, false, Style::InvalidationScope::SelfChildrenAndSiblings);
7317 });
7318 changeState(elementsToClearHover, CSSSelector::PseudoClassHover, [](auto& element) {
7319 element.setHovered(false, Style::InvalidationScope::SelfChildrenAndSiblings);
7320 });
7321 changeState(elementsToSetHover, CSSSelector::PseudoClassHover, [](auto& element) {
7322 element.setHovered(true, Style::InvalidationScope::SelfChildrenAndSiblings);
7323 });
7324}

7331Locale& Document::getCachedLocale(const AtomString& locale)
7332{
7333 AtomString localeKey = locale;
7334 if (locale.isEmpty() || !settings().langAttributeAwareFormControlUIEnabled())
7335 localeKey = defaultLanguage();
7336 LocaleIdentifierToLocaleMap::AddResult result = m_localeCache.add(localeKey, nullptr);
7337 if (result.isNewEntry)
7338 result.iterator->value = Locale::create(localeKey);
7339 return *(result.iterator->value);
7340}

7342Document& Document::ensureTemplateDocument()
7343{
7344 if (const Document* document = templateDocument())
7345 return const_cast<Document&>(*document);
7346
7347 if (isHTMLDocument())
7348 m_templateDocument = HTMLDocument::create(nullptr, m_settings, aboutBlankURL());
7349 else
7350 m_templateDocument = create(m_settings, aboutBlankURL());
7351
7352 m_templateDocument->setContextDocument(contextDocument());
7353 m_templateDocument->setTemplateDocumentHost(this); // balanced in dtor.
7354
7355 return *m_templateDocument;
7356}

7393
7394bool Document::useDarkAppearance(const RenderStyle* style) const
7395{
7396#if ENABLE(DARK_MODE_CSS)
7397 OptionSet<ColorScheme> colorScheme;
7398
7399 // Use the style's supported color schemes, if supplied.
7400 if (style)
7401 colorScheme = style->colorScheme().colorScheme();
7402
7403 // Fallback to the document's supported color schemes if style was empty (auto).
7404 if (colorScheme.isEmpty())
7405 colorScheme = m_colorScheme;
7406
7407 if (colorScheme.contains(ColorScheme::Dark) && !colorScheme.contains(ColorScheme::Light))
7408 return true;
7409#else
7410 UNUSED_PARAM(style);
7411#endif
7412
7413 bool pageUsesDarkAppearance = false;
7414 if (Page* documentPage = page())
7415 pageUsesDarkAppearance = documentPage->useDarkAppearance();
7416
7417 if (useSystemAppearance())
7418 return pageUsesDarkAppearance;
7419
7420#if ENABLE(DARK_MODE_CSS)
7421 if (colorScheme.contains(ColorScheme::Dark))
7422 return pageUsesDarkAppearance;
7423#endif
7424
7425 return false;
7426}

7429{
7430 if (auto* documentPage = page())
7431 return documentPage->useElevatedUserInterfaceLevel();
7432 return false;
7433}
7434
7435OptionSet<StyleColor::Options> Document::styleColorOptions(const RenderStyle* style) const
7436{
7437 OptionSet<StyleColor::Options> options;
7438 if (useSystemAppearance())
7439 options.add(StyleColor::Options::UseSystemAppearance);
7440 if (useDarkAppearance(style))
7441 options.add(StyleColor::Options::UseDarkAppearance);
7442 if (useElevatedUserInterfaceLevel())
7443 options.add(StyleColor::Options::UseElevatedUserInterfaceLevel);
7444 return options;
7445}
7446
7447CompositeOperator Document::compositeOperatorForBackgroundColor(const Color& color, const RenderObject& renderer) const
7448{
7449 if (LIKELY(!settings().punchOutWhiteBackgroundsInDarkMode() || !Color::isWhiteColor(color) || !renderer.useDarkAppearance()))
7450 return CompositeOperator::SourceOver;
7451
7452 auto* frameView = view();
7453 if (!frameView)
7454 return CompositeOperator::SourceOver;
7455
7456 // Mail on macOS uses a transparent view, and on iOS it is an opaque view. We need to
7457 // use different composite modes to get the right results in this case.
7458 return frameView->isTransparent() ? CompositeOperator::DestinationOut : CompositeOperator::DestinationIn;
7459}
7460
7461void Document::didAssociateFormControl(Element& element)
7462{
7463 auto* page = this->page();
7464 if (!page || !page->chrome().client().shouldNotifyOnFormChanges())
7465 return;
7466 m_associatedFormControls.add(&element);
7467 if (!m_didAssociateFormControlsTimer.isActive())
7468 m_didAssociateFormControlsTimer.startOneShot(0_s);
7469}
7470
7471void Document::didAssociateFormControlsTimerFired()
7472{
7473 auto vector = copyToVector(m_associatedFormControls);
7474 m_associatedFormControls.clear();
7475 if (auto* page = this->page()) {
7476 ASSERT(m_frame);
7477 page->chrome().client().didAssociateFormControls(vector, *m_frame);
7478 }
7479}

7481void Document::setCachedDOMCookies(const String& cookies)
7482{
7483 ASSERT(!isDOMCookieCacheValid());
7484 m_cachedDOMCookies = cookies;
7485 // The cookie cache is valid at most until we go back to the event loop.
7486 m_cookieCacheExpiryTimer.startOneShot(0_s);
7487}
7488
7489void Document::invalidateDOMCookieCache()
7490{
7491 m_cookieCacheExpiryTimer.stop();
7492 m_cachedDOMCookies = String();
7493}
7494
7495void Document::didLoadResourceSynchronously(const URL& url)
7496{
7497 // Synchronous resources loading can set cookies so we invalidate the cookies cache
7498 // in this case, to be safe.
7499 invalidateDOMCookieCache();
7500
7501 if (auto* page = this->page())
7502 page->cookieJar().clearCacheForHost(url.host().toString());
7503}
7504
7505void Document::ensurePlugInsInjectedScript(DOMWrapperWorld& world)
7506{
7507 if (m_hasInjectedPlugInsScript)
7508 return;
7509
7510 auto& scriptController = frame()->script();
7511
7512 // Use the JS file provided by the Chrome client, or fallback to the default one.
7513 String jsString = page()->chrome().client().plugInExtraScript();
7514 if (!jsString || !scriptController.shouldAllowUserAgentScripts(*this))
7515 jsString = StringImpl::createWithoutCopying(plugInsJavaScript, sizeof(plugInsJavaScript));
7516
7517 setHasEvaluatedUserAgentScripts();
7518 scriptController.evaluateInWorldIgnoringException(ScriptSourceCode(jsString), world);
7519
7520 m_hasInjectedPlugInsScript = true;
7521}

7549
7550bool Document::hasFocus() const
7551{
7552 Page* page = this->page();
7553 if (!page || !page->focusController().isActive())
7554 return false;
7555 if (Frame* focusedFrame = page->focusController().focusedFrame()) {
7556 if (focusedFrame->tree().isDescendantOf(frame()))
7557 return true;
7558 }
7559 return false;
7560}

7681#if USE(QUICK_LOOK)
7682
7683bool Document::shouldEnforceQuickLookSandbox() const
7684{
7685 if (m_isSynthesized || !m_frame)
7686 return false;
7687 DocumentLoader* documentLoader = m_frame->loader().activeDocumentLoader();
7688 return documentLoader && documentLoader->response().isQuickLook();
7689}
7690
7691void Document::applyQuickLookSandbox()
7692{
7693 auto& documentLoader = *m_frame->loader().activeDocumentLoader();
7694 auto documentURL = documentLoader.documentURL();
7695 auto& responseURL = documentLoader.responseURL();
7696 ASSERT(!documentURL.protocolIs(QLPreviewProtocol));
7697 ASSERT(responseURL.protocolIs(QLPreviewProtocol));
7698
7699 auto securityOrigin = SecurityOrigin::createNonLocalWithAllowedFilePath(responseURL, documentURL.fileSystemPath());
7700 securityOrigin->setStorageBlockingPolicy(StorageBlockingPolicy::BlockAll);
7701 setSecurityOriginPolicy(SecurityOriginPolicy::create(WTFMove(securityOrigin)));
7702
7703 static NeverDestroyed<String> quickLookCSP = makeString("default-src ", QLPreviewProtocol, ": 'unsafe-inline'; base-uri 'none'; sandbox allow-same-origin allow-scripts");
7704 RELEASE_ASSERT(contentSecurityPolicy());
7705 // The sandbox directive is only allowed if the policy is from an HTTP header.
7706 contentSecurityPolicy()->didReceiveHeader(quickLookCSP, ContentSecurityPolicyHeaderType::Enforce, ContentSecurityPolicy::PolicyFrom::HTTPHeader, referrer());
7707
7708 disableSandboxFlags(SandboxNavigation);
7709
7710 setReferrerPolicy(ReferrerPolicy::NoReferrer);
7711}
7712
7713#endif
7714
7715bool Document::shouldEnforceContentDispositionAttachmentSandbox() const
7716{
7717 if (!settings().contentDispositionAttachmentSandboxEnabled())
7718 return false;
7719
7720 if (m_isSynthesized)
7721 return false;
7722
7723 if (auto* documentLoader = m_frame ? m_frame->loader().activeDocumentLoader() : nullptr)
7724 return documentLoader->response().isAttachment();
7725 return false;
7726}
7727
7728void Document::applyContentDispositionAttachmentSandbox()
7729{
7730 ASSERT(shouldEnforceContentDispositionAttachmentSandbox());
7731
7732 setReferrerPolicy(ReferrerPolicy::NoReferrer);
7733 if (!isMediaDocument())
7734 enforceSandboxFlags(SandboxAll);
7735 else
7736 enforceSandboxFlags(SandboxOrigin);
7737}

7780
7781static void expandRootBoundsWithRootMargin(FloatRect& localRootBounds, const LengthBox& rootMargin, float zoomFactor)
7782{
7783 FloatBoxExtent rootMarginFloatBox(
7784 floatValueForLength(rootMargin.top(), localRootBounds.height()) * zoomFactor,
7785 floatValueForLength(rootMargin.right(), localRootBounds.width()) * zoomFactor,
7786 floatValueForLength(rootMargin.bottom(), localRootBounds.height()) * zoomFactor,
7787 floatValueForLength(rootMargin.left(), localRootBounds.width()) * zoomFactor
7788 );
7789
7790 localRootBounds.expand(rootMarginFloatBox);
7791}
7792
7793static std::optional<LayoutRect> computeClippedRectInRootContentsSpace(const LayoutRect& rect, const RenderElement* renderer)
7794{
7795 OptionSet<RenderObject::VisibleRectContextOption> visibleRectOptions = { RenderObject::VisibleRectContextOption::UseEdgeInclusiveIntersection, RenderObject::VisibleRectContextOption::ApplyCompositedClips, RenderObject::VisibleRectContextOption::ApplyCompositedContainerScrolls };
7796 std::optional<LayoutRect> rectInFrameAbsoluteSpace = renderer->computeVisibleRectInContainer(rect, &renderer->view(), {false /* hasPositionFixedDescendant */, false /* dirtyRectIsFlipped */, visibleRectOptions });
7797 if (!rectInFrameAbsoluteSpace || renderer->frame().isMainFrame())
7798 return rectInFrameAbsoluteSpace;
7799
7800 bool intersects = rectInFrameAbsoluteSpace->edgeInclusiveIntersect(renderer->view().frameView().layoutViewportRect());
7801 if (!intersects)
7802 return std::nullopt;
7803
7804 LayoutRect rectInFrameViewSpace(renderer->view().frameView().contentsToView(snappedIntRect(*rectInFrameAbsoluteSpace)));
7805 auto* ownerRenderer = renderer->frame().ownerRenderer();
7806 if (!ownerRenderer)
7807 return std::nullopt;
7808
7809 rectInFrameViewSpace.moveBy(ownerRenderer->contentBoxLocation());
7810 return computeClippedRectInRootContentsSpace(rectInFrameViewSpace, ownerRenderer);
7811}
7812
7813struct IntersectionObservationState {
7814 FloatRect absoluteTargetRect;
7815 FloatRect absoluteRootBounds;
7816 FloatRect absoluteIntersectionRect;
7817 bool isIntersecting { false };
7818};
7819
7820static std::optional<IntersectionObservationState> computeIntersectionState(FrameView& frameView, const IntersectionObserver& observer, Element& target, bool applyRootMargin)
7821{
7822 auto* targetRenderer = target.renderer();
7823 if (!targetRenderer)
7824 return std::nullopt;
7825
7826 FloatRect localRootBounds;
7827 RenderBlock* rootRenderer;
7828 if (observer.root()) {
7829 if (observer.trackingDocument() != &target.document())
7830 return std::nullopt;
7831
7832 if (!observer.root()->renderer() || !is<RenderBlock>(observer.root()->renderer()))
7833 return std::nullopt;
7834
7835 rootRenderer = downcast<RenderBlock>(observer.root()->renderer());
7836 if (!rootRenderer->isContainingBlockAncestorFor(*targetRenderer))
7837 return std::nullopt;
7838
7839 if (observer.root() == &target.document())
7840 localRootBounds = frameView.layoutViewportRect();
7841 else if (rootRenderer->hasOverflowClip())
7842 localRootBounds = rootRenderer->contentBoxRect();
7843 else
7844 localRootBounds = { FloatPoint(), rootRenderer->size() };
7845 } else {
7846 ASSERT(frameView.frame().isMainFrame());
7847 // FIXME: Handle the case of an implicit-root observer that has a target in a different frame tree.
7848 if (&targetRenderer->frame().mainFrame() != &frameView.frame())
7849 return std::nullopt;
7850 rootRenderer = frameView.renderView();
7851 localRootBounds = frameView.layoutViewportRect();
7852 }
7853
7854 if (applyRootMargin)
7855 expandRootBoundsWithRootMargin(localRootBounds, observer.rootMarginBox(), rootRenderer->style().effectiveZoom());
7856
7857 LayoutRect localTargetBounds;
7858 if (is<RenderBox>(*targetRenderer))
7859 localTargetBounds = downcast<RenderBox>(targetRenderer)->borderBoundingBox();
7860 else if (is<RenderInline>(targetRenderer)) {
7861 auto pair = target.boundingAbsoluteRectWithoutLayout();
7862 if (pair) {
7863 FloatRect absoluteTargetBounds = pair->second;
7864 localTargetBounds = enclosingLayoutRect(targetRenderer->absoluteToLocalQuad(absoluteTargetBounds).boundingBox());
7865 }
7866 } else if (is<RenderLineBreak>(targetRenderer))
7867 localTargetBounds = downcast<RenderLineBreak>(targetRenderer)->linesBoundingBox();
7868
7869 std::optional<LayoutRect> rootLocalTargetRect;
7870 if (observer.root()) {
7871 OptionSet<RenderObject::VisibleRectContextOption> visibleRectOptions = { RenderObject::VisibleRectContextOption::UseEdgeInclusiveIntersection, RenderObject::VisibleRectContextOption::ApplyCompositedClips, RenderObject::VisibleRectContextOption::ApplyCompositedContainerScrolls };
7872 rootLocalTargetRect = targetRenderer->computeVisibleRectInContainer(localTargetBounds, rootRenderer, { false /* hasPositionFixedDescendant */, false /* dirtyRectIsFlipped */, visibleRectOptions });
7873 } else
7874 rootLocalTargetRect = computeClippedRectInRootContentsSpace(localTargetBounds, targetRenderer);
7875
7876 FloatRect rootLocalIntersectionRect = localRootBounds;
7877
7878 IntersectionObservationState intersectionState;
7879 intersectionState.isIntersecting = rootLocalTargetRect && rootLocalIntersectionRect.edgeInclusiveIntersect(*rootLocalTargetRect);
7880 intersectionState.absoluteTargetRect = targetRenderer->localToAbsoluteQuad(FloatRect(localTargetBounds)).boundingBox();
7881 intersectionState.absoluteRootBounds = rootRenderer->localToAbsoluteQuad(localRootBounds).boundingBox();
7882
7883 if (intersectionState.isIntersecting) {
7884 FloatRect rootAbsoluteIntersectionRect = rootRenderer->localToAbsoluteQuad(rootLocalIntersectionRect).boundingBox();
7885 if (&targetRenderer->frame() == &rootRenderer->frame())
7886 intersectionState.absoluteIntersectionRect = rootAbsoluteIntersectionRect;
7887 else {
7888 FloatRect rootViewIntersectionRect = frameView.contentsToView(rootAbsoluteIntersectionRect);
7889 intersectionState.absoluteIntersectionRect = targetRenderer->view().frameView().rootViewToContents(rootViewIntersectionRect);
7890 }
7891 intersectionState.isIntersecting = intersectionState.absoluteIntersectionRect.edgeInclusiveIntersect(intersectionState.absoluteTargetRect);
7892 }
7893
7894 return intersectionState;
7895}
7896
7897void Document::updateIntersectionObservations()
7898{
7899 auto* frameView = view();
7900 if (!frameView)
7901 return;
7902
7903 bool needsLayout = frameView->layoutContext().isLayoutPending() || (renderView() && renderView()->needsLayout());
7904 if (needsLayout || hasPendingStyleRecalc())
7905 return;
7906
7907 Vector<WeakPtr<IntersectionObserver>> intersectionObserversWithPendingNotifications;
7908
7909 for (const auto& observer : m_intersectionObservers) {
7910 bool needNotify = false;
7911 auto timestamp = observer->nowTimestamp();
7912 if (!timestamp)
7913 continue;
7914 for (Element* target : observer->observationTargets()) {
7915 auto& targetRegistrations = target->intersectionObserverDataIfExists()->registrations;
7916 auto index = targetRegistrations.findMatching([observer](auto& registration) {
7917 return registration.observer.get() == observer;
7918 });
7919 ASSERT(index != notFound);
7920 auto& registration = targetRegistrations[index];
7921
7922 bool isSameOriginObservation = &target->document() == this || target->document().securityOrigin().isSameOriginDomain(securityOrigin());
7923 auto intersectionState = computeIntersectionState(*frameView, *observer, *target, isSameOriginObservation);
7924
7925 float intersectionRatio = 0;
7926 size_t thresholdIndex = 0;
7927 if (intersectionState) {
7928 if (intersectionState->isIntersecting) {
7929 float absTargetArea = intersectionState->absoluteTargetRect.area();
7930 if (absTargetArea)
7931 intersectionRatio = intersectionState->absoluteIntersectionRect.area() / absTargetArea;
7932 else
7933 intersectionRatio = 1;
7934
7935 for (auto threshold : observer->thresholds()) {
7936 if (!(threshold <= intersectionRatio || WTF::areEssentiallyEqual<float>(threshold, intersectionRatio)))
7937 break;
7938 ++thresholdIndex;
7939 }
7940 }
7941 }
7942
7943 if (!registration.previousThresholdIndex || thresholdIndex != registration.previousThresholdIndex) {
7944 FloatRect targetBoundingClientRect;
7945 FloatRect clientIntersectionRect;
7946 FloatRect clientRootBounds;
7947 if (intersectionState) {
7948 auto* targetFrameView = target->document().view();
7949 targetBoundingClientRect = targetFrameView->absoluteToClientRect(intersectionState->absoluteTargetRect, target->renderer()->style().effectiveZoom());
7950 clientRootBounds = frameView->absoluteToLayoutViewportRect(intersectionState->absoluteRootBounds);
7951 if (intersectionState->isIntersecting)
7952 clientIntersectionRect = targetFrameView->absoluteToClientRect(intersectionState->absoluteIntersectionRect, target->renderer()->style().effectiveZoom());
7953 }
7954
7955 std::optional<DOMRectInit> reportedRootBounds;
7956 if (isSameOriginObservation) {
7957 reportedRootBounds = DOMRectInit({
7958 clientRootBounds.x(),
7959 clientRootBounds.y(),
7960 clientRootBounds.width(),
7961 clientRootBounds.height()
7962 });
7963 }
7964
7965 observer->appendQueuedEntry(IntersectionObserverEntry::create({
7966 timestamp->milliseconds(),
7967 reportedRootBounds,
7968 { targetBoundingClientRect.x(), targetBoundingClientRect.y(), targetBoundingClientRect.width(), targetBoundingClientRect.height() },
7969 { clientIntersectionRect.x(), clientIntersectionRect.y(), clientIntersectionRect.width(), clientIntersectionRect.height() },
7970 intersectionRatio,
7971 target,
7972 thresholdIndex > 0,
7973 }));
7974 needNotify = true;
7975 registration.previousThresholdIndex = thresholdIndex;
7976 }
7977 }
7978 if (needNotify)
7979 intersectionObserversWithPendingNotifications.append(makeWeakPtr(observer.get()));
7980 }
7981
7982 for (const auto& observer : intersectionObserversWithPendingNotifications) {
7983 if (observer)
7984 observer->notify();
7985 }
7986}
7987
7988void Document::scheduleInitialIntersectionObservationUpdate()
7989{
7990 if (m_readyState == Complete)
7991 scheduleRenderingUpdate(RenderingUpdateStep::IntersectionObservations);
7992 else if (!m_intersectionObserversInitialUpdateTimer.isActive())
7993 m_intersectionObserversInitialUpdateTimer.startOneShot(intersectionObserversInitialUpdateDelay);
7994}
7995
7996IntersectionObserverData& Document::ensureIntersectionObserverData()
7997{
7998 if (!m_intersectionObserverData)
7999 m_intersectionObserverData = makeUnique<IntersectionObserverData>();
8000 return *m_intersectionObserverData;
8001}

8003#endif

8005#if ENABLE(RESIZE_OBSERVER)
8006
8007void Document::addResizeObserver(ResizeObserver& observer)
8008{
8009 if (!m_resizeObservers.contains(&observer))
8010 m_resizeObservers.append(makeWeakPtr(&observer));
8011}
8012
8013void Document::removeResizeObserver(ResizeObserver& observer)
8014{
8015 m_resizeObservers.removeFirst(&observer);
8016}
8017
8018bool Document::hasResizeObservers()
8019{
8020 return !m_resizeObservers.isEmpty();
8021}
8022
8023size_t Document::gatherResizeObservations(size_t deeperThan)
8024{
8025 size_t minDepth = ResizeObserver::maxElementDepth();
8026 for (const auto& observer : m_resizeObservers) {
8027 if (!observer->hasObservations())
8028 continue;
8029 auto depth = observer->gatherObservations(deeperThan);
8030 minDepth = std::min(minDepth, depth);
8031 }
8032 return minDepth;
8033}
8034
8035void Document::deliverResizeObservations()
8036{
8037 auto observersToNotify = m_resizeObservers;
8038 for (const auto& observer : observersToNotify) {
8039 if (!observer || !observer->hasActiveObservations())
8040 continue;
8041 observer->deliverObservations();
8042 }
8043}
8044
8045bool Document::hasSkippedResizeObservations() const
8046{
8047 for (const auto& observer : m_resizeObservers) {
8048 if (observer->hasSkippedObservations())
8049 return true;
8050 }
8051 return false;
8052}
8053
8054void Document::setHasSkippedResizeObservations(bool skipped)
8055{
8056 for (const auto& observer : m_resizeObservers)
8057 observer->setHasSkippedObservations(skipped);
8058}
8059
8060void Document::updateResizeObservations(Page& page)
8061{
8062 if (!hasResizeObservers())
8063 return;
8064
8065 // We need layout the whole frame tree here. Because ResizeObserver could observe element in other frame,
8066 // and it could change other frame in deliverResizeObservations().
8067 page.layoutIfNeeded();
8068
8069 // Start check resize obervers;
8070 for (size_t depth = gatherResizeObservations(0); depth != ResizeObserver::maxElementDepth(); depth = gatherResizeObservations(depth)) {
8071 deliverResizeObservations();
8072 page.layoutIfNeeded();
8073 }
8074
8075 if (hasSkippedResizeObservations()) {
8076 setHasSkippedResizeObservations(false);
8077 String url;
8078 unsigned line = 0;
8079 unsigned column = 0;
8080 getParserLocation(url, line, column);
8081 reportException("ResizeObserver loop completed with undelivered notifications.", line, column, url, nullptr, nullptr);
8082 // Starting a new schedule the next round of notify.
8083 scheduleRenderingUpdate(RenderingUpdateStep::ResizeObservations);
8084 }
8085}
8086
8087#endif

8122
8123void Document::orientationChanged(int orientation)
8124{
8125 LOG(Events, "Document %p orientationChanged - orientation %d", this, orientation);
8126 dispatchWindowEvent(Event::create(eventNames().orientationchangeEvent, Event::CanBubble::No, Event::IsCancelable::No));
8127 m_orientationNotifier.orientationChanged(orientation);
8128}

8241void Document::registerArticleElement(Element& article)

8244}
8245
8246void Document::unregisterArticleElement(Element& article)
8247{
8248 m_articleElements.remove(article);
8249 if (m_mainArticleElement == &article)
8250 m_mainArticleElement = nullptr;
8251}
8252
8253void Document::updateMainArticleElementAfterLayout()
8254{
8255 ASSERT(page() && page()->requestedLayoutMilestones().contains(DidRenderSignificantAmountOfText));
8256
8257 // If there are too many article elements on the page, don't consider any one of them to be "main content".
8258 const unsigned maxNumberOfArticlesBeforeIgnoringMainContentArticle = 10;
8259
8260 // We consider an article to be main content if it is either:
8261 // 1. The only article element in the document.
8262 // 2. Much taller than the next tallest article, and also much larger than the viewport.
8263 const float minimumSecondTallestArticleHeightFactor = 4;
8264 const float minimumViewportAreaFactor = 5;
8265
8266 m_mainArticleElement = nullptr;
8267
8268 auto numberOfArticles = m_articleElements.computeSize();
8269 if (!numberOfArticles || numberOfArticles > maxNumberOfArticlesBeforeIgnoringMainContentArticle)
8270 return;
8271
8272 RefPtr<Element> tallestArticle;
8273 float tallestArticleHeight = 0;
8274 float tallestArticleWidth = 0;
8275 float secondTallestArticleHeight = 0;
8276
8277 for (auto& article : m_articleElements) {
8278 auto* box = article.renderBox();
8279 float height = box ? box->height().toFloat() : 0;
8280 if (height >= tallestArticleHeight) {
8281 secondTallestArticleHeight = tallestArticleHeight;
8282 tallestArticleHeight = height;
8283 tallestArticleWidth = box ? box->width().toFloat() : 0;
8284 tallestArticle = &article;
8285 } else if (height >= secondTallestArticleHeight)
8286 secondTallestArticleHeight = height;
8287 }
8288
8289 if (numberOfArticles == 1) {
8290 m_mainArticleElement = makeWeakPtr(tallestArticle.get());
8291 return;
8292 }
8293
8294 if (tallestArticleHeight < minimumSecondTallestArticleHeightFactor * secondTallestArticleHeight)
8295 return;
8296
8297 if (!view())
8298 return;
8299
8300 auto viewportSize = view()->layoutViewportRect().size();
8301 if (tallestArticleWidth * tallestArticleHeight < minimumViewportAreaFactor * (viewportSize.width() * viewportSize.height()).toFloat())
8302 return;
8303
8304 m_mainArticleElement = makeWeakPtr(tallestArticle.get());
8305}

8323
8324void Document::downgradeReferrerToRegistrableDomain()
8325{
8326 URL referrerURL { { }, referrer() };
8327 if (referrerURL.isEmpty())
8328 return;
8329
8330 auto domainString = RegistrableDomain { referrerURL }.string();
8331 if (domainString.isEmpty())
8332 return;
8333
8334 if (auto port = referrerURL.port())
8335 m_referrerOverride = makeString(referrerURL.protocol(), "://", domainString, ':', *port, '/');
8336 else
8337 m_referrerOverride = makeString(referrerURL.protocol(), "://", domainString, '/');
8338}

8371
8372Vector<RefPtr<WebAnimation>> Document::getAnimations()
8373{
8374 return matchingAnimations([] (Element& target) -> bool {
8375 return !target.containingShadowRoot();
8376 });
8377}
8378
8379Vector<RefPtr<WebAnimation>> Document::matchingAnimations(const WTF::Function<bool(Element&)>& function)
8380{
8381 // For the list of animations to be current, we need to account for any pending CSS changes,
8382 // such as updates to CSS Animations and CSS Transitions.
8383 updateStyleIfNeeded();
8384
8385 Vector<RefPtr<WebAnimation>> animations;
8386 for (auto* animation : WebAnimation::instances()) {
8387 if (!animation || !animation->isRelevant() || !is<KeyframeEffect>(animation->effect()))
8388 continue;
8389
8390 auto* target = downcast<KeyframeEffect>(*animation->effect()).targetElementOrPseudoElement();
8391 if (target && target->isConnected() && &target->document() == this && function(*target))
8392 animations.append(animation);
8393 }
8394
8395 std::stable_sort(animations.begin(), animations.end(), [](auto& lhs, auto& rhs) {
8396 return compareAnimationsByCompositeOrder(*lhs, *rhs);
8397 });
8398
8399 return animations;
8400}

8404void Document::registerAttachmentIdentifier(const String& identifier)
8405{
8406 // FIXME: Can this null check for Frame be removed?
8407 if (frame())
8408 editor().registerAttachmentIdentifier(identifier);
8409}
8410
8411void Document::didInsertAttachmentElement(HTMLAttachmentElement& attachment)
8412{
8413 auto identifier = attachment.uniqueIdentifier();
8414 auto previousIdentifier = identifier;
8415 bool previousIdentifierIsNotUnique = !previousIdentifier.isEmpty() && m_attachmentIdentifierToElementMap.contains(previousIdentifier);
8416 if (identifier.isEmpty() || previousIdentifierIsNotUnique) {
8417 previousIdentifier = identifier;
8418 identifier = createCanonicalUUIDString();
8419 attachment.setUniqueIdentifier(identifier);
8420 }
8421
8422 m_attachmentIdentifierToElementMap.set(identifier, attachment);
8423
8424 // FIXME: Can this null check for Frame be removed?
8425 if (frame()) {
8426 if (previousIdentifierIsNotUnique)
8427 editor().cloneAttachmentData(previousIdentifier, identifier);
8428 editor().didInsertAttachmentElement(attachment);
8429 }
8430}
8431
8432void Document::didRemoveAttachmentElement(HTMLAttachmentElement& attachment)
8433{
8434 auto identifier = attachment.uniqueIdentifier();
8435 if (!identifier)
8436 return;
8437
8438 m_attachmentIdentifierToElementMap.remove(identifier);
8439
8440 // FIXME: Can this null check for Frame be removed?
8441 if (frame())
8442 editor().didRemoveAttachmentElement(attachment);
8443}
8444
8445RefPtr<HTMLAttachmentElement> Document::attachmentForIdentifier(const String& identifier) const
8446{
8447 return m_attachmentIdentifierToElementMap.get(identifier);
8448}

8451
8452static MessageSource messageSourceForWTFLogChannel(const WTFLogChannel& channel)
8453{
8454 static const NeverDestroyed<String> mediaChannel = MAKE_STATIC_STRING_IMPL("media");
8455 static const NeverDestroyed<String> webrtcChannel = MAKE_STATIC_STRING_IMPL("webrtc");
8456 static const NeverDestroyed<String> mediaSourceChannel = MAKE_STATIC_STRING_IMPL("mediasource");
8457
8458 if (equalIgnoringASCIICase(mediaChannel, channel.name))
8459 return MessageSource::Media;
8460
8461 if (equalIgnoringASCIICase(webrtcChannel, channel.name))
8462 return MessageSource::WebRTC;
8463
8464 if (equalIgnoringASCIICase(mediaSourceChannel, channel.name))
8465 return MessageSource::MediaSource;
8466
8467 return MessageSource::Other;
8468}
8469
8470static MessageLevel messageLevelFromWTFLogLevel(WTFLogLevel level)
8471{
8472 switch (level) {
8473 case WTFLogLevel::Always:
8474 return MessageLevel::Log;
8475 case WTFLogLevel::Error:
8476 return MessageLevel::Error;
8477 break;
8478 case WTFLogLevel::Warning:
8479 return MessageLevel::Warning;
8480 break;
8481 case WTFLogLevel::Info:
8482 return MessageLevel::Info;
8483 break;
8484 case WTFLogLevel::Debug:
8485 return MessageLevel::Debug;
8486 break;
8487 }
8488
8489 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
8490 return MessageLevel::Log;
8491}
8492
8493static inline Vector<JSONLogValue> crossThreadCopy(Vector<JSONLogValue>&& source)
8494{
8495 auto values = WTFMove(source);
8496 for (auto& value : values)
8497 value.value = crossThreadCopy(WTFMove(value.value));
8498 return values;
8499}
8500
8501void Document::didLogMessage(const WTFLogChannel& channel, WTFLogLevel level, Vector<JSONLogValue>&& logMessages)
8502{
8503 if (!isMainThread()) {
8504 postTask([this, channel, level, logMessages = crossThreadCopy(WTFMove(logMessages))](auto&) mutable {
8505 didLogMessage(channel, level, WTFMove(logMessages));
8506 });
8507 return;
8508 }
8509 auto* page = this->page();
8510 if (!page)
8511 return;
8512
8513 ASSERT(page->sessionID().isAlwaysOnLoggingAllowed());
8514
8515 auto messageSource = messageSourceForWTFLogChannel(channel);
8516 if (messageSource == MessageSource::Other)
8517 return;
8518
8519 eventLoop().queueTask(TaskSource::InternalAsyncTask, [weakThis = makeWeakPtr(*this), level, messageSource, logMessages = WTFMove(logMessages)]() mutable {
8520 if (!weakThis || !weakThis->page())
8521 return;
8522
8523 auto messageLevel = messageLevelFromWTFLogLevel(level);
8524 auto message = makeUnique<Inspector::ConsoleMessage>(messageSource, MessageType::Log, messageLevel, WTFMove(logMessages), mainWorldExecState(weakThis->frame()));
8525
8526 weakThis->addConsoleMessage(WTFMove(message));
8527 });
8528}

8530#if ENABLE(SERVICE_WORKER)
8531void Document::setServiceWorkerConnection(SWClientConnection* serviceWorkerConnection)
8532{
8533 if (m_serviceWorkerConnection == serviceWorkerConnection || m_hasPreparedForDestruction || m_isSuspended)
8534 return;
8535
8536 if (m_serviceWorkerConnection)
8537 m_serviceWorkerConnection->unregisterServiceWorkerClient(identifier());
8538
8539 m_serviceWorkerConnection = serviceWorkerConnection;
8540
8541 if (!m_serviceWorkerConnection)
8542 return;
8543
8544 auto controllingServiceWorkerRegistrationIdentifier = activeServiceWorker() ? std::make_optional<ServiceWorkerRegistrationIdentifier>(activeServiceWorker()->registrationIdentifier()) : std::nullopt;
8545 m_serviceWorkerConnection->registerServiceWorkerClient(topOrigin(), ServiceWorkerClientData::from(*this, *serviceWorkerConnection), controllingServiceWorkerRegistrationIdentifier, userAgent(url()));
8546}
8547#endif

8581
8582bool Document::hitTest(const HitTestRequest& request, HitTestResult& result)
8583{
8584 return hitTest(request, result.hitTestLocation(), result);
8585}
8586
8587bool Document::hitTest(const HitTestRequest& request, const HitTestLocation& location, HitTestResult& result)
8588{
8589 Ref<Document> protectedThis(*this);
8590 updateLayout();
8591 if (!renderView())
8592 return false;
8593
8594#if ASSERT_ENABLED
8595 SetForScope<bool> hitTestRestorer { m_inHitTesting, true };
8596#endif
8597
8598 auto& frameView = renderView()->frameView();
8599 Ref<FrameView> protector(frameView);
8600
8601 FrameFlatteningLayoutDisallower disallower(frameView);
8602
8603 bool resultLayer = renderView()->layer()->hitTest(request, location, result);
8604
8605 // ScrollView scrollbars are not the same as RenderLayer scrollbars tested by RenderLayer::hitTestOverflowControls,
8606 // so we need to test ScrollView scrollbars separately here. In case of using overlay scrollbars, the layer hit test
8607 // will always work so we need to check the ScrollView scrollbars in that case too.
8608 if (!resultLayer || ScrollbarTheme::theme().usesOverlayScrollbars()) {
8609 // FIXME: Consider if this test should be done unconditionally.
8610 if (request.allowsFrameScrollbars()) {
8611 IntPoint windowPoint = frameView.contentsToWindow(location.roundedPoint());
8612 if (auto* frameScrollbar = frameView.scrollbarAtPoint(windowPoint)) {
8613 result.setScrollbar(frameScrollbar);
8614 return true;
8615 }
8616 }
8617 }
8618 return resultLayer;
8619}

8621ElementIdentifier Document::identifierForElement(Element& element)
8622{
8623 ASSERT(&element.document() == this);
8624 auto result = m_identifiedElementsMap.ensure(&element, [&] {
8625 return element.createElementIdentifier();
8626 });
8627 return result.iterator->value;
8628}
8629
8630Element* Document::searchForElementByIdentifier(const ElementIdentifier& identifier)
8631{
8632 for (auto it = m_identifiedElementsMap.begin(); it != m_identifiedElementsMap.end(); ++it) {
8633 if (it->value == identifier)
8634 return it->key;
8635 }
8636
8637 return nullptr;
8638}

8643}

8811
8812void Document::prepareCanvasesForDisplayIfNeeded()
8813{
8814 // Some canvas contexts need to do work when rendering has finished but
8815 // before their content is composited.
8816
8817 // FIXME: Calling prepareForDisplay should not call back into a method
8818 // that would mutate our m_canvasesNeedingDisplayPreparation list. It
8819 // would be nice if this could be enforced to remove the copyToVector.
8820
8821 auto canvases = copyToVectorOf<Ref<HTMLCanvasElement>>(m_canvasesNeedingDisplayPreparation);
8822 m_canvasesNeedingDisplayPreparation.clear();
8823 for (auto& canvas : canvases) {
8824 // However, if they are not in the document body, then they won't
8825 // be composited and thus don't need preparation. Unfortunately they
8826 // can't tell at the time they were added to the list, since they
8827 // could be inserted or removed from the document body afterwards.
8828 if (!canvas->isInTreeScope())
8829 continue;
8830 canvas->prepareForDisplay();
8831 }
8832}
8833
8834void Document::clearCanvasPreparation(HTMLCanvasElement& canvas)
8835{
8836 m_canvasesNeedingDisplayPreparation.remove(canvas);
8837}
8838
8839void Document::canvasChanged(CanvasBase& canvasBase, const std::optional<FloatRect>&)
8840{
8841 if (!is<HTMLCanvasElement>(canvasBase))
8842 return;
8843 auto& canvas = downcast<HTMLCanvasElement>(canvasBase);
8844 if (canvas.needsPreparationForDisplay())
8845 m_canvasesNeedingDisplayPreparation.add(canvas);
8846}
8847
8848void Document::canvasDestroyed(CanvasBase& canvasBase)
8849{
8850 if (!is<HTMLCanvasElement>(canvasBase))
8851 return;
8852 auto& canvas = downcast<HTMLCanvasElement>(canvasBase);
8853 m_canvasesNeedingDisplayPreparation.remove(canvas);
8854}
8855
8856JSC::VM& Document::vm()
8857{
8858 return commonVM();
8859}
